	<h1 id=3D"firstHeading" class=3D"firstHeading mw-first-heading">List of ac=
cidents and incidents involving commercial aircraft</h1>
	<div id=3D"bodyContent" class=3D"vector-body">
		<div id=3D"siteSub" class=3D"noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encycloped=
ia</div>
		<div id=3D"contentSub"></div>
		<div id=3D"contentSub2"></div>
	=09
		<div id=3D"jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class=3D"mw-jump-link" href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_a=
ccidents_and_incidents_involving_commercial_aircraft#mw-head">Jump to navig=
ation</a>
		<a class=3D"mw-jump-link" href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_a=
ccidents_and_incidents_involving_commercial_aircraft#searchInput">Jump to s=
earch</a>
		<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang=
=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"mw-parser-output"><div class=3D"shortdesc=
ription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Wikipe=
dia list article</div>
<p>=20
This <b>List of accidents and incidents involving commercial aircraft</b> i=
ncludes notable events that have a corresponding Wikipedia article. Entries=
 in this list involve passenger or cargo aircraft that are operating commer=
cially and meet this list's size criteria=E2=80=94passenger aircraft with a=
 seating capacity of at least 10 passengers, or commercial cargo aircraft o=
f at least: 20,000&nbsp;lb (9,100&nbsp;kg). The list is grouped by the year=
 in which the accident or incident occurred.
</p>

<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1910s_and_1920s">1910s and 1920s</spa=
n><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accide=
nts_and_incidents_involving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;secti=
on=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: 1910s and 1920s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-e=
ditsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1919">1919</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1919">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>July 21 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W=
ingfoot_Air_Express_crash" title=3D"Wingfoot Air Express crash">Goodyear di=
rigible <i>Wingfoot Air Express</i> catches fire and crashes</a></b> into t=
he Illinois Trust and Savings Building in Chicago, Illinois, while carrying=
 passengers to a local amusement park, killing thirteen people: three out o=
f the five on board and ten others on the ground, with 27 others on the gro=
und being injured.</li>
<li>August 2 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1919_V=
erona_Caproni_Ca.48_crash" title=3D"1919 Verona Caproni Ca.48 crash">Capron=
i Ca.48 crashes at Verona</a></b>, Italy, during a flight from Venice to Ta=
liedo, Milan, killing all on board (14, 15, or 17 people, according to diff=
erent sources).</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1920">1920</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1920">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>December 14 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1920_Golders_Green_Handley_Page_O/400_crash" title=3D"1920 Golders Green H=
andley Page O/400 crash">Handley Page O/400 hits a tree and crashes</a></b>=
 at Golders Green, London, after failing to gain height following takeoff, =
killing four out of eight on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1922">1922</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1922">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>April 7 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1922_Picardie_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1922 Picardie mid-air collision=
">Picardie mid-air collision</a></b>, a de Havilland DH.18A, <i>G-EAWO</i>,=
 operated by Daimler Hire Ltd., collides with a Farman F.60 Goliath, <i>F-G=
EAD</i>, operated by Compagnie des Grands Express A=C3=A9riens (CGEA), over=
 the Thieulloy-St. Antoine road near Picardie, France, killing all seven pe=
ople on both aircraft. This is the first mid-air collision of two airliners=
.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1923">1923</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1923">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>May 14 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/May=
_1923_Air_Union_Farman_Goliath_crash" title=3D"May 1923 Air Union Farman Go=
liath crash">Air Union Farman F.60 Goliath crashes</a></b> near Monsures, S=
omme, France, due to the structural failure of a wing, killing all six on b=
oard.</li>
<li>August 27 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Augu=
st_1923_Air_Union_Farman_Goliath_crash" title=3D"August 1923 Air Union Farm=
an Goliath crash">Air Union Farman F.60 Goliath crashes</a></b> near East M=
alling, Kent, England, due to engine failure, and confusion among the passe=
ngers, killing one of 13 on board.</li>
<li>September 14 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
23_Daimler_Airway_de_Havilland_DH.34_crash" title=3D"">Daimler Airway de Ha=
villand DH.34 crashes</a></b> at Ivinghoe, Buckinghamshire, England, after =
stalling while attempting an emergency landing, killing all five on board.<=
/li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1924">1924</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1924">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>December 24 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1924_Imperial_Airways_de_Havilland_DH.34_crash" title=3D"1924 Imperial Ai=
rways de Havilland DH.34 crash">Imperial Airways de Havilland DH.34 crashes=
</a></b> near Purley, Surrey, England, due to a stall during an attempted e=
mergency landing in response to an unknown mechanical defect, killing all e=
ight on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1926">1926</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1926">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>August 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aug=
ust_1926_Air_Union_Bl%C3%A9riot_155_crash" title=3D"August 1926 Air Union B=
l=C3=A9riot 155 crash">An Air Union Bl=C3=A9riot 155 crashes</a></b> during=
 a failed emergency landing attempt at College Farm in Aldington, Kent, Eng=
land, after experiencing engine failure; two of the 15 on board are killed =
on impact and the pilot dies of his injuries one day later.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October=
_1926_Air_Union_Bl%C3%A9riot_155_crash" title=3D"October 1926 Air Union Bl=
=C3=A9riot 155 crash">An Air Union Bl=C3=A9riot 155 crashes</a></b> at Leig=
h, Kent, England, after the aircraft catches fire in mid-air during an atte=
mpted emergency landing at Penshurst Airfield, killing both crew members an=
d all five passengers; this is the first in-flight fire to occur on an airl=
iner.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1927">1927</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1927">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>August 22 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
927_KLM_Fokker_F.VIII_crash" title=3D"1927 KLM Fokker F.VIII crash">KLM Fok=
ker F. VIII crashes</a></b> near Sevenoaks, Kent, England, due to structura=
l failure of the tailfin, killing one of 11 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1928">1928</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit =
section: 1928">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></h3>
<ul><li>July 13 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
28_Imperial_Airways_Vickers_Vulcan_crash" title=3D"1928 Imperial Airways Vi=
ckers Vulcan crash">Imperial Airways Vickers Vulcan crashes</a></b> on a te=
st flight from Croydon Airport, England, with a pilot and five passengers n=
ear Purley, Surrey, 3 miles (4.8&nbsp;km) from the airport, with the death =
of four passengers.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1929">1929</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1929">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>June 17 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
29_Imperial_Airways_Handley_Page_W.10_crash" title=3D"1929 Imperial Airways=
 Handley Page W.10 crash">Imperial Airways Handley Page W.10 ditches</a></b=
> in the English Channel due to engine failure, killing seven of the 13 on =
board.</li>
<li>September 6 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
29_Jask_Imperial_Airways_de_Havilland_Hercules_crash" title=3D"1929 Jask Im=
perial Airways de Havilland Hercules crash">Imperial Airways de Havilland H=
ercules crashes</a></b> whilst landing at Jask Airport, Iran, killing three=
 of the five occupants.</li>
<li>November 6 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1929=
_Luft_Hansa_Junkers_G_24_crash" title=3D"1929 Luft Hansa Junkers G 24 crash=
">Junkers G 24 crashes</a></b> near Marden Park in Godstone, Surrey, Englan=
d; killing 7 of the eight occupants.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1930s">1930s</span><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_in=
volving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Ed=
it section: 1930s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1930">1930</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1930">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 10 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1930_Air_Union_Farman_Goliath_crash" title=3D"1930 Air Union Farman Golia=
th crash">Air Union Farman F.63 Goliath crashes</a></b> during an emergency=
 landing at Marden Airfield, Marden, Kent, following failure of the right t=
ailplane, killing two of six on board.</li>
<li>October 5 =E2=80=93 On its maiden voyage from the United Kingdom to Bri=
tish India, the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R101" title=3D"=
R101">British civil airship R101 crashes and burns</a></b> in Allonne, Oise=
, France, while flying at low altitude at night in a rainstorm, killing 48 =
out of 54 on board, the worst civil airship disaster in history.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1931">1931</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D13" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1931">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>March 21 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
931_Avro_Ten_Southern_Cloud_disappearance" title=3D"1931 Avro Ten Southern =
Cloud disappearance">Australian National Airways Avro 618 Ten, <i>Southern =
Cloud</i>, disappears</a></b> in severe weather on a flight from Sydney to =
Melbourne, killing all eight on board in Australia's first significant airl=
ine disaster; the crash site in the Snowy Mountains remains undiscovered un=
til 1958.</li>
<li>March 31 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1931_T=
ranscontinental_%26_Western_Air_Fokker_F-10_crash" title=3D"1931 Transconti=
nental &amp; Western Air Fokker F-10 crash">Transcontinental &amp; Western =
Air Fokker F-10 Trimotor crashes</a></b> near Bazaar, Kansas, after a wing =
breaks off in flight, killing all eight aboard, including University of Not=
re Dame football coach <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knute_Rockn=
e" title=3D"Knute Rockne">Knute Rockne</a>.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1933">1933</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D14" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1933">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>March 28 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
1933_Imperial_Airways_Dixmude_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1933 Im=
perial Airways Dixmude crash">1933 Imperial Airways Dixmude crash</a></b> i=
n Belgium of an Armstrong Whitworth Argosy II is the first suspected case o=
f air sabotage; all 15 on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 10 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
33_United_Airlines_Boeing_247_mid-air_explosion" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"1933 United Airlines Boeing 247 mid-air explosion">United Airlines cra=
sh near Chesterton</a></b>: a Boeing 247 is destroyed by a bomb over Cheste=
rton, Indiana, United States, in the first proven case of air sabotage on a=
 commercial aircraft; all seven on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1933_Imperial_Airways_Ruysselede_crash" title=3D"1933 Imperial Airways Ru=
ysselede crash">1933 Imperial Airways Ruysselede crash</a></b> in Belgium, =
an Avro Ten collides with a radio mast, killing all 10 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1934">1934</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D15" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1934">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 23 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1934_United_Airlines_Utah_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1934 Unite=
d Airlines Utah crash">United Air Lines Boeing 247</a></b> crashes into a U=
tah canyon in bad weather, killing all eight on board.</li>
<li>May 9 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1934_Air=
_France_Wibault_282T_crash" title=3D"1934 Air France Wibault 282T crash">Ai=
r France Wibault 282T crashes</a></b> into the English Channel off Dungenes=
s, Kent, killing all six on board.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1934_Sw=
issair_Tuttlingen_accident" title=3D"1934 Swissair Tuttlingen accident">Swi=
ssair Curtiss T-32 Condor II crashes</a></b> near Tuttlingen, Germany, afte=
r a wing separates in a thunderstorm, killing all 12 passengers and crew on=
 board.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1934_=
Hillman%27s_Airways_de_Havilland_Dragon_Rapide_crash" title=3D"1934 Hillman=
's Airways de Havilland Dragon Rapide crash">Hillman's Airways de Havilland=
 Dragon Rapide crashes</a></b> into the English Channel off Folkestone, Ken=
t, due to pilot error, killing all seven on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1935">1935</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1935">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>May 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fli=
ght_6" title=3D"TWA Flight 6">TWA Flight 6</a></b>, a Douglas DC-2 operatin=
g a multi-leg flight from Los Angeles, California, to Newark, New Jersey, U=
nited States, crashes near Atlanta, Missouri, due to poor visibility and de=
pleted fuel; five of the 13 on board are killed, including a U.S. senator.<=
/li>
<li>October 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_=
Airlines_Trip_4" title=3D"United Airlines Trip 4">United Airlines Trip 4</a=
></b>, a Boeing 247D flying from Salt Lake City, Utah, to Cheyenne, Wyoming=
, United States, crashes near Silver Crown, Wyoming, due to pilot error; al=
l 12 people on board die.</li>
<li>December 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1935_=
SABENA_Savoia-Marchetti_S.73_crash" title=3D"1935 SABENA Savoia-Marchetti S=
.73 crash">A SABENA Savoia-Marchetti S.73 crashes</a></b> near Tatsfield, S=
urrey, England, due to pilot error, while en route from Brussels Airport, B=
elgium, to Croydon Airport in South London; all 11 people on board die in t=
he accident.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1936">1936</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1936">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Am=
erican_Airlines_Flight_1_(1936)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"American Ai=
rlines Flight 1 (1936)">American Airlines Flight 1</a></b>, a Douglas DC-2,=
 crashes into a swamp near Goodwin, Arkansas, killing all 17 passengers and=
 crew on board; the cause is never determined.</li>
<li>April 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_1" title=3D"TWA Flight 1">TWA Flight 1</a></b>, a Douglas DC-2, crashes n=
ear Uniontown, Pennsylvania, United States, due to pilot error, killing 12 =
of the 14 passengers and crew aboard.</li>
<li>June 16 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ha=
v%C3%B8rn_Accident" title=3D"Hav=C3=B8rn Accident">Hav=C3=B8rn Accident</a>=
</b>, a Norwegian Air Lines Junkers Ju 52 crashes into Lihesten mountain in=
 Hyllestad, Norway, killing all seven on board.</li>
<li>August 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicago_=
and_Southern_Flight_4" title=3D"Chicago and Southern Flight 4">Chicago and =
Southern Flight 4</a></b>, a Lockheed Model 10 Electra, crashes after takeo=
ff due to pilot error, killing all eight on board.</li>
<li>December 9 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1936=
_KLM_Croydon_accident" title=3D"1936 KLM Croydon accident">KLM Douglas DC-2=
 crashes</a></b> on takeoff from Croydon Airport, England; 15 of 17 on boar=
d die.</li>
<li>December 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Trip_34" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"United Airlines Trip 34"=
>United Airlines Trip 34</a></b>, a Boeing 247, crashes at Rice Canyon (nea=
r Newhall, California, United States) due to pilot error, killing all 12 on=
 board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We=

37_Airlines_of_Australia_Stinson_crash" title=3D"1937 Airlines of Australia=
 Stinson crash">Airlines of Australia <i>Stinson Model A</i></a></b> suffer=
s controlled flight into terrain in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Queensland" title=3D"Queensland">Queensland</a>, killing four of the seve=
n people on board.</li>
<li>March 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Flig=
ht_15A" title=3D"TWA Flight 15A">TWA Flight 15A</a></b>, a Douglas DC-2 cra=
shes in Clifton, Pennsylvania due to ice accumulation. All 13 passengers an=
d crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 6 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindenb=
urg_disaster" title=3D"Hindenburg disaster">Zeppelin <i>Hindenburg</i> burs=
ts into flames and crashes</a></b> while attempting a landing at Naval Air =
Engineering Station, Lakehurst, New Jersey, United States; of the 97 people=
 on board, 35 are killed; one person on the ground also dies.</li>
<li>November 16 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
937_Sabena_Junkers_Ju_52_Ostend_crash" title=3D"1937 Sabena Junkers Ju 52 O=
stend crash">1937 Sabena Junkers Ju 52 Ostend crash</a></b> kills all 11 on=
 board, including the Grand Duke Georg Donatus and Grand Duchess Cecilie of=
 Hesse.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1938">1938</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1938">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No=
rthwest_Airlines_Flight_2" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 2">Northwest =
Airlines Flight 2</a></b>, a Lockheed L14H Super Electra, crashes near Boze=
man, Montana, United States, killing all 10 on board; the machine with whic=
h the manufacturer measured component vibration is found to be inaccurate, =
causing the aircraft to be more prone to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Aeroelasticity#Flutter" title=3D"Aeroelasticity">flutter</a> than an=
ticipated.</li>
<li>January 11 =E2=80=93 Pan American World Airways Flight 1, a Sikorsky S-=
42 flying boat named the <i><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam=
oan_Clipper" title=3D"Samoan Clipper">Samoan Clipper</a></b></i>, explodes =
over Pago Pago, American Samoa, killing all seven on board.</li>
<li>March 1 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
38_Yosemite_TWA_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1938 Yosemite TWA cra=
sh">1938 Yosemite TWA crash</a></b>, a Douglas DC-2 disappears on a flight =
from San Francisco to Winslow, Arizona; the aircraft is found three months =
later on a mountain in Yosemite National Park; all nine on board died.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 Pan American World Airways Flight 229, a Martin M-130=
 flying boat named the <i><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawai=
i_Clipper" title=3D"Hawaii Clipper">Hawaii Clipper</a></b></i>, disappears =
in the Pacific Ocean westbound from Guam to Manila with six passengers and =
nine crew on board.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template" style=3D"margin-l=
eft:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=

/i>]</sup></li>
<li>October 25 =E2=80=93 <i>Kyeema</i>, an <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/1938_Kyeema_crash" title=3D"1938 Kyeema crash">Australian Natio=
nal Airways Douglas DC-2 crashes</a></b> in heavy fog into Mount Dandenong =
in Victoria, Australia, killing all 18 people on board.</li>
<li>November 4 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1938_Jersey_Airport_disaster" title=3D"1938 Jersey Airport disaster">1938 =
Jersey Airport disaster</a></b>, a Jersey Airways de Havilland DH.86 crashe=
s on takeoff from Jersey Airport due to pilot error; all 13 passengers and =
crew lose their lives as well as one person on the ground.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1939">1939</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1939">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No=
rthwest_Airlines_Flight_1" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 1">Northwest =
Airlines Flight 1</a></b>, a Lockheed L14H Super Electra, crashes on descen=
t to Miles City, Montana, United States, after an intense fire breaks out i=
n the cockpit due to a fuel leak from the aircraft's cross-feed fuel valve;=
 all four on board are killed.</li>
<li>January 21 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/193=
9_Imperial_Airways_flying_boat_ditching" title=3D"1939 Imperial Airways fly=
ing boat ditching">Imperial Airways flying boat ditches</a></b> in the Nort=
h Atlantic, 285 miles (459&nbsp;km) southeast of New York, due to loss of p=
ower; the aircraft later sinks and three of the 12 on board die.</li>
<li>August 13 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1939_=
Pan_Am_Sikorsky_S-43_crash" title=3D"1939 Pan Am Sikorsky S-43 crash">Pan A=
m Sikorsky S-43 crashes</a></b> into Guanabara Bay, Brazil, due to loss of =
control following engine failure, killing 12 of the 14 on board.</li></ul>

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1940">1940</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1940">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>June 14 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Kaleva_(airplane)" title=3D"Kaleva (airplane)">Kaleva shootdown</a></b>, =
an Aero Junkers Ju 52 en route from Tallinn, Estonia, to Helsinki, Finland,=
 is shot down by two Soviet bombers over the Gulf of Finland during peaceti=
me; all nine on board are killed.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Lovettsville_air_disaster" title=3D"Lovettsville air disaster">Lovettsville=
 air disaster</a></b>, Pennsylvania Central Airlines Trip 19, a Douglas DC-=
3A, crashes at Lovettsville, Virginia, United States, during an intense thu=
nderstorm; all 25 on board die.</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1940=
_Deutsche_Lufthansa_Ju_90_crash" title=3D"1940 Deutsche Lufthansa Ju 90 cra=
sh">Deutsche Lufthansa Ju 90 crashes</a></b> near Sch=C3=B6nteichen in Saxo=
ny, Germany, after ice forms on the tail, killing all 29 passengers and cre=
w on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1941">1941</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1941">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
astern_Air_Lines_Flight_21" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 21">Eastern A=
ir Lines Flight 21</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes while descending to lan=
d at Atlanta, Georgia, United States, killing eight of 16 aboard; World War=
 I hero and Eastern Air Lines president <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Eddie_Rickenbacker" title=3D"Eddie Rickenbacker">Eddie Rickenbacker</=
a> is among the survivors.</li>
<li>October 30 =E2=80=93 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_=
Airlines_Flight_1_(1941)" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 1 (1941)"><b>Am=
erican Airlines Flight 1</b></a>, a Douglas DC-3, stalls and crashes at Law=
rence Station, Ontario, Canada while attempting to find a place to land, ki=
lling all 20 on board; the cause of the crash is never determined.</li>
<li>October 30 =E2=80=93 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest=
_Airlines_Flight_5_(1941)" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 5 (1941)"><b>=
Northwest Airlines Flight 5</b></a>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes at Moorhead, M=
innesota in fog due to icing; of the 15 on board, only the pilot survived.<=
/li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1942">1942</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D24" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1942">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TW=
A_Flight_3" title=3D"TWA Flight 3">TWA Flight 3</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 ret=
urning to California crashes into Potosi Mountain 30 miles (48&nbsp;km) sou=
thwest of Las Vegas, Nevada, United States; all 22 aboard die, including ac=
tress <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carole_Lombard" title=3D"Car=
ole Lombard">Carole Lombard</a> and her mother.</li>
<li>January 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1942_Q=
antas_Short_Empire_shootdown" title=3D"1942 Qantas Short Empire shootdown">=
Qantas Short Empire <i>G-AEUH</i> is shot down</a></b> by seven Japanese fi=
ghters and crashes 13 nautical miles (24&nbsp;km) from East Timor; 13 of 18=
 on board die.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1942_KNIL=
M_Douglas_DC-3_shootdown" title=3D"1942 KNILM Douglas DC-3 shootdown">KNILM=
 Douglas DC-3 <i>PK-AFV</i> is shot down</a></b> by three Japanese fighters=
 and crashes 50 miles (80&nbsp;km) north of Broome, Western Australia, kill=
ing four of 12 on board.</li>
<li>October 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Airlines_Flight_28" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 28">American Airli=
nes Flight 28</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes near Palm Springs, Californi=
a, United States, after being struck by a U.S. Army Air Corps Lockheed B-34=
 bomber; all 12 aboard the airliner die, while the bomber lands safely with=
 minor damage.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1943">1943</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D25" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1943">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pa=
n_Am_Flight_1104" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 1104">Pan Am Flight 1104</a></b>, =
a Martin M-130 nicknamed the <i>Philippine Clipper</i>, crashes into a moun=
tain near Boonville, California, United States, due to pilot error; all 19 =
occupants are killed, including Rear Admiral Robert H. English, the serving=
 submarine commander of the US Pacific Fleet.</li>
<li>June 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BOAC_Fligh=
t_777" title=3D"BOAC Flight 777">BOAC Flight 777</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 fl=
ying from Lisbon in Portugal, to Bristol, England, is shot down by Luftwaff=
e fighter aircraft over the Bay of Biscay, killing all 17 people on board, =
including film actor Leslie Howard.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_=
Airlines_Flight_63_(Flagship_Ohio)" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 63 (F=
lagship Ohio)">American Airlines Flight 63</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 nickname=
d the <i>Flagship Ohio</i>, crashes near Trammel, Kentucky, United States, =
after the crew loses control due to severe turbulence and violent downdraft=
s; 20 of the 22 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Airlines_Flight_63_(Flagship_Missouri)" title=3D"American Airlines Fligh=
t 63 (Flagship Missouri)">American Airlines Flight 63</a></b>, a Douglas DC=
-3 nicknamed the <i>Flagship Missouri</i>, crashes near Centerville, Tennes=
see, United States, after ice forms on its wings and propellers; all eight =
passengers and three crew members die.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1944">1944</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D26" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1944">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
merican_Airlines_Flight_2" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 2">American Ai=
rlines Flight 2</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes into the Mississippi River=
 between Arkansas and Tennessee, United States, for reasons unknown, killin=
g all 24 occupants (21 passengers and three crew members).</li>
<li>June 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_277" title=3D"TWA Flight 277">TWA Flight 277</a></b>, a Douglas C-54 Skym=
aster, crashes into Fort Mountain, Maine, United States, in severe weather,=
 killing all seven passengers and crew on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1945">1945</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1945">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 The <i><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/China_Clipper" title=3D"China Clipper">China Clipper</a></b></i>, a Pan=
 Am Martin M-130 flying boat operating an airmail service from Miami, Flori=
da, United States, to Leopoldville in the Belgian Congo, crashes in Port of=
 Spain, Trinidad, killing all 25 people on board.</li>
<li>January 31 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
45_Australian_National_Airways_Stinson_crash" title=3D"1945 Australian Nati=
onal Airways Stinson crash"><i>Tokana</i></a></b>, a Stinson operated by Au=
stralian National Airways, crashes near Tooborac, about 50 miles (80&nbsp;k=
m) north of Melbourne, Victoria, as the result of a fatigue crack in a wing=
 spar; all 10 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_A=
ir_Lines_Flight_45" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 45">Eastern Air Lines=
 Flight 45</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3A, collides with a Douglas A-26 Invader o=
ver Florence, South Carolina, United States; one of the 24 on board the DC-=
3 and two of the three on board the A-26 die.</li>
<li>October 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nationa=
l_Airlines_Flight_16" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 16">National Airlin=
es Flight 16</a></b>, a Lockheed L-18 Lodestar operating a multi-leg domest=
ic flight in Florida, United States, overshoots the runway after landing at=
 the new municipal airport in south Lakeland, killing two of the 15 people =
on board.</li>
<li>November 3 =E2=80=93 The <i><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Honolulu_Clipper" title=3D"Honolulu Clipper">Honolulu Clipper</a></b></i>,=
 Boeing's 314 prototype, makes a forced landing in the Pacific Ocean 650 mi=
les (1,050&nbsp;km) east of Oahu due to double engine failure; all 37 on bo=
ard survive the incident; the aircraft is deliberately sunk when salvage is=
 deemed impractical.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1946">1946</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1946">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pen=
nsylvania_Central_Airlines_Flight_105" title=3D"Pennsylvania Central Airlin=
es Flight 105">Pennsylvania Central Airlines Flight 105</a></b>, a Douglas =
DC-3, crashes in Birmingham, Alabama, United States, killing three of the f=
our crew members; the flight attendant and all 16 passengers survive.</li>
<li>March 10 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1946=
_Australian_National_Airways_DC-3_crash" title=3D"1946 Australian National =
Airways DC-3 crash">1946 Australian National Airways DC-3 crash</a></b> nea=
r Hobart, Tasmania, kills all 25 on board.</li>
<li>July 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_513" title=3D"TWA Flight 513">TWA Flight 513</a></b>, a Lockheed L-049 Co=
nstellation, crashes near Reading, Pennsylvania, United States, after a fir=
e in the baggage compartment; of the six crew on board, only one survives.<=
/li>
<li>August 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_=
European_Airways_Flight_530" title=3D"British European Airways Flight 530">=
British European Airways Flight 530</a></b>, a Douglas C-47, crashes into M=
istberget mountain near Eidsvoll, Norway; killing three of five crew; all 1=
0 passengers survived.</li>
<li>October 3 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1946=
_American_Overseas_Airlines_Douglas_DC-4_crash" title=3D"1946 American Over=
seas Airlines Douglas DC-4 crash">American Overseas Airlines Douglas DC-4 c=
rashes</a></b> into mountainous terrain after takeoff from Stephenville, Ne=
wfoundland, killing all 39 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>November 14 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1946_KLM_Douglas_DC-3_Amsterdam_accident" title=3D"1946 KLM Douglas DC-3 =
Amsterdam accident">1946 KLM Douglas DC-3 Amsterdam accident</a></b>, a Dou=
glas DC-3 crashes while attempting to land at Amsterdam Schiphol Airport in=
 the Netherlands; all 26 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1946_Railway_Air_Services_Dakota_crash" title=3D"1946 Railway Air Service=
s Dakota crash">1946 Railway Air Services Dakota crash</a></b>, a Douglas D=
C-3 crashes shortly after taking off from Northolt Airport, England and com=
es to rest on top of a house. All five occupants survive the crash without =
injury.</li>
<li>December 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_6963" title=3D"TWA Flight 6963">TWA Flight 6963</a></b>, a Lockheed L=
-049 Constellation, crashes near Shannon Airport due to an inaccurate altim=
eter caused by maintenance errors, killing nine of 23 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1947">1947</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1947">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 11 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/1947_BOAC_Douglas_C-47_crash" title=3D"1947 BOAC Douglas C-47 crash">1=
947 BOAC Douglas C-47 crash</a></b>, a BOAC Douglas C-47A crashes into Barl=
ey Hill near Stowting, Kent, United Kingdom, due to fuel starvation, killin=
g eight of the 16 onboard.</li>
<li>January 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Easter=
n_Air_Lines_Flight_665" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 665">Eastern Air =
Lines Flight 665</a></b>, a Douglas C-49, crashes into high ground near Gal=
ax, Virginia, after the pilot became disorientated, 17 people were killed i=
n the crash, only one survived.</li>
<li>January 25 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1947_Croydon_Dakota_accident" title=3D"1947 Croydon Dakota accident">1947 =
Croydon Dakota accident</a></b>, a Spencer Airways Douglas C-47A fails to g=
et airborne at Croydon Airport, United Kingdom, and crashes into a parked =
=C4=8CSA aircraft; 12 of the 22 onboard are killed.</li>
<li>January 26 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1947_KLM_Douglas_DC-3_Copenhagen_accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=
1947 KLM Douglas DC-3 Copenhagen accident">1947 KLM Douglas DC-3 Copenhagen=
 accident</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 crashes shortly after takeoff from Kastru=
p Airport in Denmark, killing all 22 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>February 15 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
47_Avianca_Douglas_DC-4_crash" title=3D"1947 Avianca Douglas DC-4 crash">Av=
ianca Douglas DC-4 crashes</a></b> into Mount El Tabalazo due to pilot erro=
r, killing all 53 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>May 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Air=
lines_Flight_521" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 521">United Airlines Flig=
ht 521</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes on takeoff from LaGuardia Airport, =
New York, United States, due to pilot error; 42 of the 48 onboard die.</li>
<li>May 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Ai=
r_Lines_Flight_605" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 605">Eastern Air Line=
s Flight 605</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, loses control and crashes near Bainbr=
idge, Maryland, United States, killing all 53 passengers and crew on board =
in the deadliest airliner crash in US history at the time.</li>
<li>June 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pennsylva=
nia_Central_Airlines_Flight_410" title=3D"Pennsylvania Central Airlines Fli=
ght 410">Pennsylvania Central Airlines Flight 410</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, =
crashes into Lookout Rock, in the West Virginia Blue Ridge Mountains of the=
 United States en route from Pittsburgh to Washington DC; all 50 passengers=
 and crew are killed.</li>
<li>June 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_Fl=
ight_121" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 121">Pan Am Flight 121</a></b>, a Lockheed=
 L-049 Constellation, crashes in the Syrian desert, en route from Karachi t=
o Istanbul, killing 14 of the 36 onboard.</li>
<li>August 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
947_BSAA_Avro_Lancastrian_Star_Dust_accident" title=3D"1947 BSAA Avro Lanca=
strian Star Dust accident">1947 BSAA <i>Star Dust</i> accident</a></b>, an =
Avro Lancastrian airliner disappears over the Andes after transmitting an e=
nigmatic coded message ("STENDEC"); the fate of the aircraft remains a myst=
ery for more than 50 years until the crash site is finally located in 2000;=
 it is apparent that all 11 people on board died in the accident.</li>
<li>August 28 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Kvitbj%C3%B8rn_disaster" title=3D"Kvitbj=C3=B8rn disaster">Kvitbj=C3=B8rn d=
isaster</a></b>, a Norwegian Air Lines Short Sandringham flying boat strike=
s a mountain near L=C3=B8dingsfjellet, Norway, killing all 35 onboard.</li>
<li>October 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United=
_Airlines_Flight_608" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 608">United Airlines =
Flight 608</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, crashes near Bryce Canyon Airport, Utah=
, United States when a fire caused by a design flaw destroys the aircraft; =
all 52 onboard die in the first hull loss of the DC-6.</li>
<li>October 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_923" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 923">Pan Am Flight 923</a></b>, a Dougl=
as DC-4, crashes into Tamgas Mountain on Annette Island, Alaska, killing al=
l 18 passengers and crew on board; the cause of the accident is never deter=
mined.</li>
<li>December 27 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1947_Korangi_Creek_crash" title=3D"1947 Korangi Creek crash">1947 Korangi=
 Creek crash</a></b>, an Air India Douglas DC-3 crashes shortly after takeo=
ff, killing all 23 onboard.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1948">1948</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D30" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1948">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 28 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/1948_Los_Gatos_DC-3_crash" title=3D"1948 Los Gatos DC-3 crash">1948 Lo=
s Gatos DC-3 crash</a></b>, an Airline Transport Carriers Douglas DC-3 cras=
hes in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diablo_Range" title=3D"=
Diablo Range">Diablo Range</a>, California, after an engine fire; all 32 pa=
ssengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>January 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/BSAA_Star_Tiger_disappearance" title=3D"BSAA Star Tiger disappearance">BSA=
A <i>Star Tiger</i> disappearance</a></b>, an Avro Tudor IV disappears with=
out a trace en route from the Azores to Bermuda with 31 on board; the loss =
of the aircraft remains an unsolved mystery to this day, with the resulting=
 speculation contributing to the Bermuda Triangle legend.</li>
<li>March 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
48_Heathrow_Disaster" title=3D"1948 Heathrow Disaster">1948 Heathrow Disast=
er</a></b>, a Sabena DC-3 crashes at Heathrow Airport in poor visibility du=
e to pilot error, killing 20 of 22 on board.</li>
<li>March 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwes=
t_Airlines_Flight_4422" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 4422">Northwest =
Airlines Flight 4422</a></b>, a Douglas C-54 Skymaster, crashes into Mount =
Sanford in the Alaska Territory, killing 30; although found, the wreckage i=
s initially inaccessible and is not rediscovered until 1999 after being bur=
ied for more than 50 years.</li>
<li>April 5 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
48_Gatow_air_disaster" title=3D"1948 Gatow air disaster">1948 Gatow air dis=
aster</a></b>, a British European Airways Vickers VC.1 Viking crashes near =
RAF Gatow, Berlin, following a collision with a Soviet Air Force Yakovlev Y=
ak-3 fighter; all 14 people on board the Viking are killed, as well as the =
Soviet pilot.</li>
<li>April 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_F=
light_1-10" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 1-10">Pan Am Flight 1-10</a></b>, a Lock=
heed Constellation, crashes while on approach to Shannon Airport, Ireland; =
of the 31 people on board, only one survives.</li>
<li>April 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_=
European_Airways_Flight_S200P" title=3D"British European Airways Flight S20=
0P">British European Airways Flight S200P</a></b>, a Vickers VC.1 Viking, c=
rashes into Irish Law Mountain in Scotland due to pilot error; all on board=
 survive.</li>
<li>June 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ai=
rlines_Flight_624" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 624">United Airlines Fli=
ght 624</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, crashes near Mount Carmel, Pennsylvania, a=
fter failed attempts to extinguish what was believed to have been an onboar=
d fire; all 39 passengers and four crew are killed.</li>
<li>July 4 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1948_N=
orthwood_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1948 Northwood mid-air collision">1948=
 Northwood mid-air collision</a></b>, between a Scandinavian Airlines Syste=
m-operated Douglas DC-6 and an RAF Avro York, kills all 39 passengers and c=
rew on board both aircraft.</li>
<li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <i><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miss_M=
acao" title=3D"Miss Macao">Miss Macao</a></b></i>, a Catalina seaplane en r=
oute from Macau to Hong Kong in southern China, is hijacked over the Pearl =
River delta by a group attempting to rob the passengers; following a strugg=
le in the cockpit, a crash kills all but one of the 26 people on board (the=
 sole survivor is later identified as the lead hijacker); this is the earli=
est known airliner hijacking.</li>
<li>August 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fran=
ce_Flight_072_(1948)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Air France Flight 072 =
(1948)">Air France Flight 072</a></b>, a Lat=C3=A9co=C3=A8re 631, disappear=
s over the Atlantic Ocean with the loss of all 52 people on board. This was=
 the worst aviation accident in the Atlantic Ocean at the time and remains =
the worst ever involving the Lat=C3=A9co=C3=A8re 631.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwe=
st_Airlines_Flight_421" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 421">Northwest A=
irlines Flight 421</a></b>, a Martin 2-0-2, crashes near Winona, Minnesota,=
 due to structural failure of a wing, killing all 37 on board in the worst =
ever accident involving the Martin 2-0-2. This crash is also the first loss=
 of a 2-0-2.</li>
<li>September 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1948_Australian_National_Airways_DC-3_crash" title=3D"1948 Australian Nat=
ional Airways DC-3 crash">1948 <i>Lutana</i> crash</a></b>, Australian Nati=
onal Airways Flight 331, a Douglas DC-3, crashes into high terrain near Nun=
dle, New South Wales, killing all 13 people on board.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Bukken_Bruse_disaster" title=3D"Bukken Bruse disaster">Bukken Bruse disaste=
r</a></b>, a Det Norske Luftfartsselskap Short Sandringham flying boat cras=
hes upon landing in Trondheim, Norway, killing 19 of the 43 people on board=
; <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bertrand_Russell" title=3D"Bertr=
and Russell">Bertrand Russell</a> is among the 24 survivors.</li>
<li>October 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1948_KLM_Constellation_air_disaster" title=3D"1948 KLM Constellation air d=
isaster">1948 KLM Constellation air disaster</a></b>, a Lockheed Constellat=
ion named <i>Nijmegen</i>, flying from Schiphol Airport, Netherlands, to Ne=
w York City, United States, crashes near Prestwick, Scotland, killing all 4=
0 on board.</li>
<li>December 28 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1948_Airborne_Transport_DC-3_(DST)_disappearance" class=3D"mw-redirect" t=
itle=3D"1948 Airborne Transport DC-3 (DST) disappearance">1948 Airborne Tra=
nsport DC-3 (DST) disappearance</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 flying from San Jua=
n, Puerto Rico to Miami, Florida, disappears without a trace off the coast =
of Florida with 32 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1949">1949</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1949">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 17 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/BSAA_Star_Ariel_disappearance" title=3D"BSAA Star Ariel disappearance"=
>BSAA <i>Star Ariel</i> disappearance</a></b>, an Avro Tudor IV disappears =
without a trace en route from Bermuda to Jamaica with 20 on board; the loss=

g speculation contributing to the Bermuda Triangle legend.</li>

 European Airways Douglas Dakota collides</a></b> with a RAF Avro Anson ove=
r Exhall, Warwickshire, killing all 14 on board both aircraft.</li>
<li>March 10 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1949_Q=

es Lockheed Lodestar crash">Queensland Airlines Lockheed Lodestar crashes</=
a></b> on takeoff from Coolangatta airstrip, killing all 21 on board.</li>
<li>May 4 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supe=

b>, an Italian Airlines Fiat G.212 CP carrying the Torino football team cra=
shes into the Superga hills near Turin, killing all 31 on board.</li>
<li>June 7 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/194=
9_Strato-Freight_Curtiss_C-46A_crash" title=3D"1949 Strato-Freight Curtiss =
C-46A crash">1949 Strato-Freight Curtiss C-46A crash</a></b>, a Curtiss Wri=
ght C-46A-50 Modified D, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean shortly after take=

are killed.</li>
<li>July 2 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1949_Mac=
Robertson_Miller_Aviation_DC-3_crash" title=3D"1949 MacRobertson Miller Avi=
ation DC-3 crash">MacRobertson Miller Airlines Douglas DC-3 crashes</a></b>=
 on takeoff from Perth, Western Australia, killing all 18 on board.</li>
<li>July 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_=
Air_Lines_Flight_897R" title=3D"Standard Air Lines Flight 897R">Standard Ai=
r Lines Flight 897R</a></b>, a Curtiss C-46, crashes at Chatsworth, Califor=
nia, due to pilot error, killing 35 of 48 on board.</li>
<li>August 19 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1949_=
Manchester_DC-3_accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1949 Manchester DC=
-3 accident">British European Airways Douglas DC-3 crashes</a></b> into a h=

.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alber=

, a Douglas DC-3, explodes over Cap Tourmente near Sault-au-Cochon, Quebec,=
 due to a bomb planted by Albert Guay; all four crew members and 19 passeng=
ers on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fr=
ance_Flight_009" title=3D"Air France Flight 009">Air France Flight 009</a><=
/b>, a Lockheed Constellation crashes into a mountain on S=C3=A3o Miguel Is=
land, Azores, Portugal, killing all 48 people on board, including boxer <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marcel_Cerdan" title=3D"Marcel Cerdan=
">Marcel Cerdan</a> and violinist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Ginette_Neveu" title=3D"Ginette Neveu">Ginette Neveu</a>.</li>
<li>November 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Easter=
n_Air_Lines_Flight_537" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 537">Eastern Air =
Lines Flight 537</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, on approach to Washington Nationa=
l Airport, suffers a mid-air collision with a Lockheed P-38; all 55 people =
on board the DC-4 die, including Congressman <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/George_J._Bates" title=3D"George J. Bates">George J. Bates</a>, =
<i>New Yorker</i> cartoonist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helen=
_E._Hokinson" title=3D"Helen E. Hokinson">Helen E. Hokinson</a>, and former=
 Congressman <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_J._Kennedy" t=
itle=3D"Michael J. Kennedy">Michael J. Kennedy</a>; the pilot and sole occu=
pant of the P-38 is seriously injured.</li>
<li>November 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Hurum_air_disaster" title=3D"Hurum air disaster">Hurum air disaster</a></=
b>, an Aero Holland Douglas DC-3 crashes near Hurum, Norway, killing 34 of =
the 35 on board, including 25 children.</li>
<li>November 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_157" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 157">American Ai=
rlines Flight 157</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, en route from New York City to M=
exico City with 46 passengers and crew, veers off the runway and strikes bu=
ildings after the flight crew loses control on final approach to Dallas Lov=
e Field; 26 passengers and two flight attendants die.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1950s">1950s</span><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_in=
volving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D32" title=3D"Ed=
it section: 1950s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1950">1950</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D33" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1950">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 5 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/1950_Sverdlovsk_air_disaster" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1950 Sverd=
lovsk air disaster">1950 Sverdlovsk air disaster</a></b>, a Lisunov Li-2 cr=
ashes near Sverdlovsk (now <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yekater=
inburg" title=3D"Yekaterinburg">Yekaterinburg</a>), <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Union" title=3D"Soviet Union">Soviet Union</a>,  k=
illing all 19 on board.</li>
<li>March 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest=
_Orient_Airlines_Flight_307" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 307"=
>Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 307</a></b>, a Martin 2-0-2, crashes near=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minneapolis%E2%80%93Saint_Paul_In=
ternational_Airport" title=3D"Minneapolis=E2=80=93Saint Paul International =
Airport">Minneapolis=E2=80=93Saint Paul International Airport</a>, after hi=
tting a flagpole during approach, killing all 13 on board and two on the gr=
ound.</li>
<li>March 12 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Llan=
dow_air_disaster" title=3D"Llandow air disaster">Llandow air disaster</a></=
b>: An Airflight Avro 689 Tudor V stalls and crashes after the rear cargo h=
old was overloaded, resulting in a center of gravity exceeding the aft limi=
t; 80 out of the 83 people on board die, at the time the worst air disaster=
 in history.</li>
<li><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1950_Air_France_multiple_Do=
uglas_DC-4_accidents" title=3D"1950 Air France multiple Douglas DC-4 accide=
nts">1950 Air France multiple Douglas DC-4 accidents</a></b>:
<ul><li>June 12 =E2=80=93 An Air France Douglas DC-4 (F-BBDE) on a flight f=
rom <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ho_Chi_Minh_City" title=3D"Ho =
Chi Minh City">Saigon</a> to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris=
" title=3D"Paris">Paris</a> crashes in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Arabian_Sea" title=3D"Arabian Sea">Arabian Sea</a> while on approa=
ch to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahrain_International_Airpor=
t" title=3D"Bahrain International Airport">Bahrain Airport</a>, killing 46 =
of 52 on board.</li>
<li>June 14 =E2=80=93 An Air France Douglas DC-4, F-BBDM, crashes in the Ar=
abian Sea while on approach to Bahrain Airport, killing 40 of 53 on board. =
This aircraft was operating on the same flight route as F-BBDE.</li></ul></=
li>
<li>June 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest=
_Orient_Airlines_Flight_2501" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 250=
1">Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 2501</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, with 58 p=
eople on board, disappears without a trace over <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Lake_Michigan" title=3D"Lake Michigan">Lake Michigan</a>.</li=
>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1950_Aust=
ralian_National_Airways_Douglas_DC-4_crash" title=3D"1950 Australian Nation=
al Airways Douglas DC-4 crash">Australian National Airways <i>Amana</i></a>=
</b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes after takeoff from <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Perth_Airport" title=3D"Perth Airport">Perth Airport</a>, ki=
lling all 29 people on board.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fli=
ght_903" title=3D"TWA Flight 903">TWA Flight 903</a></b>, a Lockheed L-749A=
 Constellation, crashes because of an engine fire, in the desert about 65 m=
iles (105&nbsp;km) NNW of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cairo" t=
itle=3D"Cairo">Cairo</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_=
of_Egypt" title=3D"Kingdom of Egypt">Egypt</a>; all 55 on board are killed =
in the worst ever accident involving the Lockheed L-749.</li>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1950=
_Heathrow_BEA_Viking_accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1950 Heathrow=
 BEA Viking accident">British European Airways Vickers VC.1 Viking crashes<=
/a></b> on the runway at London Heathrow Airport in foggy weather; of the 3=
0 on board, only a stewardess and a passenger survive.</li>
<li>November 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_In=
dia_Flight_245" title=3D"Air India Flight 245">Air India Flight 245</a></b>=
, a Lockheed L-749A Constellation, crashes into <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Mont_Blanc" title=3D"Mont Blanc">Mont Blanc</a> in France; al=
l 40 passengers and eight crew are killed. Sixteen years later, <b><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India_Flight_101" title=3D"Air India =
Flight 101">Air India Flight 101</a></b> crashes in almost exactly the same=
 spot.</li>
<li>November 13 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1950_T%C3%AAte_de_l%27Obiou_C-54_crash" title=3D"1950 T=C3=AAte de l'Obio=
u C-54 crash">1950 T=C3=AAte de l'Obiou C-54 crash</a></b>, a Douglas C-54 =
Skymaster operated by Curtiss Reid Flying Services crashes 30 miles (48&nbs=
p;km) from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grenoble" title=3D"Gren=
oble">Grenoble</a>, France, on the T=C3=AAte de l'Obiou mountain; all 52 pa=
ssengers and crew die.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1951">1951</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1951">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Na=
tional_Airlines_Flight_83" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 83">National A=
irlines Flight 83</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes on landing at <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philadelphia_International_Airport" title=3D=
"Philadelphia International Airport">Philadelphia International Airport</a>=
, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pennsylvania" title=3D"Pennsylva=
nia">Pennsylvania</a>. Seven of the 28 passengers and crew are killed, one =
of them being heroine flight attendant <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Frankie_Housley" title=3D"Frankie Housley">Frankie Housley</a> who die=
d trying to save more passengers.</li>
<li>March 27 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
951_Ringway_Dakota_crash" title=3D"1951 Ringway Dakota crash">1951 Ringway =
Dakota crash</a></b>, an Air Transport Charter Douglas DC-3 crashes shortly=
 after taking off from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester_=
Airport" title=3D"Manchester Airport">Manchester-Ringway Airport</a>, <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England" title=3D"England">England</a>.=
 Two of the three crew members are killed.</li>
<li>April 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cubana_d=
e_Aviaci%C3%B3n_Flight_493" title=3D"Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 493">Cu=
bana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 493</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4 en route from <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami" title=3D"Miami">Miami</a> to <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Havana" title=3D"Havana">Havana</a>,=
 collides in mid-air with a United States Navy Beech SNB-1 Kansan off <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_West" title=3D"Key West">Key West</=
a>; all 43 aboard both aircraft are killed.</li>
<li>June 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_Fl=
ight_151" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 151">Pan Am Flight 151</a></b>, a Lockheed=
 L-049 Constellation en route from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Accra" title=3D"Accra">Accra</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Gold_Coast_(British_colony)" title=3D"Gold Coast (British colony)">Ghana</=
a> to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monrovia" title=3D"Monrovia"=
>Monrovia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liberia" title=3D"L=
iberia">Liberia</a>, crashes into a hill near <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Sanoyie" title=3D"Sanoyie">Sanoye</a> in <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Bong_County" title=3D"Bong County">Bong County</a>, Libe=
ria, 54 miles (86&nbsp;km) from the airport; all 31 passengers and six crew=
 members die.</li>
<li>June 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ai=
rlines_Flight_610" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 610">United Airlines Fli=
ght 610</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, flies into a mountain in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larimer_County,_Colorado" title=3D"Larimer County, =
Colorado">Larimer County</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colo=
rado" title=3D"Colorado">Colorado</a>, due to a navigational error; all 45 =
passengers and five crew members are killed.</li>
<li>July 21 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1951_Ca=
nadian_Pacific_Air_Lines_Douglas_DC-4_disappearance" class=3D"mw-redirect" =
title=3D"1951 Canadian Pacific Air Lines Douglas DC-4 disappearance">Canadi=
an Pacific Air Lines Douglas DC-4 disappears</a></b> on a flight from <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vancouver" title=3D"Vancouver">Vancouve=
r</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Columbia" title=3D"=
British Columbia">British Columbia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Canada" title=3D"Canada">Canada</a>, to <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Tokyo" title=3D"Tokyo">Tokyo</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Japan" title=3D"Japan">Japan</a>; all 37 on board are presumed =
dead; the aircraft has never been found.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_=
Airlines_Flight_615" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 615">United Airlines F=
light 615</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6B, crashes near <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Decoto,_California" title=3D"Decoto, California">Decoto</a> =
(now <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Union_City,_California" title=

.org/wiki/California" title=3D"California">California</a>), while on final =
approach to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oakland,_California" t=
itle=3D"Oakland, California">Oakland</a>, California; all 44 passengers and=
 six crew members die.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/195=
1_LOT_Li-2_Tuszyn_air_disaster" title=3D"1951 LOT Li-2 Tuszyn air disaster"=
>LOT Polish Airlines Lisunov Li-2 crashes</a></b> near <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuszyn" title=3D"Tuszyn">Tuszyn</a> shortly after take=
off due to engine failure, killing all 16 passengers and crew on board.</li=
>
<li>December 16 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/195=

 Airlines Curtiss C-46 Commando crashes</a></b> at <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth,_New_Jersey" title=3D"Elizabeth, New Jersey">Eli=
zabeth</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Jersey" title=3D"N=
ew Jersey">New Jersey</a>, after a loss of control following an engine fire=
, killing all 56 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/195=
1_Misrair_SNCASE_Languedoc_crash" title=3D"1951 Misrair SNCASE Languedoc cr=
ash">Misrair SNCASE Languedoc crashes</a></b> west of <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehran" title=3D"Tehran">Tehran</a>, killing all 20 peo=
ple on board.</li>
<li>December 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conti=
nental_Charters_Flight_44-2" title=3D"Continental Charters Flight 44-2">Con=
tinental Charters Flight 44-2</a></b>, a Curtiss-Wright C-46, crashes into =
a ridge near <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Napoli,_New_York" tit=
le=3D"Napoli, New York">Napoli</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/New_York_(state)" title=3D"New York (state)">New York</a>, while en route=
 to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buffalo,_New_York" title=3D"Bu=
ffalo, New York">Buffalo</a>, New York; three crew members and 23 passenger=
s die.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1952">1952</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D35" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1952">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Am=
erican_Airlines_Flight_6780" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 6780">Americ=
an Airlines Flight 6780</a></b>, a Convair CV-240, crashes on approach to <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newark,_New_Jersey" title=3D"Newark=
, New Jersey">Newark, New Jersey</a>, into dwellings in Elizabeth, New Jers=
ey, killing 30 and leading to the Doolittle Commission recommendation for l=
aws coordinating urban zoning to keep airport approach paths clear.</li>
<li>February 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natio=
nal_Airlines_Flight_101" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 101">National Ai=
rlines Flight 101</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6 crashes into an apartment buildin=
g in Elizabeth, New Jersey, two minutes after departing <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newark_Liberty_International_Airport" title=3D"Newark=
 Liberty International Airport">Newark Airport</a>, killing 33 people (incl=
uding four residents of the building).</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1952_A=
ir_France_SNCASE_Languedoc_crash" title=3D"1952 Air France SNCASE Languedoc=
 crash">Air France SNCASE Languedoc crashes</a></b> on takeoff from <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nice" title=3D"Nice">Nice</a>, <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France" title=3D"France">France</a>, due to =
jammed controls. All 38 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_F=
light_526A" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 526A">Pan Am Flight 526A</a></b>, a Doug=
las DC-4, suffers engine failure and is forced to ditch in the Atlantic 11 =
miles (18&nbsp;km) north of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Ju=
an,_Puerto_Rico" title=3D"San Juan, Puerto Rico">San Juan</a>, <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puerto_Rico" title=3D"Puerto Rico">Puerto Rico=
</a>; 52 of 69 on board die.</li>
<li>April 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_F=
light_202" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 202">Pan Am Flight 202</a></b>, a Boeing =
377 Stratocruiser, crashes after a propeller failure in a remote area of <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil" title=3D"Brazil">Brazil</a> =
on its way from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buenos_Aires" titl=
e=3D"Buenos Aires">Buenos Aires</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Argentina" title=3D"Argentina">Argentina</a>, to <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_City" title=3D"New York City">New York City</a> =
via <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rio_de_Janeiro" title=3D"Rio d=
e Janeiro">Rio de Janeiro</a>; all 50 on board are killed in the deadliest =
accident involving the Boeing 377.</li>
<li>June 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_=
Airlines_Flight_910" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 910">American Airlin=
es Flight 910</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6 carrying 55 passengers and five crew =
collides with a Temco Swift private plane on final approach to <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dallas_Love_Field" title=3D"Dallas Love Field"=
>Dallas Love Field</a>, killing both occupants of the Swift; the DC-6 lands=
 safely with no injuries to the passengers or crew.</li>
<li>August 12 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1952_=
Transportes_A%C3%A9reos_Nacional_Douglas_C-47_mid-air_fire" title=3D"1952 T=
ransportes A=C3=A9reos Nacional Douglas C-47 mid-air fire">Transportes A=C3=
=A9reos Nacional Douglas C-47A explodes in mid-air</a></b> on a domestic fl=
ight in Brazil; all 24 on board die.</li>
<li>December 6 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1952=
_Bermuda_air_crash" title=3D"1952 Bermuda air crash">Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3=
n Douglas DC-4 crashes</a></b> into the Atlantic Ocean off <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bermuda" title=3D"Bermuda">Bermuda</a> after faili=
ng to gain altitude after takeoff, killing 37 of 41 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1953">1953</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D36" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1953">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 5 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/1953_Nutts_Corner_Viking_accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1953 =
Nutts Corner Viking accident">1953 Nutts Corner Viking accident</a></b>, a =
British European Airways Vickers Viking crashes on approach to Belfast-Nutt=
s Corner Airport, killing 27 of the 31 on board.</li>
<li>February 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1953_Skyways_Avro_York_disappearance" title=3D"1953 Skyways Avro York disa=
ppearance">1953 Skyways Avro York disappearance</a></b>, a plane with 39 on=
 board disappears over the North Atlantic.</li>
<li>February 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natio=
nal_Airlines_Flight_470_(1953)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"National Air=
lines Flight 470 (1953)">National Airlines Flight 470</a></b>, a Douglas DC=
-6 en route from Tampa, Florida to New Orleans, Louisiana crashes into the =
Gulf of Mexico after encountering severe turbulence. All 46 passengers and =
crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BOAC_Flight=
_783" title=3D"BOAC Flight 783">BOAC Flight 783</a></b>, a de Havilland Com=
et, breaks up in mid-air and crashes near Calcutta, India after flying into=
 a thunderstorm; all 43 on board die.</li>
<li>July 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transocea=
n_Air_Lines_Flight_512" title=3D"Transocean Air Lines Flight 512">Transocea=
n Air Lines Flight 512</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6A, crashes in the Pacific Oce=
an while en route from Wake Island to Honolulu, Hawaii. All 58 passengers a=
nd crew are killed.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fran=
ce_Flight_152" title=3D"Air France Flight 152">Air France Flight 152</a></b=
>, a Lockheed L-749A Constellation ditches into the Mediterranean Sea while=
 en route from Rome to Beirut after an engine separated. Four elderly passe=
ngers drowned.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_F=
rance_Flight_178" title=3D"Air France Flight 178">Air France Flight 178</a>=
</b>, a Lockheed Constellation, crashes into a mountain in southern France;=
 all 42 on board are killed.</li>
<li>September 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amer=
ican_Airlines_Flight_723" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 723">American A=
irlines Flight 723</a></b>, a Convair 240, crashes while on approach to Alb=
any Airport; all 28 passengers and crew die.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BCPA_F=
light_304" title=3D"BCPA Flight 304">BCPA Flight 304</a></b>, a Douglas DC-=
6B, crashes into King's Mountain, southeast of Half Moon Bay, California, o=
n its approach to San Francisco International Airport, killing all 11 on bo=
ard.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1954">1954</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D37" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1954">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BO=
AC_Flight_781" title=3D"BOAC Flight 781">BOAC Flight 781</a></b>, a de Havi=
lland Comet flying from Rome to London on the last leg of a flight from Sin=
gapore, disintegrates in mid-air, when metal fatigue from repeated pressuri=
zation cycles compromises the fuselage, killing the 29 passengers and six c=
rew.</li>
<li>March 13 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1954_B=
OAC_Lockheed_Constellation_crash" title=3D"1954 BOAC Lockheed Constellation=
 crash">BOAC Lockheed L-749A Constellation</a></b> crashes as it attempts t=
o land at Kallang Airport, Singapore; of the 40 passengers and crew on boar=
d, 33 are killed.</li>
<li>April 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Afr=
ican_Airways_Flight_201" title=3D"South African Airways Flight 201">South A=
frican Airways Flight 201</a></b>, a de Havilland Comet flying from Rome to=
 Cairo bound for Johannesburg, disintegrates in mid-air, killing all 14 pas=
sengers and seven crew; as in BOAC Flight 781, the cause is metal fatigue a=
t stress risers at the corners of the square windows in the aluminium skin.=
</li>
<li>June 19 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
54_Swissair_Convair_CV-240_crash" title=3D"1954 Swissair Convair CV-240 cra=
sh">1954 Swissair Convair CV-240 crash</a></b>, a Convair CV-240 ditches in=
to the English Channel after running out of fuel. All survive the ditching,=
 but three of the passengers drown due to a lack of lifejackets.</li>
<li>July 23 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1954_=
Cathay_Pacific_Douglas_DC-4_shootdown" title=3D"1954 Cathay Pacific Douglas=
 DC-4 shootdown">1954 Cathay Pacific Douglas DC-4 shootdown</a></b>: a Cath=
ay Pacific Douglas DC-4 is attacked by two PLAAF La-7 fighters and crashes =
off Hainan Island, killing 10 of 19 on board.</li>
<li>August 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_Fli=
ght_608" title=3D"KLM Flight 608">KLM Flight 608</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, c=
rashes into the North Sea for reasons unknown, killing all 12 passengers an=
d nine crew members on board.</li>
<li>September 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_F=
light_633" title=3D"KLM Flight 633">KLM Flight 633</a></b>, a Lockheed L-10=
49 Super Constellation, ditches after takeoff from Shannon Airport in Irela=
nd, killing 28 of 56 on board.</li>
<li>December 25 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1954_Prestwick_air_disaster" title=3D"1954 Prestwick air disaster">1954 P=
restwick air disaster</a></b> a British Overseas Airways Corporation Boeing=
 377 Stratocruiser crashes on landing at Prestwick Airport, Scotland, killi=
ng 28 of the 36 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1955">1955</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
