 section: 1955">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
55_Cincinnati_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1955 Cincinnati mid-air collision=
">TWA Flight 694</a></b>, a Martin 2-0-2, collides with a privately owned D=
ouglas DC-3 over Cincinnati, Ohio, killing all 15 on board both aircraft.</=
li>
<li>February 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_260" title=3D"TWA Flight 260">TWA Flight 260</a></b>, a Martin 4-0-4,=
 crashes into the Sandia Mountains near Albuquerque, New Mexico, killing al=
l 16 on board.</li>
<li>March 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American=
_Airlines_Flight_711" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 711">American Airli=
nes Flight 711</a></b>, a Convair CV-240 crashes into a field on approach i=
nto Springfield-Branson Regional Airport, Missouri. 13 of the 35 passengers=
 and crew are killed.</li>
<li>March 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_F=
light_845/26" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 845/26">Pan Am Flight 845/26</a></b>, =
a Boeing 377 Stratocruiser, ditches into the Pacific Ocean off the Oregon c=
oast, killing four of the 23 on board.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1955_Ma=
cArthur_Airport_United_Airlines_crash" title=3D"1955 MacArthur Airport Unit=
ed Airlines crash">United Airlines Douglas DC-6 crashes</a></b> after takeo=
ff from Long Island MacArthur Airport, New York, killing all three on board=
.</li>
<li>April 11 =E2=80=93 An Air India Lockheed L-749 Constellation named <i><=
b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmir_Princess" title=3D"Kashm=
ir Princess">Kashmir Princess</a></b></i> explodes under suspicious circums=
tances; 16 people are killed and three survive.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Al_Fli=
ght_402" title=3D"El Al Flight 402">El Al Flight 402</a></b>, a Lockheed L-=
049 Constellation, inadvertently strays over Bulgarian territory on its way=
 from Vienna to Tel Aviv, and is shot down by two Bulgarian fighter aircraf=
t, killing all 58 on board.</li>
<li>October 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_=
Airlines_Flight_409" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 409">United Airlines F=
light 409</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes into Medicine Bow Peak near Cent=
ennial, Wyoming, killing all 66 on board.</li>
<li>November 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United=
_Airlines_Flight_629" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 629">United Airlines =
Flight 629</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6B, is bombed by Jack Gilbert Graham over =
Longmont, Colorado; all 44 on board are killed.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1956">1956</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1956">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 18 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/1956_Scottish_Airlines_Malta_air_disaster" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"1956 Scottish Airlines Malta air disaster">1956 Scottish Airlines Malta=
 air disaster</a></b>: a Scottish Airlines Avro York crashes near =C5=BBurr=
ieq, Malta due to pilot error, killing all 50 on board.</li>
<li>April 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_400" title=3D"TWA Flight 400">TWA Flight 400</a></b>, a Martin 4-0-4, cra=
shes on takeoff at Greater Pittsburgh International Airport, killing 22 of =
the 36 on board; 14 survive.</li>
<li>April 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest=
_Orient_Airlines_Flight_2" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 2">Nor=
thwest Orient Airlines Flight 2</a></b>, a Boeing 377 Stratocruiser, ditche=
s into Puget Sound after takeoff from Seattle=E2=80=93Tacoma International =
Airport after the cowl flaps are incorrectly set for takeoff; four passenge=
rs and a flight attendant die.</li>
<li>June 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linea_Aer=
opostal_Venezolana_Flight_253_(June_1956)" title=3D"Linea Aeropostal Venezo=
lana Flight 253 (June 1956)">Linea Aeropostal Flight 253</a></b>, a Lockhee=
d L-1049 Constellation, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean off Asbury Park, Ne=
w Jersey. All 74 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 24 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
56_BOAC_Argonaut_accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1956 BOAC Argonau=
t accident">1956 BOAC Argonaut accident</a></b>, a Canadair C-4 Argonaut cr=
ashes shortly after taking off from Kano Airport, Nigeria, into a thunderst=
orm, killing 32 of the 38 passengers and three of the seven crew.</li>
<li>June 30 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1956_=
Grand_Canyon_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1956 Grand Canyon mid-air collisio=
n">1956 Grand Canyon mid-air collision</a></b> between United Airlines Flig=
ht 718, a DC-7 and TWA Flight 2, a Lockheed Constellation, over the Grand C=
anyon, kills all 128 aboard both aircraft; operating under Visual Flight Ru=
les, the planes fail to see each other and collide; the Federal Aviation Ad=
ministration is created in the aftermath.</li>
<li>July 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans-Cana=
da_Air_Lines_Flight_304" title=3D"Trans-Canada Air Lines Flight 304">Trans-=
Canada Air Lines Flight 304</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, sheds a propeller =
blade over Flat Rock, Michigan; the blade penetrates the passenger cabin, k=
illing one of 35 aboard; this is the first known case of a turboprop sheddi=
ng a blade in passenger service.</li>
<li>October 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_6" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 6">Pan Am Flight 6</a></b>, a Boeing 377 =
Stratocruiser, is forced to ditch in the Pacific Ocean between Hawai'i and =
San Francisco; all 31 on board are rescued by a nearby United States Coast =
Guard ship.</li>
<li>November 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braath=
ens_SAFE_Flight_253" title=3D"Braathens SAFE Flight 253">Braathens SAFE Fli=
ght 253</a></b>, a de Havilland Heron, crashes into Hummelfjell mountain ne=
ar Tolga, Norway, killing two of 12 on board.</li>
<li>November 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linea=
_Aeropostal_Venezolana_Flight_253_(November_1956)" title=3D"Linea Aeroposta=
l Venezolana Flight 253 (November 1956)">Linea Aeropostal Flight 253</a></b=
>, a Lockheed L-749 Constellation, crashes while on approach to Caracas Int=
ernational Airport, killing all 25 on board.</li>
<li>December 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans-=
Canada_Air_Lines_Flight_810" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Trans-Canada Ai=
r Lines Flight 810">Trans-Canada Air Lines Flight 810</a></b>, a Canadair N=
orth Star, crashes near Hope, British Columbia, Canada, killing all 62 peop=
le on board; the wreckage is located several months later. Aboard are four =
members of the Canadian Football League Saskatchewan Roughriders, and forme=
r Iowa Hawkeye Outland Trophy winner Cal Jones.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1957">1957</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

<ul><li>February 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No=

ast Airlines Flight 823</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, crashes during a snowstorm=
 shortly after takeoff from LaGuardia Airport; 20 of the 101 occupants die.=
</li>

British European Airways Flight 411</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes wh=
ile on approach to Manchester Airport, killing all 20 on board and two on t=
he ground.</li>
<li>May 1 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1957=
_Blackbushe_Viking_accident" title=3D"1957 Blackbushe Viking accident">1957=
 Blackbushe Viking accident</a></b>, an Eagle Aviation Vickers VC.1 Viking =
crashes after engine failure at Blackbushe Airport; of the 35 on board, onl=
y a passenger survives.</li>
<li>July 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_Fligh=

nstellation, crashes after takeoff from Biak-Mokmer Airport, Indonesia, kil=

<li>August 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maritim=

>Maritime Central Airways Flight 315</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes near =

ll 79 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_7" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 7">Pan Am Flight 7</a></b>, a Boeing 377 =
Stratocruiser, disappears between San Francisco and Honolulu; small pieces =
of wreckage and human remains are found almost a week later by the United S=
tates Navy; all 44 on board are believed to have been killed.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1957_Aquila_Airways_Solent_crash" title=3D"1957 Aquila Airways Solent cra=
sh">1957 Aquila Airways Solent crash</a></b>, a flying boat crashes near Ch=
essell, Isle of Wight, UK, due to engine failure, killing 45 out of the 58 =
on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1958">1958</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1958">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=

<ul><li>February 6 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=

</a></b>, a British European Airways Airspeed Ambassador operating as Fligh=
t 609 crashes while attempting a take off in a snowstorm from Munich-Riem A=
irport, killing 23 of 44 passenger and crew members on board including eigh=
t Manchester United footballers.</li>

air disaster</a></b>, a Silver City Airways Bristol 170 Freighter traveling=
 from the Isle of Man to Manchester Ringway Airport crashes into Winter Hil=
l, Lancashire, killing 35 people and injuring seven.</li>

ight 67</a></b>, a Vickers 745D Viscount, crashes at Tri-City Airport (now =
MBS International Airport) near Freeland, Michigan, killing all 47 passenge=
rs and crew; an undiscovered ice buildup on the wing and windy conditions a=
re possible causes.</li>

ight 736</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7, collides near Las Vegas, Nevada, with a U=

the airliner and both F-100 crew members are killed.</li>
<li>May 20 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_Airlines_F=

0</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, and an USAF T-33 jet trainer collide in mida=
ir and crash. Of the 13 people on both aircraft only 1 pilot of the jet sur=
vives.</li>

n-Air_Avro_York_crash" title=3D"1958 Dan-Air Avro York crash">Avro York 685=
 cargo aircraft crashes</a></b> during a forced landing after an engine cat=
ches fire en route from Karachi to Delhi, killing four of the five people o=
n board.</li>
<li>August 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_=

ntral African Airways Flight 890</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes due t=
o pilot error near Benina International Airport, Libya.  Of the 54 on board=
, 36 are killed.</li>
<li>August 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_Fli=
ght_607-E" title=3D"KLM Flight 607-E">KLM Flight 607-E</a></b>, a Lockheed =
L-1049 Super Constellation (named <i>Hugo de Groot</i>) en route from Amste=
rdam to New York, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean shortly after takeoff fro=
m Shannon Airport in Ireland, killing all 99 passengers and crew, including=
 six members of the Egyptian fencing team.</li>
<li>August 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=

ht 4</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes after stalling in an updraft, killi=
ng all 64 people on board.</li>
<li>August 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northea=
st_Airlines_Flight_258" title=3D"Northeast Airlines Flight 258">Northeast A=
irlines Flight 258</a></b>, a Convair 240, crashes near Nantucket Internati=
onal Airport due to pilot error, killing 25 of 34 on board.</li>
<li>September 2 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=

dent">Independent Air Travel Vickers VC.1 Viking crashes</a></b> near South=
all, Middlesex, killing all three crew on board and another four people on =
the ground.</li>

roflot =D0=A2u-104 Kanash crash">Aeroflot Tupolev Tu-104 crashes</a></b> ne=

h_European_Airways_Flight_142" title=3D"British European Airways Flight 142=

 with an Italian Air Force North American F-86 Sabre over Italy, all 31 on =
board die.</li>

h">Aviaco SNCASE Languedoc crashes</a></b> in the Guadarrama Mountains, kil=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1959">1959</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1959">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sou=
theast_Airlines_Flight_308" title=3D"Southeast Airlines Flight 308">Southea=
st Airlines Flight 308</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3A, crashes into the Holston M=
ountain range, Tennessee, on approach to the Tri-Cities Regional Airport, k=
illing all 10 people on board.</li>
<li>January 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luftha=
nsa_Flight_502" title=3D"Lufthansa Flight 502">Lufthansa Flight 502</a></b>=
, a Lockheed L-1049 Super Constellation, crashes on approach to Rio de Jane=
iro=E2=80=93Gale=C3=A3o International Airport, Brazil, 36 of the 39 on boar=
d are killed.</li>
<li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austra=
l_L%C3%ADneas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_205" title=3D"Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9r=
eas Flight 205">Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 205</a></b>, a Curti=
ss C-46 Commando, crashes after a missed approach to Mar Del Plata Airport =
in Argentina, killing 51 of the 52 people on board.</li>
<li>February 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Airlines_Flight_320" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 320">American Air=
lines Flight 320</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Super Electra, crashes into the =
East River, New York City, as a result of pilot error; 65 passengers and cr=
ew are killed.</li>
<li>February 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_115" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 115">Pan Am Flight 115</a></b>, a Boein=
g 707 with 119 people on board experiences an unplanned emergency descent f=
rom 35,000&nbsp;ft to 6,000&nbsp;ft. The crew manage to regain control and =
make an emergency landing in Gander, Canada.</li>
<li>February 17 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1959_Turkish_Airlines_Gatwick_crash" title=3D"1959 Turkish Airlines Gatwi=
ck crash">1959 Turkish Airlines Gatwick crash</a></b>, a chartered Vickers =
Viscount 793 carrying the Turkish prime minister and other government offic=
ials crashes in heavy fog during its final approach into London Gatwick Air=
port; five of the eight crew and nine of the 16 passengers die in the accid=
ent; Prime Minister <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adnan_Menderes=
" title=3D"Adnan Menderes">Adnan Menderes</a> is among the 10 survivors.</l=
i>
<li>April 23 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
959_Air_Charter_Turkey_crash" title=3D"1959 Air Charter Turkey crash">1959 =
Air Charter Turkey crash</a></b>, an Avro Super Trader IV crashes on Mount =
S=C3=BCphan, Turkey; all 12 crew on board die.</li>
<li>May 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_Ai=
rlines_Flight_75" title=3D"Capital Airlines Flight 75">Capital Airlines Fli=
ght 75</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount 745D flying from New York City to Atlant=
a, breaks up in flight over Chase, Maryland, due to loss of control in seve=
re turbulence; all 31 on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_891" title=3D"TWA Flight 891">TWA Flight 891</a></b>, a Lockheed Starline=
r, is struck by lightning shortly after takeoff from Milan Malpensa Airport=
 and crashes near Marnate; all 68 passengers and crew on board are killed.<=
/li>
<li>August 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/America=
n_Airlines_Flight_514" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 514">American Airl=
ines Flight 514</a></b>, a Boeing 707 crashes near Calverton-Peconic River =
Airport, New York after a loss of control. All five crew members are killed=
 in the first crash involving a Boeing 707.</li>
<li>August 19 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1959_=
Transair_Douglas_Dakota_accident" title=3D"1959 Transair Douglas Dakota acc=
ident">Transair Douglas Dakota crashes</a></b> into a mountain in Spain, ki=
lling all 32 on board.</li>
<li>September 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAI_=
Flight_307" title=3D"TAI Flight 307">TAI Flight 307</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7=
, crashes into a pine forest on departure from M=C3=A9rignac Airport, Franc=
e; 54 of the 65 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>September 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bran=
iff_Flight_542" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Braniff Flight 542">Braniff =
Flight 542</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Electra, breaks up in mid-air and cras=
hes 4 miles (6.4&nbsp;km) from Buffalo, Texas; all 34 on board die.</li>
<li>October 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piedmo=
nt_Airlines_Flight_349" title=3D"Piedmont Airlines Flight 349">Piedmont Air=
lines Flight 349</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes on Bucks Elbow Mountain n=
ear Charlottesville, Virginia, killing the crew of three and 23 of 24 passe=
ngers; the sole survivor is seriously injured; the cause is a navigational =
error during an Instrument Landing System approach.</li>
<li>November 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natio=
nal_Airlines_Flight_967" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 967">National Ai=
rlines Flight 967</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7B, explodes in mid-air and crashes=
 into the Gulf of Mexico while on a flight from Tampa, Florida, to New Orle=
ans, Louisiana; all 40 on board die.</li>
<li>November 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_315_(1959)" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 315 (1959)">Aeroflot Flight=
 315</a></b>, an Antonov An-10, enters a nosedive and crashes on approach t=
o Lviv Airport due to tail icing, killing all 40 on board.</li>
<li>November 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arian=
a_Afghan_Airlines_Flight_202" title=3D"Ariana Afghan Airlines Flight 202">A=
riana Afghan Airlines Flight 202</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4, crashes into a hi=
llside near Beirut shortly after takeoff, killing 24 of 27 on board.</li>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allegh=
eny_Airlines_Flight_371" title=3D"Allegheny Airlines Flight 371">Allegheny =
Airlines Flight 371</a></b>, a Martin 2-0-2 crashes on approach into Willia=
msport Regional Airport, Pennsylvania. Only one passenger survives out of t=
he 26 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>December 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_120" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 120">Aeroflot Flight 120</a></b>, =
an Ilyushin Il-14, crashes in the Baysuntau mountain range, Uzbekistan, aft=
er the pilot deviates from the flight route; all 30 on board die.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1960s">1960s</span><span class=3D"mw-=

it section: 1960s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1960">1960</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D44" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1960">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nat=
ional_Airlines_Flight_2511" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 2511">Nationa=
l Airlines Flight 2511</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6B bound from New York to Miam=
i, crashes near Bolivia, North Carolina, when a bomb planted on board explo=
des in mid-air; all 34 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>January 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capita=
l_Airlines_Flight_20" title=3D"Capital Airlines Flight 20">Capital Airlines=
 Flight 20</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, en route from Washington National A=
irport to Norfolk International Airport crashes near Holdcroft, Virginia du=
e to engine failure caused by icy conditions; all 50 on board are killed.</=
li>
<li>January 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scandi=
navian_Airlines_System_Flight_871" title=3D"Scandinavian Airlines System Fl=
ight 871">Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 871</a></b>, a Sud Aviation C=
aravelle, crashes while on approach to Esenbo=C4=9Fa Airport, Ankara, Turke=
y, killing all 42 on board; an undetermined descent was to blame for the fi=
rst fatal crash of the Sud Caravelle.</li>
<li>January 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avianc=
a_Flight_671" title=3D"Avianca Flight 671">Avianca Flight 671</a></b>, a Lo=
ckheed Constellation, crashes on landing at Sangster International Airport,=
 Jamaica, killing two of the seven crew and 35 of 39 passengers on board in=
 Jamaica's worst aviation accident.</li>
<li>February 25 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
960_Rio_de_Janeiro_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1960 Rio de Janeiro mid-air =
collision">1960 Rio de Janeiro mid-air collision</a></b>: A United States N=
avy Douglas R6D-1 (DC-6A) collides with Real Transportes A=C3=A9reos Flight=
 753, a Douglas DC-3, over Rio de Janeiro, Brazil; of the 38 occupants of t=
he American aircraft, three survive, and all 26 passengers and crew of the =
Brazilian aircraft are killed.</li>
<li>February 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_315_(1960)" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 315 (1960)">Aeroflot Flight=
 315</a></b>, an Antonov An-10A, crashes short of the runway at Lviv Airpor=
t due to tail icing; of the 33 on board, only a passenger survives.</li>
<li>February 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alita=
lia_Flight_618" title=3D"Alitalia Flight 618">Alitalia Flight 618</a></b>, =
a Douglas DC-7C, crashes shortly after takeoff from Shannon Airport for rea=
sons unknown, killing 34 of 52 on board.</li>
<li>March 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwes=
t_Orient_Airlines_Flight_710" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 710=
">Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 710</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Super Elec=
tra en route from Chicago to Miami, Florida, breaks apart at 15,000 feet (4=
,600&nbsp;m) and crashes near Tell City, Indiana, killing all 63 on board.<=
/li>
<li>June 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans_Aus=
tralia_Airlines_Flight_538" title=3D"Trans Australia Airlines Flight 538">T=
rans Australia Airlines Flight 538</a></b>, a Fokker F-27, crashes into the=
 ocean near Mackay, Queensland, Australia, killing all 29 on board in Austr=
alia's worst civilian air disaster. This crash was responsible for the mand=
atory installation of cockpit voice recorders in airliners in Australia, fo=
llowed by the rest of the world.</li>
<li>June 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_207" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 207">Aeroflot Flight 207</a></b>, an I=
lyushin Il-14, crashes into a mountain near Tkvarcheli, Georgia after the c=
rew deviated from the flight route; all 31 on board die.</li>
<li>July 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopian=
_Airlines_Flight_372" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Fli=
ght 372">Ethiopian Airlines Flight 372</a></b>, a Douglas C-47 Skytrain, cr=
ashes into a mountain near Jimma, Ethiopia due to pilot error, killing one =
of the pilots.</li>
<li>August 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_36_(1960)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 36 (1960=
)">Aeroflot Flight 36</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-18, crashes near Tarasovich, =
Ukraine following an engine fire, killing all 34 on board.</li>
<li>September 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aust=
rian_Airlines_Flight_901" title=3D"Austrian Airlines Flight 901">Austrian A=
irlines Flight 901</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes short of runway 07 =
at Sheremetyevo International Airport. 31 of the 37 passengers and crew on =
board are killed.</li>
<li>October 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern=
_Air_Lines_Flight_375" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 375">Eastern Air L=
ines Flight 375</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Super Electra, crashes on takeoff=
 from Boston's Logan International Airport into Winthrop Bay, after multipl=
e bird strikes; 62 of 72 aboard die.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ca=
l_Poly_football_team_plane_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cal Poly f=
ootball team plane crash">Cal Poly football team plane crash</a></b>: a cha=
rtered Curtiss C-46 crashes on takeoff at the Toledo Express Airport in Tol=
edo, Ohio, with the loss of 22 people including 16 players on the Californi=
a Polytechnic State University football team.</li>
<li>December 16 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
960_New_York_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1960 New York mid-air collision">1=
960 New York mid-air collision</a></b>: United Airlines Flight 826, a Dougl=
as DC-8, and TWA Flight 266, a Lockheed Super Constellation, collide in mid=
-air over Staten Island in New York; all 128 aboard the two planes and six =
people on the ground are killed. This is the first crash in which a flight =
recorder was used to provide details in a crash investigation. The accident=
 was the deadliest aviation disaster in history at the time.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1961">1961</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1961">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aer=

DC-3, crashes into woods near Koivulahti, Finland, killing all 25 on board.=
</li>

irlines Flight 1502</a></b>, a Boeing 707, crashes into the sea off Montauk=
 Point, New York during a training flight following a loss of control. All =
six crew members on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saben=

ng 707, crashes on approach in Brussels, Belgium, killing 73, including the=
 entire United States figure skating team: a runaway stabilizer is thought =
to have been the cause of the first fatal accident involving a 707 in regul=
ar passenger service.</li>
<li>March 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot=
_Flight_68" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 68">Aeroflot Fli=
ght 68</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes shortly after takeoff from Koltso=
vo Airport following engine failure, killing five of 51 on board; two peopl=
e on the ground also die when the aircraft hits a house.</li>
<li>March 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C4%8CSA=
_Flight_511_(March_1961)" title=3D"=C4=8CSA Flight 511 (March 1961)">=C4=8C=
SA Flight 511</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-18, breaks up and crashes at Gr=C3=A4=
fenberg, West Germany. All 52 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>

 Flight 621</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes in the Andes, killing all 24 o=
n board including footballers and coaching staff from the CD Green Cross Ch=
ilean football team.</li>
<li>May 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_France=
_Flight_406" title=3D"Air France Flight 406">Air France Flight 406</a></b>,=
 a Lockheed Starliner, crashes into the Sahara Desert near the Edjele oilfi=
eld in Algeria after a bomb goes off on board. All 78 passengers and crew a=
re killed in the crash.</li>

ht_897" title=3D"Viasa Flight 897">Viasa Flight 897</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8=
, crashes shortly after taking off from Lisbon Portela Airport. All 61 pass=
engers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_Fligh=

ectra, crashes while on approach to Cairo International Airport due to pilo=
t error; 20 of 36 on board die.</li>
<li>July 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ai=
rlines_Flight_859" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 859">United Airlines Fli=
ght 859</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, crashes on landing at Stapleton Internatio=
nal Airport, killing 17 passengers and one person on the ground.</li>
<li>July 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C4%8CSA_=

 reasons unknown, killing all 72 on board.</li>
<li>July 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerol%C3%=
ADneas_Argentinas_Flight_644" title=3D"Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Flight 64=
4">Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Flight 644</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, breaks up=
 and crashes 12 miles west of Pardo, Buenos Aires, Argentina after encounte=
ring severe turbulence shortly after takeoff. All 67 passengers and crew on=
 board are killed.</li>
<li>July 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska_Ai=
rlines_Flight_779" title=3D"Alaska Airlines Flight 779">Alaska Airlines Fli=
ght 779</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6A on a military contract flight crashes shor=
t of the runway at Shemya Air Force Base, Alaska. All six crew members are =
killed.</li>
<li>August 9 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holt=
aheia_Accident" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Holtaheia Accident">Holtahei=
a Accident</a></b>: An Eagle Airways Vickers VC.1 Viking crashes at Holta, =
Strand, Norway, killing all 39 on board, including 36 people from the Archb=
ishop Lanfranc School.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_529" title=3D"TWA Flight 529">TWA Flight 529</a></b>, a Lockheed Cons=
tellation L-049 propliner, abruptly pitches up and crashes shortly after ta=
keoff from Chicago's Midway Airport, killing all 73 passengers and five cre=
w on board; a 5/16&nbsp;inch bolt that fell out of the elevator control lin=
kage just before the crash is blamed.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
61_President_Airlines_Douglas_DC-6_crash" title=3D"1961 President Airlines =
Douglas DC-6 crash">President Airlines Douglas DC-6</a></b> crashes shortly=
 after takeoff from Shannon Airport en route to Gander due to loss of contr=
ol caused by possible pilot error, killing all 83 passengers and crew on bo=
ard. The crash remains the worst in Irish territory.</li>
<li>September 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_=

</a></b>, a Sud Aviation Caravelle, crashes on approach to Rabat=E2=80=93Sa=
l=C3=A9 Airport due to misread instruments, killing all 77 on board.</li>
<li>September 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nort=
hwest_Orient_Airlines_Flight_706" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight=
 706">Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 706</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Electr=
a, crashes on takeoff from Chicago as a result of a maintenance error causi=
ng the ailerons to become detached from the control wheels; all 37 on board=
 die.</li>
<li>September 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1961=

 United Nations DC-6 Crash">1961 Ndola United Nations DC-6 Crash</a></b>, a=
 Douglas DC-6B, carrying Dag Hammarskj=C3=B6ld, second Secretary-General of=
 the United Nations, crashes near Ndola, killing all 16 on board.</li>
<li>September 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turk=
ish_Airlines_Flight_835" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 835">Turkish Airl=
ines Flight 835</a></b>, a Fokker F27 Friendship crashes while on approach =
to Esenbo=C4=9Fa Airport; 28 of the 29 passengers and crew on board die in =
the crash.</li>

viation crash</a></b>, a Douglas Dakota, crashes into Canigou mountainside =
en route to Perpignan from London due to a navigation error, killing all 34=
 aboard.</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperi=

 Airlines Flight 201/8</a></b>, a Lockheed Constellation L-049, crashes on =
landing at Byrd Field near Richmond, Virginia; all 74 passengers=E2=80=94mo=
stly new US Army recruits being flown to their base for training=E2=80=94di=
e of carbon monoxide asphyxiation, along with three crew members; the capta=
in and flight engineer survive by escaping the burning wreckage.</li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerol=
%C3%ADneas_Argentinas_Flight_322" title=3D"Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Fligh=
t 322">Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Flight 322</a></b>, a de Havilland Comet,=
 crashes in Campinas, Brazil, shortly after takeoff, killing all 12 crew an=
d 40 passengers on board.</li>
<li>November 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anset=
t-ANA_Flight_325" title=3D"Ansett-ANA Flight 325">Ansett-ANA Flight 325</a>=
</b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes into Botany Bay, Australia, 9 minutes aft=
er takeoff, killing all 15 people on board.</li>
<li>December 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=

an Ilyushin Il-18, enters a nosedive and crashes near Chebotovka, Russia, a=
fter the pilot deployed the flaps by mistake, killing all 59 on board.</li>=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1962">1962</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D46" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1962">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
962_Avensa_Fairchild_F-27_accident" title=3D"1962 Avensa Fairchild F-27 acc=
ident">An Avensa Fairchild F-27 crashes</a></b> into San Juan mountain on M=
argarita Island in the Caribbean Sea, killing all 23 on board.</li>
<li>March 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_=
Airlines_Flight_1" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"American Airlines Flight =
1">American Airlines Flight 1</a></b>, a Boeing 707 destined for Los Angele=
s, California, United States, crashes in Jamaica Bay, Queens, New York, due=
 to a rudder malfunction; all 95 passengers and crew on board are killed.</=
li>
<li>March 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caledonia=
n_Airways_Flight_153" title=3D"Caledonian Airways Flight 153">Caledonian Ai=
rways Flight 153</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7 operating a non-scheduled multi-le=
g flight out of Luxembourg, crashes into a jungle swamp at Douala, Cameroon=
 for reasons unknown, killing all 111 on board.</li>
<li>March 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1962_Turk=
ish_Airlines_Taurus_Mountains_crash" title=3D"1962 Turkish Airlines Taurus =
Mountains crash">A Turkish Airlines Fairchild F-27 crashes</a></b> into the=
 Bolkar Mountains while on approach to Turkey's Adana Airport, killing all =
11 on board.</li>
<li>March 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flying_T=
iger_Line_Flight_739" title=3D"Flying Tiger Line Flight 739">Flying Tiger L=
ine Flight 739</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1049 Super Constellation chartered by =
the United States military to transport 96 American soldiers to South Vietn=
am, disappears over the western Pacific.</li>
<li>May 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1962_Channe=
l_Airways_Dakota_accident" title=3D"1962 Channel Airways Dakota accident">A=
 Channel Airways Douglas C-47 Dakota crashes</a></b> into a hill on the Isl=
e of Wight in bad weather, while en route from Jersey to London's Southend =
Airport, killing 12 of the 18 on board.</li>
<li>May 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1962_Godth=
ab_Catalina_crash" title=3D"1962 Godthab Catalina crash">An Eastern Provinc=
ial Airlines Canso flying boat sinks</a></b> at Godthab Harbour, Greenland,=
 killing 15 of the 21 on board.</li>
<li>May 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continenta=
l_Airlines_Flight_11" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 11">Continental =
Airlines Flight 11</a></b>, a Boeing 707 flying from Chicago, Illinois, to =
Kansas City, Missouri, breaks up in mid-air near Unionville, Missouri, afte=
r a passenger's bomb explodes in the lavatory, killing all 45 people on boa=
rd.</li>
<li>June 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_France=
_Flight_007" title=3D"Air France Flight 007">Air France Flight 007</a></b>,=
 a chartered Boeing 707, catches fire after overshooting the runway on take=
off, killing all but two of the 130 passengers and crew on board; among the=
 fatalities are many of the civic and cultural leaders of Atlanta, Georgia;=
 it is the worst single-aircraft accident to that date.</li>
<li>June 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Franc=
e_Flight_117" title=3D"Air France Flight 117">Air France Flight 117</a></b>=
, a Boeing 707 operating an international multi-leg flight from Paris, Fran=
ce, to Santiago, Chile, crashes into a forested hill on the island of Guade=
loupe, while approaching Pointe-=C3=A0-Pitre International Airport; all 113=
 on board are killed; the cause of the crash is never determined.</li>
<li>June 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_902" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 902">Aeroflot Flight 902</a></b>, a Tu=
polev Tu-104 operating a domestic flight in the Soviet Union, is shot down =
by a missile near Voznesenka, Krasnoyarsk Krai; all 84 people on board die =
in Russia's worst air accident to that date.</li>
<li>July 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alitalia_F=
light_771" title=3D"Alitalia Flight 771">Alitalia Flight 771</a></b>, a Dou=
glas DC-8 operating a multi-leg flight between Sydney, Australia, and Rome,=
 Italy, hits high terrain while descending near Junnar in India, due to nav=
igation error; all 94 on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ar=
ab_Airlines_Flight_869_(1962)" title=3D"United Arab Airlines Flight 869 (19=
62)">United Arab Airlines Flight 869</a></b>, a de Havilland DH-106 Comet 4=
C operating an international scheduled flight from Hong Kong to Cairo, via =
Bangkok, crashes into the Khao Yai mountain while descending to Bangkok; al=
l 26 people on board lose their lives.</li>
<li>July 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_=
Pacific_Air_Lines_Flight_301" title=3D"Canadian Pacific Air Lines Flight 30=
1">Canadian Pacific Air Lines Flight 301</a></b>, a Bristol Britannia desti=
ned for Nadi, Fiji, crashes during an attempted "go-around" on a three-engi=
ned approach at Honolulu Airport, Hawaii, after experiencing engine problem=
s shortly after takeoff; 27 of the 40 on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_415" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 415">Aeroflot Flight 415</a></b>, an A=
ntonov An-10 operating a domestic flight in the Soviet Union, crashes into =
a mountain near Sochi Airport due to ATC and crew errors; all 81 on board l=
ose their lives.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_3" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3">Aeroflot Fl=
ight 3</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-104 operating a domestic flight in the Soviet =
Union, crashes near Kuruna, Nanaysky District, due to an unexplained loss o=
f control; all 86 on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Flight_297" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 297">United Airlines=
 Flight 297</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount 745D operating a multi-leg flight b=
etween the US states of New Jersey and Georgia, crashes near Ellicott City,=
 Maryland, following a bird strike; all 17 people on board lose their lives=
.</li>
<li>November 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Varig=
_Flight_810" title=3D"Varig Flight 810">Varig Flight 810</a></b>, a Boeing =
707-441 flying from Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, to Los Angeles, California, Uni=
ted States, crashes into a mountain near Lima airport in Peru, killing all =
97 occupants.</li>
<li>November 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Easte=
rn_Air_Lines_Flight_512" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 512">Eastern Air=
 Lines Flight 512</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7B operating a domestic flight from=
 Charlotte, North Carolina, United States, to New York City, crashes as a r=
esult of pilot error during a missed approach at New York's Idlewild Airpor=
t; 25 of the 51 on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1962_=
LOT_Vickers_Viscount_Warsaw_crash" title=3D"1962 LOT Vickers Viscount Warsa=
w crash">A LOT Vickers Viscount Warsaw crashes</a></b> on approach to Okeci=
e International Airport, Warsaw, Poland, due to loss of control; all 33 pas=
sengers and crew on board lose their lives.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1963">1963</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1963">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

<ul><li>February 1 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/1963_Ankara_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1963 Ankara mid-air collision"=
>Ankara mid-air collision</a></b>, Middle East Airlines Flight 265, a Vicke=
rs Viscount, collides with a Turkish Air Force Douglas C-47, killing all 17=
 on board both aircraft and 87 on the ground.</li>
<li>February 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North=
west_Orient_Airlines_Flight_705" title=3D"Northwest Orient Airlines Flight =
705">Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 705</a></b>, a Boeing 720, breaks up =
in turbulence associated with a severe thunderstorm and crashes into the Ev=
erglades; all 43 passengers and crew members on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_191" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 191">Aeroflot Flight 191</a></b>, an I=
lyushin Il-18, crashes on landing at Ashgabat International Airport due to =
a dust storm, killing 12 of 54 on board.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_25" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 25">Aeroflot Flight 25</a></b>, an Ilyu=
shin Il-18, crashes in Tatarstan after suffering an engine malfunction, kil=
ling all 67 people aboard.</li>
<li>June 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest_=
Airlines_Flight_293" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flig=
ht 293">Northwest Airlines Flight 293</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7C operating a =
military charter crashes into the sea off Annette Island, Alaska for reason=
s unknown. All 101 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>July 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohawk_Air=
lines_Flight_121" title=3D"Mohawk Airlines Flight 121">Mohawk Airlines Flig=
ht 121</a></b>, a Martin 4-0-4, crashes near Rochester, New York, while att=
empting takeoff, killing seven of the 43 people on board.</li>
<li>July 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealan=
d_National_Airways_Corporation_Flight_441" title=3D"New Zealand National Ai=
rways Corporation Flight 441">New Zealand National Airways Corporation Flig=
ht 441</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 en route from Whenuapai Airport, Auckland to=
 Tauranga, crashes into the Kaimai Ranges; all 23 aboard die, making it the=
 worst air disaster in mainland New Zealand to date.</li>
<li>July 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_12" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 12">Aeroflot Flig=
ht 12</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes on approach to Irkutsk following a=
 premature descent, killing 33 of 35 on board.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ar=
ab_Airlines_Flight_869_(1963)" title=3D"United Arab Airlines Flight 869 (19=
63)">United Arab Airlines Flight 869</a></b>, a de Havilland Comet 4C, cras=
hes into the sea while on approach to Bombay Airport, India, killing all 63=
 on board.</li>
<li>August 21 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1963=
_Aeroflot_Tupolev_Tu-124_Neva_river_ditching" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"1963 Aeroflot Tupolev Tu-124 Neva river ditching">Aeroflot Tupolev Tu-1=
24 ditches in the Neva river</a></b> in Leningrad after engine failure; the=
re are no fatalities among the 52 on board, but the aircraft is destroyed.<=
/li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_663" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 663">Aeroflot Flight 663</a></b>, an=
 Avia 14P, crashes into a mountain near Gegechkori, Georgia in bad weather =
after the pilot deviated from the flight route; all 32 on board die.</li>
<li>September 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swiss=
air_Flight_306" title=3D"Swissair Flight 306">Swissair Flight 306</a></b>, =
a Sud Aviation Caravelle, crashes near D=C3=BCrren=C3=A4sch, Switzerland, d=
ue to an in-flight fire, killing all 80 on board.</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero_F=
light_217" title=3D"Aero Flight 217">Aero Flight 217</a></b>, a Douglas DC-=
3, crashes in poor visibility near <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Mariehamn_Airport" title=3D"Mariehamn Airport">Mariehamn Airport</a>, kill=
ing 22 out of 25 on board.</li>
<li>November 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans=
-Canada_Air_Lines_Flight_831" title=3D"Trans-Canada Air Lines Flight 831">T=
rans-Canada Air Lines Flight 831</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, crashes shortly a=
fter takeoff from Montreal/Dorval Airport, killing all 118 people on board.=
</li>
<li>December 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_214" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 214">Pan Am Flight 214</a></b>, a Boein=
g 707, is struck by positive lightning and crashes near Elkton, Maryland, k=
illing all 81 people on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1964">1964</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1964">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>February 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
astern_Air_Lines_Flight_304" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 304">Eastern=
 Air Lines Flight 304</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8 flying from New Orleans Inter=
national Airport to Washington National Airport, crashes into Lake Pontchar=
train, killing all 51 passengers and seven crew aboard.</li>
<li>February 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Briti=
sh_Eagle_International_Airlines_Flight_802" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=
British Eagle International Airlines Flight 802">British Eagle Internationa=
l Airlines Flight 802</a></b>, a Bristol Britannia, crashes into a mountain=
 near Innsbruck, Austria. All 75 passengers and eight crew are killed in th=
e crash.</li>
<li>March 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paradise_=
Airlines_Flight_901A" title=3D"Paradise Airlines Flight 901A">Paradise Airl=
ines Flight 901A</a></b>, a Lockheed L-049 Constellation, crashes near Lake=
 Tahoe, killing all 85 aboard when it collides with a mountain.</li>
<li>May 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Air=
_Lines_Flight_773" title=3D"Pacific Air Lines Flight 773">Pacific Air Lines=
 Flight 773</a></b>, a Fairchild F27, crashes near San Ramon, California, k=
illing all 44 aboard, after a passenger shoots both the captain and first o=
fficer before turning the gun on himself.</li>
<li>June 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_Air=
_Transport_Flight_106" title=3D"Civil Air Transport Flight 106">Civil Air T=
ransport Flight 106</a></b>, a Curtiss C-46, crashes near Shenkang, Taiwan,=
 killing all 57 on board.</li>
<li>July 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Air=
lines_Flight_823" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 823">United Airlines Flig=
ht 823</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes near Parrottsville, Tennessee, =
after a fire on board; all 39 passengers and crew die.</li>
<li>September 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_721" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 721">Aeroflot Flight 721</a></b>, =
an Ilyushin Il-18, crashes into a hillside while on approach to Yuzhno-Sakh=
alinsk Airport due to pilot error, killing 87 of 93 on board.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonan=
za_Air_Lines_Flight_114" title=3D"Bonanza Air Lines Flight 114">Bonanza Air=
 Lines Flight 114</a></b>, a Fairchild F27, flies into a mountain in poor w=
eather while on a nighttime approach to Las Vegas, Nevada. All 29 aboard ar=
e killed.</li>
<li>November 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linje=
flyg_Flight_267" title=3D"Linjeflyg Flight 267">Linjeflyg Flight 267</a></b=
>, a Convair CV-340, crashes during the approach to Engelholm, Sweden, when=
, in instrument meteorological conditions, the crew abandons the set proced=
ure and descends prematurely; 31 people are killed; 12 survive.</li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_800_(1964)" title=3D"TWA Flight 800 (1964)">TWA Flight 800</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 707, suffers engine failure and crashes at Leonardo da Vinci-Fiumic=
ino Airport, killing 50 of 73 on board; the cause is an inoperative thrust =
reverser.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flyin=
g_Tiger_Line_Flight_282" title=3D"Flying Tiger Line Flight 282">Flying Tige=
r Line Flight 282</a></b>, a Lockheed Constellation, crashes near San Bruno=
, California, after an unexplained course deviation, killing the crew of th=
ree.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1965">1965</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D49" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1965">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aer=
oflot_Flight_20" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 20">Aeroflo=
t Flight 20</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-18, crashes on approach to Alma-Ata in =
poor visibility, killing 64 of 103 on board.</li>
<li>February 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAN_Ch=
ile_Flight_107" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LAN Chile Flight 107">LAN Ch=
ile Flight 107</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, crashes shortly after takeoff from =
Santiago-Los Cerrillos Airport in Santiago, Chile. All 87 passengers and cr=
ew on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Easter=
n_Air_Lines_Flight_663" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 663">Eastern Air =
Lines Flight 663</a></b>, a Douglas DC-7B on takeoff, overreacts in avoidin=
g Pan Am Flight 212 (a Boeing 707) on approach, loses control, and crashes =
into the ocean several miles off Jones Beach State Park, New York, killing =
all 84 on board.</li>
<li>March 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_513" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 513">Aeroflot Flight 513</a></b>, a Tu=
polev Tu-124V stalls and crashes after taking off from Kuybyshev Airport, R=
ussia. 30 out of the 39 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>April 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_=
United_Airways_Flight_1030X" title=3D"British United Airways Flight 1030X">=
British United Airways Flight 1030X</a></b>, a Douglas C-47, crashes on lan=
ding at Jersey Airport due to pilot error; of the 27 passengers and crew on=
 board, only a flight attendant survives.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iberia_Airl=
ines_Flight_401" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Iberia Airlines Flight 401"=
>Iberia Airlines Flight 401</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1049 Super Constellation,=
 crashes after striking a tractor on the runway at Los Rodeos Airport, Tene=
rife, during a go-around in foggy weather; 30 of 49 passengers and crew die=
.</li>
<li>May 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIA_Flight=
_705" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"PIA Flight 705">PIA Flight 705</a></b>=
, a Boeing 720, crashes on descent to Cairo International Airport, killing =
119 of 125 on board in the worst-ever accident involving the 720.</li>
<li>July 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continenta=
l_Airlines_Flight_12" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 12">Continental =
Airlines Flight 12</a></b>, a Boeing 707, runs off the end of the runway at=
 Kansas City Downtown Airport, breaking into three pieces; all 66 on board =
survive.</li>
<li>July 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_P=
acific_Air_Lines_Flight_21" title=3D"Canadian Pacific Air Lines Flight 21">=
Canadian Pacific Air Lines Flight 21</a></b>, a Douglas DC-6, crashes near =
100 Mile House, British Columbia, after the explosion of a device in the la=
vatory; all 46 passengers and six crew aboard die.</li>
<li>July 10 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1965_Sk=
yways_Coach-Air_Avro_748_crash" title=3D"1965 Skyways Coach-Air Avro 748 cr=
ash">Skyways Coach-Air Avro 748 crashes</a></b> on landing at Lympne Airpor=
t, Kent, United Kingdom, due to a waterlogged runway; all 52 on board survi=
ve; this crash marks the first loss of the Avro 748/HS 748.</li>
<li>July 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ca=
mbrian_Airways_Liverpool_crash" title=3D"Cambrian Airways Liverpool crash">=
Cambrian Airways Liverpool crash</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount crashes on app=
roach into Liverpool-Speke Airport, United Kingdom. Both crew members, as w=
ell as two on the ground, are killed.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_=
Airlines_Flight_389" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 389">United Airlines F=
light 389</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes into Lake Michigan at night, after=
 the pilots apparently misread their altimeters; all 24 passengers and six =
crew die in the first fatal crash of the Boeing 727.</li>
<li>September 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_=
Am_Flight_292" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 292">Pan Am Flight 292</a></b>, a Boe=
ing 707, crashes into Chances Peak, Montserrat, in stormy weather; all 30 o=
n board die.</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Airlines_Flight_383_(1965)" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 383 (1965)=
">American Airlines Flight 383</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes while on appr=
oach to Greater Cincinnati airport; of the 62 people on board, one flight a=
ttendant and three passengers survive.</li>
<li>November 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Flight_227" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 227">United Airlines=
 Flight 227</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes short of the runway during landi=
ng at Salt Lake City International Airport, Utah; 43 of 91 aboard are kille=
d.</li>
<li>November 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_99" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 99">Aeroflot Flight 99</a></b>, a T=
upolev Tu-124, crashes near Murmansk, Russia, due to pilot error, killing 3=
2 of 64 on board.</li>
<li>December 4 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
65_Carmel_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1965 Carmel mid-air collision">1965 C=
armel mid-air collision</a></b>; Eastern Air Lines Flight 853, a Lockheed S=
uper Constellation, collides with TWA Flight 42, a Boeing 707 over Carmel, =
New York. Flight 42 makes an emergency landing at John F. Kennedy Internati=
onal Airport; Flight 853 is forced to crash land on Hunt Mountain near Danb=
ury, Connecticut, killing three passengers and one of the pilots on board. =
No casualties are reported on board Flight 42.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1966">1966</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1966">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Av=
ianca_Flight_4" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Avianca Flight 4">Avianca Fl=
ight 4</a></b>, a Douglas C-54, suffers engine failure and crashes off Cart=
agena, Colombia, killing 56 of the 64 on board.</li>

dia_Flight_101" title=3D"Air India Flight 101">Air India Flight 101</a></b>=
, a Boeing 707-437, crashes into the southwest face of Mont Blanc in France=
; all 106 passengers and 11 crew are killed. Sixteen years earlier <b><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India_Flight_245" title=3D"Air Indi=
a Flight 245">Air India Flight 245</a></b> had crashed in almost exactly th=
e same spot.</li>

, a Convair 440, crashes at Bremen Airport; all 46 on board die.</li>

al Airlines Flight 17</a></b>, a Sikorsky S-61 helicopter, crashes near Far=
idpur, Bangladesh, Pakistan; of the 23 on board, only a passenger survives.=
</li>

ppon_Airways_Flight_60" title=3D"All Nippon Airways Flight 60">All Nippon A=
irways Flight 60</a></b>, a Boeing 727-100, crashes into Tokyo Bay, Japan; =
all 133 aboard are killed in Japan's worst air disaster at that time.</li>

Flight 65</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-114, crashes on takeoff from Sheremetyevo I=
nternational Airport due to crew and ATC errors, killing 21 of 63 on board.=

passengers and crew; eight passengers survive.</li>

nd for Hong Kong, breaks up in mid-air and crashes at Mount Fuji near Goten=

nto a hill short of Ardmore Municipal Airport in Oklahoma, United States. 8=

></b>, a Vickers Viscount, crashes near Winton, Queensland, Australia, kill=

>

n Airways Flight 533</a></b>, a NAMC YS-11, plunges into Seto Inland Sea af=

 Sam Ratulangi Airport, killing 22 of 84 passengers on board; all eight cre=
w survive.</li>

 after a propeller detaches and severs the fuselage, causing a loss of cont=
rol; all 38 on board die.</li>

>Varig Airlines Flight 837</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, crashes while on approa=

 DC-9, collides with a Beechcraft Baron near Dayton, Ohio, killing all 26 o=
n both planes.</li>

oast Flight 720</a></b>, a Fokker F27 Friendship crashes shortly after taki=
ng off from Klamath Falls, Oregon. All four occupants are killed.</li>
<li>March 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Af=
rican_Airways_Flight_406" title=3D"South African Airways Flight 406">South =
African Airways Flight 406</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount 818, crashes into th=
e sea while on approach to East London, South Africa, killing all 25 passen=
gers and crew on board. The report on the accident speculated that the pilo=
t of the plane suffered a fatal heart attack while on approach and the co-p=
ilot was unable to regain control of the aircraft.</li>
<li>April 20 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1967=

 Nicosia Britannia disaster</a></b>: a Globe Air-operated Bristol Britannia=
 on a charter flight in bad weather near Lakatamia, Cyprus, killing 126 of =
the 130 on board.</li>

Ferry DC-4 accident</a></b>, a Douglas DC-4 crashes into a mountain en rout=

gers and crew are killed.</li>

r</a></b>, a British Midland Canadair C-4 Argonaut carrying passengers retu=
rning from Palma de Mallorca is on approach to Manchester Airport when an e=
ngine loses power because of a design failure in the aircraft's fuel system=

erruns the runway at Greater Cincinnati Airport and catches fire; all on bo=
ard escape the aircraft, but a passenger dies four days later.</li>
<li>November 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=

>, an Ilyushin Il-18, crashes just after takeoff from Koltsovo Airport, kil=
ling all 107 passengers and crew on board in the worst-ever accident involv=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1969">1969</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1969">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ari=
ana_Afghan_Airlines_Flight_701" title=3D"Ariana Afghan Airlines Flight 701"=
>Ariana Afghan Airlines Flight 701</a></b>, a Boeing 727-100C, arriving at =
London Gatwick Airport from Frankfurt Airport crashes into a house in dense=
 fog, killing 48 of the 62 persons aboard; a married couple living at the h=
ouse also die, but their baby survives.</li>
<li>January 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alleghe=
ny_Airlines_Flight_737" title=3D"Allegheny Airlines Flight 737">Allegheny A=
irlines Flight 737</a></b>, a Convair CV-580, crashes while on approach to =
Bradford Regional Airport. 11 of the 28 passengers and crew on board are ki=
lled.</li>
<li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scandi=
navian_Airlines_Flight_933" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Scandinavian Air=
lines Flight 933">Scandinavian Airlines Flight 933</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8,=
 crashes into Santa Monica Bay due to pilot error, killing 15 of 45 on boar=
d.</li>
<li>January 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United=
_Airlines_Flight_266" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 266">United Airlines =
Flight 266</a></b>, a Boeing 727, en route from Los Angeles to Milwaukee lo=
ses all electrical power and crashes into Santa Monica Bay; six crew and 32=
 passengers are killed.</li>
<li>February 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawth=
orne_Nevada_Airlines_Flight_708" title=3D"Hawthorne Nevada Airlines Flight =
708">Hawthorne Nevada Airlines Flight 708</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes =
near Lone Pine, California, killing all 35 people on board.</li>
<li>February 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far_E=
astern_Air_Transport_Flight_104" title=3D"Far Eastern Air Transport Flight =
104">Far Eastern Air Transport Flight 104</a></b>, a Handley Page Dart Hera=
ld, suffers engine failure and crashes while on approach to Tainan Airport,=
 Taiwan; all 36 on board die.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prinair_f=
light_277" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Prinair flight 277">Prinair fligh=
t 277</a></b>, a de Havilland Heron, crashes into mountainous territory at =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luquillo,_Puerto_Rico" title=3D"Lu=
quillo, Puerto Rico">Luquillo, Puerto Rico</a>, killing all 19 people on bo=
ard.</li>
<li>March 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viasa_Fl=
ight_742" title=3D"Viasa Flight 742">Viasa Flight 742</a></b>, a McDonnell =
Douglas DC-9-30, crashes on takeoff from Maracaibo, Venezuela. All 84 passe=
ngers on board, plus 71 people on the ground are killed in the crash. At 15=
5 people dead, it was the worst aviation disaster in history at that time.<=
/li>
<li>March 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
969_Aswan_Ilyushin_Il-18_crash" title=3D"1969 Aswan Ilyushin Il-18 crash">1=
969 Aswan Ilyushin Il-18 crash</a></b>, a United Arab Airlines flight crash=
es while attempting to land at Aswan International Airport. 100 of the 105 =
passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOT_Polis=
h_Airlines_Flight_165" title=3D"LOT Polish Airlines Flight 165">LOT Polish =
Airlines Flight 165</a></b>, an Antonov An-24, crashes in southern Poland, =
killing all 53 people on board.</li>
<li>April 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAN_Chil=
e_Flight_160" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LAN Chile Flight 160">LAN Chil=
e Flight 160</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes near Colina, Chile; all 60 on b=
oard survive.</li>
<li>June 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexicana_F=
light_704" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mexicana Flight 704">Mexicana Fli=
ght 704</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes near Salinas Victoria in Mexico. All=
 79 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 23 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
69_Yukhnov_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1969 Yukhnov mid-air collision">Yukh=
nov mid-air collision</a></b>, Aeroflot Flight 831, an Ilyushin Il-14, coll=
ides in mid-air with a Soviet Air Force Antonov An-12 over Yukhnovsky Distr=
ict, Russia, killing all 120 people on both aircraft.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
TWA_Flight_840_hijacking" title=3D"TWA Flight 840 hijacking">TWA Flight 840=
 hijacking</a></b>, two operatives from the Popular Front for the Liberatio=
n of Palestine force a Boeing 707 to land at Damascus, Syria; all passenger=
s are released except for two passengers who are released two months later;=
 there are no casualties to the 127 on board, but the aircraft's nose secti=
on is blown up.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alleg=
heny_Airlines_Flight_853" title=3D"Allegheny Airlines Flight 853">Allegheny=
 Airlines Flight 853</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9, collides in flight with a Pip=
er PA-28 Cherokee and crashes near Fairland, Indiana, killing all 83 occupa=
nts aboard the two aircraft.</li>
<li>September 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phil=
ippine_Airlines_Flight_158" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 158">Philip=
pine Airlines Flight 158</a></b>, a BAC One-Eleven, crashes on approach to =
Manila International Airport, killing 45 of the 47 passengers and crew on b=
oard.</li>
<li>November 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohaw=
k_Airlines_Flight_411" title=3D"Mohawk Airlines Flight 411">Mohawk Airlines=
 Flight 411</a></b>, a Fairchild 227, crashes near Glens Falls, New York, k=
illing all 14 people on board.</li>
<li>November 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger=
ia_Airways_Flight_825" title=3D"Nigeria Airways Flight 825">Nigeria Airways=
 Flight 825</a></b>, a Vickers VC-10, crashes on approach to Lagos Internat=
ional Airport, killing all 87 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>December 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fr=
ance_Flight_212_(1969)" title=3D"Air France Flight 212 (1969)">Air France F=
light 212</a></b>, a Boeing 707-328B, crashes into the sea shortly after ta=
keoff from Sim=C3=B3n Bol=C3=ADvar International Airport with the loss of a=
ll 62 on board.</li>
<li>December 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olympi=
c_Airways_Flight_954" title=3D"Olympic Airways Flight 954">Olympic Airways =
Flight 954</a></b>, a DC-6, crashes into Mt. Paneio while on approach to At=
hens-Ellinikon International Airport. All 90 passengers and crew on board a=
re killed.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1970s">1970s</span><span class=3D"mw-=

s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_in=

it section: 1970s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1970">1970</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D55" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1970">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/197=
0_Spantax_CV-990_crash" title=3D"1970 Spantax CV-990 crash">A Spantax Conva=
ir 990 Coronado crashes</a></b> shortly after takeoff from Stockholm's Arla=
nda Airport when the flight crew loses control of the aircraft; five of the=
 ten people on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerol%=
C3%ADneas_Argentinas_Flight_707" title=3D"Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Flight=
 707">Aerol=C3=ADneas Argentinas Flight 707</a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 7=
48 operating a multi-leg flight from Paraguay to Argentina, crashes near Lo=
ma Alta when the pilots lose control of the aircraft due to severe turbulen=
ce; all 37 passengers and crew die.</li>
<li>February 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_U-45" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight U-45">Aeroflot Flight U-45</a></b>=
, an Ilyushin Il-18 operating a domestic flight in Uzbekistan, crashes into=
 a mountain on approach to Samarkand International Airport due to ATC error=
; 92 of the 106 people on board the aircraft were killed.</li>
<li>February 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Domin=
icana_DC-9_air_disaster" title=3D"Dominicana DC-9 air disaster">A Dominican=
a Douglas DC-9 crashes</a></b> shortly after takeoff from Santo Domingo in =
the Dominican Republic, due to engine failure; all 102 people on board are =
killed.</li>
<li>February 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swiss=
air_Flight_330" title=3D"Swissair Flight 330">Swissair Flight 330</a></b>, =
a Convair CV-990 bound for Tel Aviv, Israel, en route to Hong Kong, crashes=
 when a bomb detonates in the cargo hold nine minutes after takeoff from Zu=
rich International Airport, Switzerland; all 38 passengers and nine crew di=
e.</li>
<li>March 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_=
Air_Lines_Shuttle_Flight_1320" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Shuttle Flight 13=
20">Eastern Air Lines Shuttle Flight 1320</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9-31 flying=
 from Newark, New Jersey, to Boston, Massachusetts, is hijacked by a suicid=
al man who shoots both pilots before being subdued; the captain makes a suc=
cessful emergency landing in Boston where the hijacker is arrested; the co-=
pilot dies from his injuries.</li>
<li>March 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_Ai=
rlines_Flight_351" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines Flight 351=
">Japan Airlines Flight 351</a></b>, a Boeing 727 operating a domestic flig=
ht from Tokyo to Fukuoka, is hijacked by a Japanese Red Army faction who fo=
rce the crew to proceed to North Korea after releasing 21 passengers at Fuk=
uoka Airport; the hijackers eventually surrender and all 129 people on boar=
d the flight are unharmed.</li>
<li>April 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_1661" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1661">Aeroflot Flight 1661</a></b>, a=
n Antonov An-24 operating a domestic flight in Russia, crashes on climbout =
after departing from Novosibirsk Tolmachevo Airport, due to a collision wit=
h a weather balloon; all 45 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>April 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippi=
ne_Airlines_Flight_215" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 215">Philippine=
 Airlines Flight 215</a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 748 operating a domestic=
 flight from Cauayan Airport to Manila International Airport, explodes in m=
id-air and crashes 75 miles (121&nbsp;km) north of its destination, killing=
 all 36 on board; a bomb is suspected.</li>
<li>May 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ALM_Flight_=
980" title=3D"ALM Flight 980">ALM Flight 980</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9 operat=
ed by Overseas National Airways, ditches into the Caribbean Sea near St. Cr=
oix, Virgin Islands, due to fuel exhaustion after several unsuccessful land=
ing attempts at St. Maarten in the Dutch Antilles; 23 of the 63 people on b=
oard die.</li>
<li>July 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan-Air_Fl=
ight_1903" title=3D"Dan-Air Flight 1903">Dan-Air Flight 1903</a></b>, a de =
Havilland Comet 4 operating a flight from Manchester, England, to Barcelona=
, Spain, crashes near Arb=C3=BAcies in Catalonia on approach to El Prat Jos=
ep Tarradellas Airport; all 112 people on board the aircraft are killed.</l=
i>
<li>July 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Canada=
_Flight_621" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 621">Air Canada Flight 621</a></b>,=
 a Douglas DC-8 operating a flight from Montreal, Canada, to Los Angeles, U=
nited States, crashes during a failed landing attempt at its scheduled stop=
over at Toronto Pearson International Airport, killing all 109 on board.</l=
i>
<li>August 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LANSA_Fl=
ight_502" title=3D"LANSA Flight 502">LANSA Flight 502</a></b>, a Lockheed L=
-188 Electra turboprop operating a domestic flight in Peru, crashes shortly=
 after takeoff from Cusco's Quispiquilla Airport due to engine failure, kil=
ling 99 of the 100 people on board, including 49 U.S. high school exchange =
students, as well as two on the ground.</li>
<li>August 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_A=
irlines_Flight_206" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 206">China Airlines Flig=
ht 206</a></b>, a NAMC YS-11, crashes into Yuan Mountain in thick fog durin=
g a severe thunderstorm, while on approach to Taipei International Airport;=
 14 of the 31 people on board lose their lives.</li></ul>
