<ul><li>September 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
eroflot_Flight_3630" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3630">Aeroflot Flight 3630</a=
></b>, a Tupolev Tu-124 en route from southern Russia to Lithuania, crashes=
 after the pilots lose control of the aircraft at cruise altitude between R=
ostov-on-Don Airport and Vilnius Airport, on the second leg of the flight; =
all 37 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>September 6 =E2=80=93 The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine=
 orchestrates the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dawson%27s_Fi=
eld_hijackings" title=3D"Dawson's Field hijackings">Dawson's Field hijackin=
gs</a></b> of El Al Flight 219 (Boeing 707), Pan Am Flight 93 (Boeing 747),=
 Swissair Flight 100 (Douglas DC-8), TWA Flight 741 (Boeing 707), and (on S=
eptember 9) BOAC Flight 775 (Vickers VC10); the unprecedented scale of the =
incident draws international outrage and contributes to the eventual widesp=
read implementation of systematic air passenger screening; Flight 93 is the=
 first ever loss of the Boeing 747.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita=
_State_University_football_team_plane_crash" title=3D"Wichita State Univers=
ity football team plane crash">A chartered Martin 4-0-4 airliner crashes</a=
></b> into a mountain near Silver Plume, Colorado, United States, while car=
rying members of the Wichita State University football team to Logan, Utah,=
 for a game; 31 of the 40 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_244" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 244">Aeroflot Flight 244</a></b>, a=
n Antonov An-24 flying from Georgia to Abkhazia along the Black Sea coast, =
is hijacked by a Lithuanian national and his 13-year-old son, who kill one =
flight attendant and force the plane to divert to Trabzon, Turkey, where th=
ey surrender to the Turkish government; this is the first known successful =
airline hijacking in the Soviet Union.</li>
<li>November 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South=
ern_Airways_Flight_932" title=3D"Southern Airways Flight 932">Southern Airw=
ays Flight 932</a></b>, a chartered Douglas DC-9 flying from North Carolina=
 to West Virginia, United States, crashes on approach to Huntington's Tri-S=
tate Airport due to pilot error; all 75 on board die, including 37 players =
of the Marshall University football team and eight of the coaching staff.</=
li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1971">1971</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D56" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1971">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
71_January_22_Surgut_Aeroflot_Antonov_An-12_crash" title=3D"1971 January 22=
 Surgut Aeroflot Antonov An-12 crash">An Aeroflot Antonov An-12 crashes</a>=
</b> due to icing while on approach to Surgut International Airport, RSFSR,=
 Soviet Union, killing all 14 on board the aircraft.</li>
<li>January 30 =E2=80=93 In the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
71_Indian_Airlines_hijacking" title=3D"1971 Indian Airlines hijacking"><b>1=
971 Indian Airlines hijacking</b></a>, a Fokker F-27 Friendship 100 operati=
ng a domestic passenger flight is hijacked en-route from Srinagar to Jammu =
and flown to Lahore in Pakistan where the passengers and crew are released =
and the plane is subsequently destroyed.</li>
<li>January 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1971_J=
anuary_31_Surgut_Aeroflot_Antonov_An-12_crash" title=3D"1971 January 31 Sur=
gut Aeroflot Antonov An-12 crash">An Aeroflot Antonov An-12 crashes</a></b>=
 due to icing while on approach to Surgut International Airport, RSFSR, Sov=
iet Union. All seven on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot=
_Flight_1969" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1969">Aeroflot Flight 1969</a></b>, =
an Antonov An-10, crashes on approach to Voroshilovgrad Airport (now Luhans=
k Airport), Ukraine following an unexplained structural failure of the righ=
t wing, killing all 65 on board.</li>
<li>May 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aviogenex_=
Flight_130" title=3D"Aviogenex Flight 130">Aviogenex Flight 130</a></b>, a =
Tupolev Tu-134 flying from London's Gatwick Airport to Rijeka Airport in Cr=
oatia, crashes on landing at its destination due to pilot error, killing 78=
 of the 83 people on board.</li>
<li>June 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hughes_Air=
west_Flight_706" title=3D"Hughes Airwest Flight 706">Hughes Airwest Flight =
706</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9 operating a domestic flight from Los Angeles, C=
alifornia, to Seattle, Washington, United States, collides with a US Marine=
 Corps McDonnell Douglas F-4B Phantom II fighter jet, and crashes into the =
San Gabriel Mountains near Duarte, California, killing all 49 people on boa=
rd; the fighter jet pilot is also killed, but the Radar Intercept Officer s=
uccessfully bails out.</li>
<li>June 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allegheny_=
Airlines_Flight_485" title=3D"Allegheny Airlines Flight 485">Allegheny Airl=
ines Flight 485</a></b>, a Convair CV-580 operating a multi-leg domestic fl=
ight between Washington, D.C., and Virginia in the United States, crashes o=
n approach to Tweed New Haven Airport, Connecticut, killing 28 of the 31 pe=
ople on board.</li>
<li>July 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toa_Domest=
ic_Airlines_Flight_63" title=3D"Toa Domestic Airlines Flight 63">Toa Domest=
ic Airlines Flight 63</a></b>, a NAMC YS-11 operating a domestic flight in =
Japan, crashes into Yokotsu Mountain near Hakodate Airport on Japan's Hokka=
id=C5=8D island, killing all 68 passengers and crew in the worst-ever disas=
ter involving the YS-11.</li>
<li>July 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_1912" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1912">Aeroflot Flight 1912</a></b>, a=
 Tupolev Tu-104 operating a multi-leg domestic flight between Odessa and Vl=
adivostok in the Soviet Union, lands hard and crashes short of the runway a=
t Irkutsk Airport, killing 97 of the 126 people on board.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_Nippo=
n_Airways_Flight_58" title=3D"All Nippon Airways Flight 58">All Nippon Airw=
ays Flight 58</a></b>, a Boeing 727-200 operating a domestic flight from Sa=
pporo to Tokyo, Japan, collides with a JASDF F-86 Sabre fighter jet at Shiz=
ukuishi near Morioka, killing all 162 passengers and crew on board; the F-8=
6 pilot parachutes to safety, but is later arrested and charged with involu=
ntary manslaughter.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_Fl=
ight_845" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 845">Pan Am Flight 845</a></b>, a Boeing 7=
47-100 flying from Los Angeles, California, United States, to Tokyo, Japan,=
 collides with approach lighting structures on taking off from its intermed=
iate stop, San Francisco International Airport, and then crashes after turn=
ing back to attempt an emergency landing at the same airport; there are no =
fatalities but 29 of the 199 passengers are injured.</li>
<li>September 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alask=
a_Airlines_Flight_1866" title=3D"Alaska Airlines Flight 1866">Alaska Airlin=
es Flight 1866</a></b>, a Boeing 727 operating a flight from Anchorage, Ala=
ska, to Seattle, Washington, United States, crashes into a mountain in the =
Tongass National Forest near Juneau, Alaska, killing all 111 on board.</li>
<li>September 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panin=
ternational_Flight_112" title=3D"Paninternational Flight 112">Paninternatio=
nal Flight 112</a></b>, a BAC One-Eleven flying from Hamburg, Germany, to M=
=C3=A1laga, Spain, suffers dual engine failure shortly after takeoff and cr=
ashes onto the motorway near Hamburg Airport, killing 22 of the 121 people =
on board.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British=
_European_Airways_Flight_706" title=3D"British European Airways Flight 706"=
>British European Airways Flight 706</a></b>, a Vickers Vanguard turboprop =
flying from London's Heathrow Airport to Salzburg, Austria, breaks up in mi=
d-air and crashes near Aarsele, Belgium, after suffering explosive decompre=
ssion; all 63 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_773" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 773">Aeroflot Flight 773</a></b>, a=
 Tupolev Tu-104, breaks up and crashes near Baranovo, Naro-Fominsky Distric=
t, Russia when a bomb placed in the cabin explodes; all 25 on board die.</l=
i>
<li>November 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1971_=
Indian_Ocean_Vickers_Viscount_crash" title=3D"1971 Indian Ocean Vickers Vis=
count crash">A Merpati Nusantara Vickers Viscount 828</a></b> crashes in th=
e Indian Ocean off the west coast of Sumatra, Indonesia, on approach to Tab=
ing Airport in Padang, due to poor visibility in bad weather; all 69 people=
 on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D._B.=
_Cooper" title=3D"D. B. Cooper">Northwest Orient Airlines Flight 305</a></b=
>, a Boeing 727 flying from Portland, Oregon, to Seattle, Washington, Unite=
d States, is hijacked by an unidentified person who parachutes from the air=
craft mid-flight after extorting US$200,000 of ransom money from the US gov=
ernment; the aircraft lands safely and all 41 on board are unharmed, but th=
e perpetrator is never apprehended.</li>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_2174" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 2174">Aeroflot Flight 2174</a></b>=
, an Antonov An-24, loses control and crashes on approach to Saratov Airpor=
t due to wing icing, killing all 57 on board.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LANSA=
_Flight_508" title=3D"LANSA Flight 508">LANSA Flight 508</a></b>, a Lockhee=
d L-188 Electra en route from Lima to Pucallpa, Peru, breaks apart in mid-a=
ir during a thunderstorm and crashes in the Amazon Rainforest; of the 92 on=
 board, the sole survivor is a German teenager who falls 2 miles (3.2&nbsp;=
km) strapped to her seat, and then walks for 10 days through the rainforest=
 before being rescued by local lumbermen.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1972">1972</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1972">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ibe=
ria_Airlines_Flight_602" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Iberia Airlines Fli=
ght 602">Iberia Airlines Flight 602</a></b>, a Sud Aviation SE 210 Caravell=
e flying from Valencia to Ibiza, crashes into a mountain while on approach =
to Ibiza Airport, killing all 104 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>January 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JAT_Fl=
ight_367" title=3D"JAT Flight 367">JAT Flight 367</a></b>, a McDonnell Doug=
las DC-9, suffers a bomb explosion in mid-air, killing 27 of the 28 on boar=
d; Vesna Vulovi=C4=87, the only survivor, is entered in the <i>Guinness Boo=
k of World Records</i> for surviving the longest fall without a parachute, =
over 33,000 feet (10,000&nbsp;m).</li>
<li>February 22=E2=80=9323 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Lufthansa_Flight_649" title=3D"Lufthansa Flight 649">Lufthansa Flight=
 649</a></b>, a Boeing 747 en route from Tokyo to Frankfurt, is hijacked du=
ring the Delhi=E2=80=93Athens leg and forced to divert to Aden, South Yemen=
, where all 182 passengers and crew are released in exchange for a $5 milli=
on ransom.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohawk_Ai=
rlines_Flight_405" title=3D"Mohawk Airlines Flight 405">Mohawk Airlines Fli=
ght 405</a></b>, a Fairchild F-27 flying from New York City to Albany, New =
York, crashes while descending to land at Albany County Airport, killing 16=
 of the 48 people on board and one on the ground.</li>
<li>March 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sterling=
_Airways_Flight_296" title=3D"Sterling Airways Flight 296">Sterling Airways=
 Flight 296</a></b>, a Sud Caravelle flying from Colombo, Ceylon, to Copenh=
agen, Denmark, crashes near Kalba in the United Arab Emirates due to pilot =
error; all 112 on board die in the worst air disaster in the history of the=
 UAE.</li>
<li>March 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EgyptAir=
_Flight_763" title=3D"EgyptAir Flight 763">EgyptAir Flight 763</a></b>, a M=
cDonnell Douglas DC-9 flying from Egypt to South Yemen, crashes on approach=
 to Aden International Airport, killing all 30 passengers and crew.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alitalia_Fl=
ight_112" title=3D"Alitalia Flight 112">Alitalia Flight 112</a></b>, a Doug=
las DC-8 operating a domestic flight from Rome to Palermo, Italy, crashes i=
nto Mount Longa some 3 miles (4.8&nbsp;km) southwest of its destination, ki=
lling all 115 passengers and crew on board; it remains the deadliest single=
-aircraft disaster in Italy.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabena_Flig=
ht_571" title=3D"Sabena Flight 571">Sabena Flight 571</a></b>, a Boeing 707=
 flying from Brussels to Tel Aviv, is hijacked by members of the Black Sept=
ember Organisation demanding the release of palaestinian prisoners by Israe=
l; during a commando raid the hijackers are killed or captured and one host=
age terminally injured, the others freed.</li>
<li>May 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_1491" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1491">Aeroflot Flight 1491</a></b>, an=
 Antonov An-10, suffers in-flight structural failure on approach to Kharkiv=
 Airport in Ukraine; all 122 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>May 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Air_=
Lines_Flight_9570" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 9570">Delta Air Lines Fl=
ight 9570</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9 operating as a training flight,=
 crashes while attempting to land at Greater Southwest International Airpor=
t in Fort Worth, Texas, United States, due to wake turbulence from a DC-10 =
that landed moments earlier; all four crew members are killed.</li>
<li>June 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_=
Airlines_Flight_96" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 96">American Airlines=
 Flight 96</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, suffers explosive depressuri=
sation when one of its cargo doors fails in mid-flight; the crew performs a=
n emergency landing at Detroit Metro Airport, Michigan, where all 67 on boa=
rd are evacuated safely.</li>
<li>June 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_Air=
lines_Flight_471" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines Flight 471"=
>Japan Airlines Flight 471</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8 en route from Bangkok, T=

 82 of the 87 on board and three people on the ground.</li>
<li>June 15 =E2=80=93 A carry-on suitcase bomb explodes on <b><a href=3D"ht=

t" title=3D"Cathay Pacific Flight 700Z">Cathay Pacific Flight 700Z</a></b>,=

 die.</li>

uropean_Airways_Flight_548" title=3D"British European Airways Flight 548">B=

rgoes a series of stalls due to pilot error, followed by a deep stall, and =
crashes near Staines, United Kingdom; all 118 on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prinair_F=

erto Rico, killing five of the 20 people on board.</li>
<li>June 29 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=

ollision">1972 Lake Winnebago mid-air collision</a></b>, North Central Airl=
ines Flight 290, a Convair CV-580, and Air Wisconsin Flight 671, a de Havil=

<li>July 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_Fli=

7 en route from San Francisco to Saigon, South Vietnam, is hijacked over th=

n Interflug Ilyushin Il-62 flying from East Germany to Bulgaria, crashes ne=

<li>September 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japa=

nal Airport; all 37 on board die.</li>

</li>

_Lines_Flight_404" title=3D"Japan Air Lines Flight 404">Japan Air Lines Fli=

iphol Airport in the Netherlands; one hijacker is killed and the flight's p=

<li>August 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=

 an Antonov An-24, crashes near Baku, Azerbaijan after striking a cable on =
an oil rig following engine failure, killing 56 of 64 on board. The acciden=
t remains the deadliest in Azerbaijan.</li>
<li>September 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World=
_Airways_Flight_802" title=3D"World Airways Flight 802">World Airways Fligh=
t 802</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8-63CF crashes on approach into Cold Bay Airpor=
t, Alaska. All six occupants are killed.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JAT_=
Airways_Flight_769" title=3D"JAT Airways Flight 769">JAT Airways Flight 769=
</a></b>, a Sud Aviation Caravelle, crashes into Mt. Maganik near Kola=C5=
=A1in, Montenegro, killing all 41 on board.</li>
<li>September 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texa=
s_International_Airlines_Flight_655" title=3D"Texas International Airlines =
Flight 655">Texas International Airlines Flight 655</a></b>, a Convair 600,=
 crashes into Black Fork Mountain while avoiding thunderstorms, killing all=
 11 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>September 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero=
flot_Flight_3932" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3932">Aeroflot Flight 3932</a></=
b>, a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes shortly after takeoff from Koltsovo Airport i=
n Sverdlovsk (now Yekaterinburg), Russia after the pilots became disorienta=
ted following electrical failure, killing all 108 on board.</li>
<li>October 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_964" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 964">Aeroflot Flight 964</a></b>, a=
 Tupolev Tu-104, crashes while on approach to Domodedovo International Airp=
ort, Moscow, Russia after the pilots became disorientated following electri=
cal failure, killing all 122 on board in the deadliest accident involving t=
he Tu-104.</li>
<li>November 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nation=
al_Airlines_Flight_27" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 27">National Airli=
nes Flight 27</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10 with 128 on board, suffers=
 an uncontained engine failure at 39,000 feet 65 miles southwest of Albuque=
rque, New Mexico. Debris from the engine punctures the fuselage and a passe=
nger is blown out of the aircraft, but the aircraft is able to land safely =
with no other casualties.</li>
<li>December 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_2022" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 2022">Aeroflot Flight 2022</a></b=
>, a Tupolev Tu-124, crashes near Karacharovo, Russia after entering a nose=
dive following a failure in the horizontal stabilizer, killing all 51 on bo=
ard.</li>
<li>December 17 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1973_Rome_airport_attacks_and_hijacking" title=3D"1973 Rome airport attac=
ks and hijacking">1973 Rome airport attacks and hijacking</a></b>, armed gu=
nmen kill two people in the terminal, then firebomb <b>Pan Am Flight 110</b=
>, a Boeing 707, killing 30 inside the aircraft. The gunmen then hijack <b>=
Lufthansa Flight 303</b>, a Boeing 737 en route to Munich, killing two more=
 before landing and surrendering in Kuwait.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1974">1974</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1974">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Com=

ommonwealth Commuter Flight 317</a></b>, a Beechcraft Model 99A, crashes sh=
ort of the runway on approach to Johnstown=E2=80=93Cambria County Airport, =
Pennsylvania following a premature descent, killing 12 of the 17 on board.<=
/li>

h_Airlines_Flight_301" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 301">Turkish Airlin=
es Flight 301</a></b>, a Fokker F28-1000, stalls and crashes after takeoff =
from Izmir Cumaovasi Airport due to wing icing; of the 73 on board, only se=
ven survive.</li>
<li>January 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am=
_Flight_806" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 806">Pan Am Flight 806</a></b>, a Boein=
g 707-320B, crashes on approach to Pago Pago International Airport, America=
n Samoa due to pilot error after encountering a microburst, killing 97 of 1=
01 on board.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_A=
irlines_Flight_981" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 981">Turkish Airlines =
Flight 981</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, crashes in the Ermenonville =
forest near Senlis, France, after the rear underfloor cargo door opens in m=
id-flight; all 346 on board die.</li>
<li>March 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sterling=
_Airways_Flight_901" title=3D"Sterling Airways Flight 901">Sterling Airways=
 Flight 901</a></b>, a Sterling Airways Sud Aviation Caravelle suffers land=
ing gear failure at Mehrabad International Airport; the right wing contacts=
 the runway, rupturing a fuel tank and starting a fire that kills 15 of 92 =
passengers; all four crew survive.</li>
<li>April 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Court_Li=
ne_Flight_95" title=3D"Court Line Flight 95">Court Line Flight 95</a></b>, =
a BAC One-Eleven, collides with a Piper Aztec on the runway at London Luton=
 Airport, killing the pilot of the Aztec; there are no casualties on board =
the One-Eleven, but the aircraft is substantially damaged; the Aztec is wri=
tten off.</li>
<li>April 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_F=
light_812" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 812">Pan Am Flight 812</a></b>, a Boeing =
707-320B, crashes into mountainous terrain 42.5 nautical miles (78.7&nbsp;k=
m) northwest of Denpasar, Bali due to instrument failure and pilot error, k=
illing all 107 on board.</li>
<li>April 27 =E2=80=93 An Aeroflot Ilyushin Il-18 <b><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/1974_Leningrad_Aeroflot_Il-18_crash" title=3D"1974 Lenin=
grad Aeroflot Il-18 crash">crashes</a></b> shortly after takeoff from Pulko=
vo Airport, Leningrad (now St. Petersburg), Russia due to loss of control f=
ollowing engine failure; all 109 on board die.</li>
<li>September 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_841_(1974)" title=3D"TWA Flight 841 (1974)">TWA Flight 841</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 707, breaks up after a bomb explodes in the cargo hold and plunges =
into the Ionian Sea, killing all 88 on board.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East=
ern_Air_Lines_Flight_212" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 212">Eastern Ai=
r Lines Flight 212</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes on approach t=
o Charlotte, North Carolina; 72 of 82 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>September 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_=
Vietnam_Flight_706" title=3D"Air Vietnam Flight 706">Air Vietnam Flight 706=
</a></b>, a Boeing 727, is hijacked and crashes in Phan Rang, Vietnam follo=
wing an aborted landing; all 75 on board die.</li>
<li>November 1 =E2=80=93 Aeroflot Flight 662, an Antonov An-2, <b><a href=

974 Surgut mid-air collision">collides in mid-air</a></b> with a Mil Mi-8 h=
elicopter near Surgut, Russia due to ATC errors, killing all 38 on board bo=
th aircraft.</li>
<li>November 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lufth=

> crashes shortly after takeoff in Nairobi, Kenya; 59 of 157 on board are k=
illed in the first crash of a Boeing 747.</li>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northw=
est_Airlines_Flight_6231" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Northwest Airlines=
 Flight 6231">Northwest Airlines Flight 6231</a></b>, a Boeing 727, stalls =
and crashes twelve minutes after takeoff from JFK International Airport, Ne=
w York due to wing icing caused by pilot error, killing the three crew.</li=
>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fl=
ight_514" title=3D"TWA Flight 514">TWA Flight 514</a></b>, a Boeing 727 inb=
ound to Dulles International Airport, crashes into Mount Weather in Bluemon=
t, Virginia, killing all 92 on board.</li>
<li>December 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin=
air_Flight_138" title=3D"Martinair Flight 138">Martinair Flight 138</a></b>=
, a Douglas DC-8 on a charter flight, crashes into a mountain shortly befor=
e landing, on approach to Katunayake, Sri Lanka, for a refueling stop; kill=
ing all aboard =E2=80=93 182 Indonesian hajj pilgrims bound for Mecca, and =
nine crew members.</li>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avens=
a_Flight_358" title=3D"Avensa Flight 358">Avensa Flight 358</a></b>, a McDo=
nnell Douglas DC-9, suffers dual engine failure after takeoff and crashes n=
ear Matur=C3=ADn, Venezuela, killing all 77 on board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gol=

 Flight 66</a></b>, a Boeing 727, encounters wind shear on final approach a=
nd strikes approach lights at John F. Kennedy International Airport, killin=
g 113 of 124 people on board.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agad=

 an Air Maroc-operated Boeing 707 owned by Royal Jordanian Airlines crashes=
 while on approach to Agadir, Morocco due to pilot error; all 188 on board =
die in the worst-ever accident involving the Boeing 707.</li>
<li>August 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C4%8CS=

8 passengers and crew on board die in the accident.</li>

r_Alaska_Flight_99" title=3D"Wien Air Alaska Flight 99">Wien Air Alaska Fli=
ght 99</a></b>, a Fairchild F-27, crashes into Seuvokuk Mountain, Alaska, w=
hile on approach to Gambell Airport, killing 10 of 32 on board.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter=

</b>, a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes while on approach to Leipzig, killing 27 of=
 34 on board.</li>

esia Flight 150</a></b>, a Fokker F-28 Fellowship, crashes while on approac=
h to Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II Airport in foggy weather; 25 of 61 on boar=

<li>September 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mal%=

></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes on approach near Lebanon, killing all 60 p=
eople on board.</li>
<li>October 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inex-A=

-Adria Aviopromet Flight 450</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes on =
approach in Prague suburb, killing 75 of 120 on board.</li>

an></h3>
<ul><li>January 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mid=

dle East Airlines Flight 438</a></b>, a Boeing 720, crashes in Saudi Arabia=
 when a bomb explodes in the forward baggage compartment, killing all 81 pe=

 a Tupolev Tu-124, crashes just after takeoff from Vnukovo Airport due to i=
nstrument failure, killing all 61 passengers and crew on board and one pers=
on on the ground.</li>

/li>

olev Tu-154, crashes into a mountainside on the island of Bioko in Equatori=
al Guinea for reasons unknown; all 45 on board die.</li>
<li>June 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Manila=

 a Lockheed L-188 Electra, crashes shortly after takeoff from NAS Agana, Gu=

on on the ground also dies when a car is struck by the aircraft.</li>
<li>June 6 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/197=
6_Sabah_Air_GAF_Nomad_crash" title=3D"1976 Sabah Air GAF Nomad crash">1976 =
Sabah Air GAF Nomad crash</a></b>, a GAF N-22B Nomad crashes into the sea o=
n approach into Kota Kinabalu International Airport, Malaysia. All 11 passe=
ngers and crew are killed. Several local political leaders were on board at=
 the time.</li>
<li>June 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation=
_Entebbe" title=3D"Operation Entebbe">Air France Flight 139</a></b>, an Air=
bus A300, is hijacked from Athens by two Palestinians and two Germans who d=
ivert the flight to Libya and then to Uganda, where the plane is met by pro=
-Palestinian forces from Idi Amin's government; Israeli troops eventually s=
torm the airport in Operation Entebbe, killing hijackers and Ugandan soldie=
rs and freeing all but three of the hostages; Israeli colonel Yonatan Netan=
yahu, brother of Benjamin Netanyahu, is also killed in the raid.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C4%8CSA_=
Flight_001" title=3D"=C4=8CSA Flight 001">=C4=8CSA Flight 001</a></b>, an I=
lyushin Il-18, crashes near Bratislava in Czechoslovakia, killing 76 of 78 =
people on board.</li>
<li>August 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SAETA_F=
light_232" title=3D"SAETA Flight 232">SAETA Flight 232</a></b>, a Vickers V=
iscount 785D, goes missing mid-route from Quito to Cuenca, Ecuador; all fou=
r crew members and 55 passengers are killed, but the scene remains undiscov=
ered for 26 years until October 2002, when climbers on the eastern face of =
the stratovolcano Chimborazo come upon the site.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1976_Anapa_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1976 Anapa mid-air collision">1976=
 Anapa mid-air collision</a></b>, <b>Aeroflot Flight 7957</b>, an Antonov A=
n-24, collides with <b>Aeroflot Flight C-31</b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40, over th=
e Black Sea off Anapa due to ATC and crew errors, killing all 70 on board b=
oth aircraft.</li>
<li>September 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1976=
_Zagreb_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1976 Zagreb mid-air collision">1976 Zag=
reb mid-air collision</a></b> between <b>British Airways Flight 476</b>, a =
Hawker Siddeley Trident, and <b>Inex-Adria Aviopromet Flight 550</b>, a McD=
onnell Douglas DC-9, near Zagreb, Yugoslavia, kills all 176 people on board=
 both aircraft.</li>
<li>September 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turk=

ines Flight 452</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes into a hillside near Karatep=

w die.</li>
<li>October 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cubana_=

ubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 455</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, is bombed by ant=

landing at Bombay Airport; all 95 passengers and crew on board are killed.<=
/li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olymp=

 Flight 830</a></b>, a NAMC YS-11A, crashes into a mountain in Greece in lo=
w visibility, killing all 50 on board.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=

>, a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes shortly after takeoff from Sheremetyevo Intern=
ational Airport due to crew disorientation following artificial horizon fai=
lure, killing all 73 on board.</li>
<li>December 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1977">1977</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D62" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1977">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Het_verongelukte_KLM-toeste=

<ul><li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ae=
roflot_Flight_3843" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3843">Aeroflot Flight 3843</a>=
</b>, a Tupolev Tu-104 operating a flight from Khabarovsk Novy Airport, Sov=
iet Union, to Almaty Airport in Kazakhstan, crashes in a field just short o=
f its destination due to an engine fire; all 90 people on board are killed.=
</li>
<li>January 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linjef=
lyg_Flight_618" title=3D"Linjeflyg Flight 618">Linjeflyg Flight 618</a></b>=
, a Skyline Vickers Viscount 838 operating a multi-leg domestic flight in S=
weden, crashes in the district of K=C3=A4lvesta, western Stockholm, due to =
atmospheric icing, killing all 22 people on board.</li>
<li>February 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_5003_(1977)" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 5003 (1977)">Aeroflot Flig=
ht 5003</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-18 operating a domestic flight in the weste=
rn Soviet Union, crashes due to pilot error after a missed approach to Mine=
ralnye Vody Airport, killing 77 of the 98 people on board.</li>
<li>March 27 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T=
enerife_airport_disaster" title=3D"Tenerife airport disaster">Tenerife airp=
ort disaster</a></b>, two Boeing 747s, KLM Flight 4805 and Pan Am Flight 17=
36, collide on the runway at Los Rodeos Airport in heavy fog; 583 of the 64=
4 people on board the two aircraft are killed in <b>the deadliest accident =
in the history of commercial aviation.</b></li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_=
Airways_Flight_242" title=3D"Southern Airways Flight 242">Southern Airways =
Flight 242</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9 flying from northwest Alabama =
to Atlanta, Georgia, crash lands on a highway near New Hope, Georgia, after=
 encountering dual engine failure in a thunderstorm; 63 of the 85 people on=
 board are killed, as well as nine on the ground.</li>
<li>April 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Ai=
r_Lines_Flight_1080" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 1080">Delta Air Lines =
Flight 1080</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1011 Tristar operating a domestic flight =
in California, United States, experiences a loss of pitch control during ta=
keoff from Los Angeles International Airport due to a malfunctioning elevat=
or; the aircraft is able to land safely with no casualties.</li>
<li>April 27 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1977_=
Aviateca_Convair_240_crash" title=3D"1977 Aviateca Convair 240 crash">Aviat=
eca Convair 240 crashes</a></b> shortly after taking off from La Aurora Int=
ernational Airport, Guatemala City, Guatemala, in Central America, due to a=
 maintenance error, killing all 28 people on board.</li>
<li>May 14 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1977_Dan=
-Air_Boeing_707_crash" title=3D"1977 Dan-Air Boeing 707 crash">Dan-Air Boei=
ng 707 crashes</a></b> near Lusaka Airport, Zambia, at the conclusion of a =
multi-leg flight from London's Heathrow Airport, via Athens and Nairobi, du=
e to structural failure; the one passenger and five crew members are killed=
.</li>
<li>May 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_331" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 331">Aeroflot Flight 331</a></b>, an Il=
yushin Il-62 operating a multi-leg flight from Moscow, Soviet Union, to Hav=
ana, Cuba, crashes due to pilot error while on approach to its destination,=
 Jos=C3=A9 Mart=C3=AD International Airport, killing all but two of the 70 =
people on board, plus one person on the ground.</li>
<li>July 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_2" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 2">Aeroflot Flight=
 B-2</a></b>, an Avia 14, crashes shortly after takeoff from Vitim Airport,=
 Russia due to pilot and ATC errors; of the 50 on board, only a passenger s=
urvives.</li>
<li>September 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japa=
n_Airlines_Flight_715" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines Flight=
 715">Japan Airlines Flight 715</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-8 operating=
 a multi-leg flight from Tokyo to Singapore, crashes into a hillside while =
on approach to Sultan Abdul Aziz Shah Airport in Malaysia due to pilot erro=
r, killing 34 of the 79 people on board.</li>
<li>September 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japa=
n_Airlines_Flight_472_(1977)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines=
 Flight 472 (1977)">Japan Airlines Flight 472</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas =
DC-8 bound for Tokyo, is hijacked by Japanese Red Army (JRA) militants shor=
tly after departing from Bombay, India, and forced to land in Dhaka, Bangla=
desh; the hijackers' demands are eventually met and all 151 passengers and =
crew are released unharmed.</li>
<li>October 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luftha=
nsa_Flight_181" title=3D"Lufthansa Flight 181">Lufthansa Flight 181</a></b>=
, a Boeing 737 flying from Mallorca to Germany, is hijacked over the Medite=
rranean Sea by members of the PFLP (a Palestinian revolutionary organizatio=
n) who murder the pilot; the aircraft eventually lands in Mogadishu where i=
t is stormed by German police commandos; three of the hijackers are killed,=
 the fourth is captured, and there are no other fatalities.</li>
<li>October 20 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lyny=
rd_Skynyrd_plane_crash" title=3D"Lynyrd Skynyrd plane crash">Convair CV-240=
 chartered by Lynyrd Skynyrd crashes</a></b> into a heavily wooded swamp in=
 Amite County, Mississippi, United States, while en route from Greenville, =
South Carolina, to Baton Rouge, Louisiana, due to fuel exhaustion; four of =
the 24 passengers and both crew members are killed.</li>
<li>November 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAP_P=
ortugal_Flight_425" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"TAP Portugal Flight 425"=
>TAP Portugal Flight 425</a></b>, a Boeing 727 operating a multi-leg flight=
 from Belgium to Portugal, plunges over a steep bank and bursts into flames=
 after overshooting the runway at Madeira Airport due to pilot error, killi=
ng 131 of the 164 people on board.</li>
<li>December 2 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1977=
_Libyan_Arab_Airlines_Tu-154_crash" title=3D"1977 Libyan Arab Airlines Tu-1=
54 crash">Libyan Arab Airlines Tupolev Tu-154 crashes</a></b> near Benghazi=
, Libya, due to fuel exhaustion, while en route from King Abdulaziz Interna=
tional Airport, Saudi Arabia, to Benina International Airport in Libya; 59 =
of the 165 people on board lose their lives.</li>
<li>December 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malays=
ian_Airline_System_Flight_653" title=3D"Malaysian Airline System Flight 653=
">Malaysian Airline System Flight 653</a></b>, a Boeing 737 operating a fli=
ght from Penang to Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, crashes into a swamp near Tanjun=
g Kupang, Johor, as a result of a failed hijacking attempt; all 100 people =
on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_I=
ndiana_Flight_216" title=3D"Air Indiana Flight 216">Air Indiana Flight 216<=
/a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 carrying the Purple Aces basketball team on a chart=
er flight from Evansville, Indiana, to Nashville, Tennessee, crashes shortl=
y after take-off due to overloading and pilot error, killing all 29 passeng=
ers and crew.</li>
<li>December 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Flight_2860" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 2860">United Airlin=
es Flight 2860</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-8 flying from San Francisco,=
 California, to Chicago, Illinois, in the United States, crashes in the Was=
atch mountain range in Utah, killing the three crew on board.</li>
<li>December 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SA_de=
_Transport_A%C3%A9rien_Flight_730" title=3D"SA de Transport A=C3=A9rien Fli=
ght 730">SA de Transport A=C3=A9rien Flight 730</a></b>, a Sud Aviation SE-=
210 Caravelle operating a flight from Geneva, Switzerland, to Madeira, Port=
ugal, crashes into the sea while on final approach to its destination due t=
o pilot error, killing 36 of the 57 people on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1978">1978</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 1978">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Nationalcrash.jpg" class=3D=

ta-file-height=3D"523"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magn=
