<ul><li>January 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air=
_India_Flight_855" title=3D"Air India Flight 855">Air India Flight 855</a><=
/b>, a Boeing 747, crashes into the Arabian Sea as a result of instrument m=
alfunction and pilot error, killing all 213 passengers and crew on board.</=
li>
<li>February 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacif=
ic_Western_Airlines_Flight_314" title=3D"Pacific Western Airlines Flight 31=
4">Pacific Western Airlines Flight 314</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, from Edmo=
nton crashes at Cranbrook Airport after one thrust reverser did not fully s=
tow following an aborted landing, killing 42 of the 49 people on board.</li=
>
<li>March 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continent=
al_Airlines_Flight_603" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 603">Continent=
al Airlines Flight 603</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, crashes on takeo=
ff from Los Angeles International Airport after a tire blows on the left ma=
in landing gear, causing it to collapse; of 200 on board, two die at the ti=
me and two others die of their injuries three months later.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1978_LA=
V_HS_748_accident" title=3D"1978 LAV HS 748 accident">L=C3=ADnea Aeropostal=
 Venezolana Hawker Siddeley HS 748</a></b> crashes on departure from <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sim%C3%B3n_Bol%C3%ADvar_International_Ai=
rport_(Venezuela)" title=3D"Sim=C3=B3n Bol=C3=ADvar International Airport (=
Venezuela)">Sim=C3=B3n Bol=C3=ADvar International Airport</a>, Venezuela du=
e to possible instrument failure; all 46 on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 16 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
978_Balkan_Bulgarian_Tupolev_Tu-134_crash" title=3D"1978 Balkan Bulgarian T=
upolev Tu-134 crash">1978 Balkan Bulgarian Tupolev Tu-134 crash</a></b>, a =
Tupolev Tu-134 crashes near the village of Gabare, Bulgaria, killing all 73=
 people on board.</li>
<li>April 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_A=
ir_Lines_Flight_902" title=3D"Korean Air Lines Flight 902">Korean Air Lines=
 Flight 902</a></b>, a Boeing 707, is shot down by Soviet fighter planes; t=
he plane crash-lands near the Soviet Union's border with Finland; two of th=
e 109 people on board are killed, the rest are subsequently released.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Ai=
rlines_Flight_193" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 193">National Airlines=
 Flight 193</a></b>, a Boeing 727, lands short on approach to Pensacola, Fl=
orida, United States, in Escambia Bay, as a result of pilot error; three pa=
ssengers out of 58 people on board drown.</li>
<li>May 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_6709" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 6709">Aeroflot Flight 6709</a></b>, a =
Tupolev Tu-154, crashes in a field near Maksatikha, Russia after all three =
engines failed due to fuel starvation, killing four of 134 on board.</li>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Canad=
a_Flight_189" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 189">Air Canada Flight 189</a></b>=
, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes on takeoff in Toronto, Ontario, Canada,=
 because of tire failure; Two of the 107 passengers and crew on board die.<=
/li>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helikopte=
r_Service_Flight_165" title=3D"Helikopter Service Flight 165">Helikopter Se=
rvice Flight 165</a></b>, a Sikorsky S-61, crashes into the North Sea while=
 en route to Statfjord oil field due to fatigue failure of a rotor, killing=
 all 18 on board.</li>
<li>August 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
LOT_Polish_Airlines_Flight_165_hijacking" title=3D"LOT Polish Airlines Flig=
ht 165 hijacking">LOT Polish Airlines Flight 165 hijacking</a></b>, two Eas=
t German citizens hijack a Tupolev Tu-134, and force it to land at Tempelho=
f Airport; there are no casualties to the 63 passengers on board.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_R=
hodesia_Flight_825" title=3D"Air Rhodesia Flight 825">Air Rhodesia Flight 8=
25</a></b> from Kariba to Salisbury is shot down by a SA-7 surface-to-air m=
issile; 18 of the 56 passengers initially survive the emergency landing, 10=
 are subsequently killed by Zimbabwe People's Revolutionary Army (ZIPRA) mi=
litants.</li>
<li>September 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paci=
fic_Southwest_Airlines_Flight_182" title=3D"Pacific Southwest Airlines Flig=
ht 182">Pacific Southwest Airlines Flight 182</a></b>, a Boeing 727, collid=
es with a Cessna 172 over San Diego, California, United States; all 135 abo=
ard the airliner, both pilots of the Cessna, and seven people on the ground=
 are killed, making this the worst aviation disaster in California history,=
 and the deadliest <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mid-air_collisi=
on" title=3D"Mid-air collision">mid-air collision</a> in <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America" title=3D"North America">North America=
</a>.</li>
<li>October 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_1080" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1080">Aeroflot Flight 1080</a></b>,=
 a Yakovlev Yak-40, crashes shortly after takeoff from Koltsovo Airport due=
 to engine failure caused by ice ingestion, killing all 38 on board.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icela=
ndic_Airlines_Flight_001" title=3D"Icelandic Airlines Flight 001">Icelandic=
 Airlines Flight 001</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8 on a charter flight, crashes i=
nto a coconut plantation while on approach to Katunayake, Sri Lanka, for a =
refueling stop; 183 out of 262 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alita=
lia_Flight_4128" title=3D"Alitalia Flight 4128">Alitalia Flight 4128</a></b=
>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9-32, crashes into the Tyrrhenian Sea when on app=
roach to Palermo International Airport in Palermo, Italy. Of the 129 passen=
gers and crew, 108 die.</li>
<li>December 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Flight_173" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 173">United Airlines=
 Flight 173</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, runs out of fuel while circling near P=
ortland, Oregon, United States, as the crew investigates a light indicating=
 a problem with the landing gear; the plane crashes in a suburban area dama=
ging two unoccupied houses, killing 10 and injuring 24 of the 181 on board.=
</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1979">1979</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D64" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1979">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Va=
rig_Flight_967" title=3D"Varig Flight 967">Varig Flight 967</a></b>, a Boei=
ng 707 bound for Rio de Janeiro=E2=80=93Gale=C3=A3o International Airport, =
disappears over the Pacific Ocean 125 miles (201&nbsp;km) after takeoff fro=
m Narita International Airport; the cause for the disappearance remains unk=
nown, as neither survivors (six-man flight crew) nor wreckage have ever bee=
n found.</li>
<li>February 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_R=
hodesia_Flight_827" title=3D"Air Rhodesia Flight 827">Air Rhodesia Flight 8=
27</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount on a flight between Kariba and Salisbury, is=
 shot down by Zimbabwe People's Revolutionary Army militants using a SA-7 (=
Strela 2) surface-to-air missile shortly after takeoff in similar circumsta=
nces to <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Rhodesia_Flight_825=
" title=3D"Air Rhodesia Flight 825">Flight 825</a></b> five months earlier;=
 all 55 passengers and four crew are killed.</li>
<li>February 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_N=
ew_Zealand_Flight_4374" title=3D"Air New Zealand Flight 4374">Air New Zeala=
nd Flight 4374</a></b>, a Fokker F-27 Friendship crashes while on approach =
into Auckland International Airport, New Zealand. The captain and one passe=
nger are killed.</li>
<li>March 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alia_Roy=
al_Jordanian_Airlines_Flight_600" title=3D"Alia Royal Jordanian Airlines Fl=
ight 600">Alia Royal Jordanian Airlines Flight 600</a></b>, a Boeing 727 cr=
ashes following a missed approach at Doha International Airport, Qatar; 44 =
of the 64 on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot=
_Flight_1691" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1691">Aeroflot Flight 1691</a></b>, =
a Tupolev Tu-104, crashes near Vnukovo International Airport while attempti=
ng to make an emergency landing after a fire alarm is reported, killing 58 =
of 119 on board.</li>
<li>March 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quebecai=
r_Flight_255" title=3D"Quebecair Flight 255">Quebecair Flight 255</a></b>, =
a Fairchild F-27 bound for Montreal, crashes minutes after takeoff from Que=
bec City as it was attempting to return to the airport following the explos=
ion of its number 2 engine, killing 17 of the 24 people on board.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_841_(1979)" title=3D"TWA Flight 841 (1979)">TWA Flight 841</a></b>, a Boe=
ing 727, goes into a dive over Saginaw, Michigan, following the loss of the=
 number 7 slat; despite the loss of 34,000 feet (10,000&nbsp;m) in altitude=
 within 63 seconds, all 89 passengers and crew survive an emergency landing=
 at Detroit after the first officer regains control of the plane at 5,000 f=
eet (1,500&nbsp;m).</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_A=
irlines_Flight_191" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 191">American Airline=
s Flight 191</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, crashes upon takeoff from =
O'Hare International Airport after its left engine detaches from the wing, =
killing all 271 on board and two on the ground in the worst single-aircraft=
 accident on U.S. soil.</li>
<li>May 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Downeast_F=
light_46" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Downeast Flight 46">Downeast Fligh=
t 46</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes on approach i=
nto Knox County Regional Airport, Maine. 17 of the 18 passengers and crew a=
re killed.</li>
<li>June 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_New_E=
ngland_Flight_248" title=3D"Air New England Flight 248">Air New England Fli=
ght 248</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes near Camp =
Greenough, Massachusetts, while on approach to Barnstable Municipal Airport=
, killing the pilot.</li>
<li>July 11 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1979_Ga=
ruda_Fokker_F28_crash" title=3D"1979 Garuda Fokker F28 crash">Garuda Indone=
sia Fokker F28 strikes a volcano</a></b> on approach to Medan Airport, Indo=
nesia, killing all 61 on board.</li>
<li>July 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan-Air_F=
light_0034" title=3D"Dan-Air Flight 0034">Dan-Air Flight 0034</a></b>, a Ha=
wker Siddeley HS 748, fails to become airborne at Sumburgh Airport, Scotlan=
d, due to a maintenance error, killing 17 of 44 on board.</li>
<li>August 11 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/197=
9_Dniprodzerzhynsk_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1979 Dniprodzerzhynsk mid-ai=
r collision">1979 Dniprodzerzhynsk mid-air collision</a></b> between two Ae=
roflot Tupolev Tu-134s kills 178.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_5484" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 5484">Aeroflot Flight 5484</a></b>,=
 a Tupolev Tu-124, breaks up in mid-air after experiencing loss of control =
due to unexplained release of the flaps, killing all 63 people aboard.</li>
<li>October 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swissai=
r_Flight_316" title=3D"Swissair Flight 316">Swissair Flight 316</a></b>, a =
Douglas DC-8-62 crashes after overrunning the runway at Athens-Ellinikon In=
ternational Airport, killing 14 of the 154 passengers and crew on board.</l=
i>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wester=
n_Airlines_Flight_2605" title=3D"Western Airlines Flight 2605">Western Airl=
ines Flight 2605</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, strikes a vehicle on a=
 closed runway in dense fog at Mexico City, Mexico; 72 die.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_444" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 444">American Ai=
rlines Flight 444</a></b>, a Boeing 727, takes off with a bomb planted in t=
he cargo hold by the Unabomber. The bomb fails to detonate, giving off larg=
e quantities of smoke. Twelve passengers are treated for smoke inhalation, =
but all 78 on board survive.</li>
<li>November 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIA_F=
light_740" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"PIA Flight 740">Pakistan Internat=
ional Airlines Flight 740</a></b>, a Boeing 707, crashes after a fire in th=
e cabin in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia; all 145 passengers and 11 crew die.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_N=
ew_Zealand_Flight_901" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Air New Zealand Fligh=
t 901">Air New Zealand Flight 901</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, colli=
des with Mount Erebus, Antarctica, during a sightseeing flight, killing all=
 257 people on board; this crash is also known as the Mount Erebus Disaster=
.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/197=
9_Turkish_Airlines_Ankara_crash" title=3D"1979 Turkish Airlines Ankara cras=
h">Turkish Airlines Fokker F28 crashes into a hillside</a></b> near Kuyumcu=
k=C3=B6y, Ankara, Turkey, while on approach to Esenbo=C4=9Fa Airport; of th=
e 45 on board, only four survive.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1980s">1980s</span><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_in=
volving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D65" title=3D"Ed=
it section: 1980s">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></h2>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1980">1980</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D66" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1980">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Saudia_163_close-up.jpg" cl=
ass=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/c=
ommons/thumb/5/59/Saudia_163_close-up.jpg/220px-Saudia_163_close-up.jpg" de=
coding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"144" class=3D"thumbimage" data-fil=
e-width=3D"306" data-file-height=3D"200"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption">=
<div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Saudia=
_163_close-up.jpg" class=3D"internal" title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>The burnt=
 out remains of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudia_Flight_163"=
 title=3D"Saudia Flight 163">Saudia Flight 163</a>.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ir=
an_Air_Flight_291" title=3D"Iran Air Flight 291">Iran Air Flight 291</a></b=
>, a Boeing 727, crashes into the Alborz Mountains near Tehran, Iran, amid =
a snowstorm on approach to Mehrabad International Airport; killing all 128 =
people on board.</li>
<li>February 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advan=
ce_Airlines_Flight_4210" title=3D"Advance Airlines Flight 4210">Advance Air=
lines Flight 4210</a></b>, a Beechcraft Super King Air 200, crashes shortly=
 after takeoff from Sydney Airport, following failure of one engine due to =
water in the fuel, killing all 13 people on board.</li>
<li>March 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOT_Flig=
ht_7" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LOT Flight 7">LOT Polish Airlines Flig=
ht 007</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-62, crashes near Warsaw, Poland, after the N=
o. 2 engine disintegrates and severs the elevator and rudder control lines;=
 all 87 on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transbra=
sil_Flight_303" title=3D"Transbrasil Flight 303">Transbrasil Flight 303</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 727, crashes into a hill near Florian=C3=B3polis, Brazil, ki=
lling 55 of 58 on board.</li>
<li>April 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan-Air_=
Flight_1008" title=3D"Dan-Air Flight 1008">Dan-Air Flight 1008</a></b>, a B=
oeing 727, crashes into a mountain near Tenerife, Spain, killing all 138 pa=
ssengers and eight crew on board.</li>
<li>April 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_Air=
ways_Flight_231" title=3D"Thai Airways Flight 231">Thai Airways Flight 231<=
/a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 748, crashes while on approach to Don Mueang =
International Airport, Bangkok, Thailand, in severe weather, killing 44 of =
53 on board.</li>
<li>June 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Wisco=
nsin_Flight_965" title=3D"Air Wisconsin Flight 965">Air Wisconsin Flight 96=
5</a></b>, a Swearingen Metro II, crashes after a catastrophic engine failu=
re in poor weather en route to Lincoln Municipal Airport, Nebraska. 13 of t=
he 15 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>June 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itavia_Fl=
ight_870" title=3D"Itavia Flight 870">Itavia Flight 870</a></b>, a McDonnel=
l Douglas DC-9, crashes into the Tyrrhenian Sea near Italy, killing all 81 =
people on board.</li>
<li>July 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_4225" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 4225">Aeroflot Flight 4225</a></b>, a =
Tupolev Tu-154, crashes shortly after takeoff from Almaty International Air=
port, killing all 163 people on board.</li>
<li>August 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudia_=
Flight_163" title=3D"Saudia Flight 163">Saudia Flight 163</a></b>, a Lockhe=
ed L-1011 Tristar, lands at King Khalid International Airport in Riyadh, Sa=
udi Arabia, when a fire breaks out on board; the evacuation of the plane is=
 delayed and all 301 on board die.</li>
<li>September 12 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Florida_Commuter_Airlines_crash" title=3D"Florida Commuter Airlines cras=
h">Florida Commuter Airlines crash</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3 ditches into the=
 Atlantic Ocean near the Bahamas, killing all 34 on board.</li>
<li>November 3 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Latin_Carga_Convair_CV-880_crash" title=3D"Latin Carga Convair CV-880 cras=
h">Latin Carga Convair CV-880 crash</a></b>, a Convair CV-880 crashes short=
ly after taking off from Caracas Airport, Venezuela. All four crew members =
are killed.</li>
<li>November 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korea=
n_Air_Flight_015" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 015">Kor=
ean Air Flight 015</a></b>, a Boeing 747, crashes on landing at Gimpo Inter=
national Airport. 15 of the 226 passengers and crew on board are killed.</l=
i>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi=
a_Flight_162" title=3D"Saudia Flight 162">Saudia Flight 162</a></b>, a Lock=
heed L-1011 Tristar, suffers an explosive decompression over Qatar, killing=
 two passengers who are blown out of the aircraft; the cause is traced to a=
 fatigue failure of a main landing gear wheel flange.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1981">1981</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D67" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1981">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>March 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garu=
da_Indonesia_Flight_206" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 206">Garuda Indon=
esia Flight 206</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9, is hijacked by Komando Jihad, the =
pilot is killed; all others survive.</li>
<li>May 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aer_Lingus_=
Flight_164" title=3D"Aer Lingus Flight 164">Aer Lingus Flight 164</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737, is hijacked while on approach to London Heathrow Airport. The=
 hijacker demanded to be taken to Iran. The plane landed at Le Touquet =E2=
=80=93 C=C3=B4te d'Opale Airport. After a nearly 10-hour stand-off the hija=
cker was arrested. All 108 survive.</li>
<li>May 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austral_L%C=
3%ADneas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_901" title=3D"Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas F=
light 901">Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 901</a></b>, a BAC One-El=
even, crashes near Aeroparque Jorge Newbery after losing control in a thund=
erstorm, killing all 31 on board.</li>
<li>June 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_498" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 498">Aeroflot Flight 498</a></b>, an I=
lyushin Il-14, crashes into a mountain on the Holy Nose Peninsula in Lake B=
aikal due to crew error, killing all 48 on board.</li>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan-Air_F=
light_240" title=3D"Dan-Air Flight 240">Dan-Air Flight 240</a></b>, a Hawke=
r Siddeley HS 748, crashes near Nailstone, Leicestershire, due to failure o=
f the baggage door, causing rapid decompression and loss of control; all th=
ree crew on board die.</li>
<li>July 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1981_Arme=
nia_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1981 Armenia mid-air collision">A Soviet Ai=
r Defence Forces Sukhoi SU-15 collides</a></b> with an Argentine Canadair C=
L-44 operating an international cargo flight between Iran and Cyprus; the S=
U-15 pilot ejects and survives the incident, but all four occupants of the =
CL-44 are killed.</li>
<li>July 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somali_Ai=
rlines_Flight_40" title=3D"Somali Airlines Flight 40">Somali Airlines Fligh=
t 40</a></b>, a Fokker F27 Friendship, crashes shortly after takeoff from M=
ogadishu International Airport. All 50 passengers and crew on board are kil=
led.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeromexic=
o_Flight_230" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeromexico Flight 230">Aeromex=
ico Flight 230</a></b>, a DC-9, makes a hard landing at Chihuahua Airport, =
breaks up and a fire breaks out, killing 32 of the 66 people on board.</li>
<li>August 13 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
1981_Bristow_Helicopters_Westland_Wessex_crash" title=3D"1981 Bristow Helic=
opters Westland Wessex crash">G-ASWI North Sea ditching</a></b>, a Bristow =
Helicopters Westland Wessex suffers engine failure and ditches in the North=
 Sea, killing all 13 on board.</li>
<li>August 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far_Eas=
tern_Air_Transport_Flight_103" title=3D"Far Eastern Air Transport Flight 10=
3">Far Eastern Air Transport Flight 103</a></b>, a Boeing 737, disintegrate=
s during flight and crashes near Taipei, Taiwan; severe corrosion in the fu=
selage structure leads to explosive decompression and disintegration at hig=
h altitude; all 110 on board are killed.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_811" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 811">Aeroflot Flight 811</a></b>, an=
 Antonov An-24, collides in mid-air with a Soviet Air Force Tupolev Tu-16 o=
ver the Zavitinsky District, Russia, killing 31 of 32 on board the An-24 an=
d all six on board the Tu-16.</li>
<li>August 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeropes=
ca_Colombia_Flight_221" title=3D"Aeropesca Colombia Flight 221">Aeropesca C=
olombia Flight 221</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, flies into Mount Santa Elen=
a, killing all 50 people on board.</li>
<li>September 22 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Air_=
Lines_Flight_935" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 935">Eastern Air Lines =
Flight 935</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1011 TriStar, makes an emergency landing a=
fter engine No. 2 explodes severing 3 out of 4 hydraulic lines, all 201 occ=
upants on board survive.</li>
<li>September 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indi=
an_Airlines_Flight_423" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 423">Indian Airline=
s Flight 423</a></b>, a Boeing 737 operating a domestic flight from Delhi t=
o Amritsar in India, is hijacked by Sikh extremists and forced to land in L=
ahore, Pakistan, where special forces storm the aircraft; there are no fata=
lities.</li>
<li>October 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NLM_Cit=
yHopper_Flight_431" title=3D"NLM CityHopper Flight 431">NLM CityHopper Flig=
ht 431</a></b>, a Fokker F28 Fellowship, is destroyed in flight by a tornad=
o near Rotterdam, killing all 17 people on board.</li>
<li>November 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_3603" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3603">Aeroflot Flight 3603</a></b=
>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes while attempting to land at Noril'sk Airport d=
ue to crew error and CFIT, killing 99 of the 167 passengers and crew on boa=
rd.</li>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inex-A=
dria_Aviopromet_Flight_1308" title=3D"Inex-Adria Aviopromet Flight 1308">In=
ex-Adria Aviopromet Flight 1308</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-81, crashes=
 in the mountains while approaching Campo dell'Oro Airport in Ajaccio, Cors=
ica, killing all 180 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1982">1982</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D68" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1982">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wider%C3%B8e_Flight_933_ver=
tical_stablizer_2.png" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.=
wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Wider%C3%B8e_Flight_933_vertical=
_stablizer_2.png/220px-Wider%C3%B8e_Flight_933_vertical_stablizer_2.png" de=
coding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"323" class=3D"thumbimage" data-fil=
e-width=3D"304" data-file-height=3D"446"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption">=
<div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wider%=
C3%B8e_Flight_933_vertical_stablizer_2.png" class=3D"internal" title=3D"Enl=
arge"></a></div>Vertical stabilizer found on crash site of <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wider%C3%B8e_Flight_933" title=3D"Wider=C3=B8e Fli=
ght 933">Wider=C3=B8e Flight 933</a>.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ai=
r_Florida_Flight_90" title=3D"Air Florida Flight 90">Air Florida Flight 90<=
/a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into the frozen Potomac River after takeoff =
from Washington National Airport, Virginia, United States; five on board su=
rvive; 74 on board and four on the ground die, including one initial surviv=
or who dies after ensuring that the other crash survivors are rescued from =
the frozen river.</li>
<li>January 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_=
Airways_Flight_30H" title=3D"World Airways Flight 30H">World Airways Flight=
 30H</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, overshoots the runway at Boston, M=
assachusetts, United States; two passengers are reported missing.</li>
<li>February 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_=
Airlines_Flight_350" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines Flight 3=
50">Japan Airlines Flight 350</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8-61, crashes on approa=
ch to Tokyo International Airport (Haneda), Japan; of the 166 passengers an=
d eight crew, 24 passengers are killed.</li>
<li>March 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wider%C3=
%B8e_Flight_933" title=3D"Wider=C3=B8e Flight 933">Wider=C3=B8e Flight 933<=
/a></b>, a de Havilland Canada Twin Otter, crashes into the Barents Sea nea=
r Mehamn, killing all 15 on board; this accident sparked conspiracy theorie=
s in Norway.</li>
<li>March 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
982_Garuda_Fokker_F28_crash" title=3D"1982 Garuda Fokker F28 crash">1982 Ga=
ruda Fokker F28 crash</a></b>, the Fokker F28 overruns the runway in bad we=
ather at Tanjung Karang-Branti Airport; all 27 are killed when the aircraft=
 bursts into flames.</li>
<li>March 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeropesc=
a_Colombia_Flight_217" title=3D"Aeropesca Colombia Flight 217">Aeropesca Co=
lombia Flight 217</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount, hits a mountain in Colombia;=
 all 21 on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAAC_Fli=
ght_3303" title=3D"CAAC Flight 3303">CAAC Flight 3303</a></b>, a Hawker Sid=
deley Trident, crashes into a mountain near Yangsuo while on approach to Gu=
ilin Liangjiang International Airport, China, in heavy weather; all 112 on =
board die.</li>
<li>June 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VASP_Fligh=
t_168" title=3D"VASP Flight 168">VASP Flight 168</a></b>, a Boeing 727, cra=
shes into a hillside in Brazil, killing all 137 on board.</li>
<li>June 12 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1982_TA=
BA_Fairchild_FH-227_accident" title=3D"1982 TABA Fairchild FH-227 accident"=
>TABA Fairchild FH-227 crashes</a></b> at Tabatinga Airport, Brazil; all 44=
 on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India=
_Flight_403" title=3D"Air India Flight 403">Air India Flight 403</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 707, crashes at Sahar International Airport in Bombay, India, while=
 landing during a heavy rainstorm; 15 of 99 passengers and two of 12 crew a=
re killed.</li>
<li>June 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_A=
irways_Flight_009" title=3D"British Airways Flight 009">British Airways Fli=
ght 009</a></b>, a Boeing 747-200, flies through a cloud of volcanic ash so=
uth of Java; all engines fail in flight, forcing the plane to glide; the cr=
ew is able to restart the engines and make a safe landing.</li>
<li>June 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_8641" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 8641">Aeroflot Flight 8641</a></b>, a=
 Yakovlev Yak-42, breaks up in mid-air and crashes near Mozyr, Belarus due =
to a failure in the jackscrew mechanism caused by metal fatigue, killing al=
l 132 on board in the first loss of and the deadliest accident involving th=
e Yak-42. The crash remains the worst in Belarus.</li>
<li>July 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_411" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 411">Aeroflot Flight 411</a></b>, an Il=
yushin Il-62, crashes after takeoff from Sheremetyevo International Airport=
; all 90 on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_Fli=
ght_759" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 759">Pan Am Flight 759</a></b>, a Boeing 72=
7, crashes in Kenner, Louisiana, United States, shortly after takeoff; all =
145 on board and eight people on the ground are killed.</li>
<li>August 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_Am_=
Flight_830" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 830">Pan Am Flight 830</a></b>, a bomb p=
laced under a seat cushion explodes aboard a Boeing 747-100 flying from Tok=
yo, Japan to Honolulu, Hawaii, killing one passenger. The plane makes an em=
ergency landing in Honolulu.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 An Aerol=C3=ADneas C=C3=B3ndor de Havilland Canad=
a DHC-4 Caribou <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1982_Aerocondor=
_DHC-4_Caribou_accident" title=3D"1982 Aerocondor DHC-4 Caribou accident">f=
lies into high ground</a></b> in the Andes, Ecuador; all 44 on board are ki=
lled.</li>
<li>September 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Span=
tax_Flight_995" title=3D"Spantax Flight 995">Spantax Flight 995</a></b>, a =
McDonnell Douglas DC-10, is destroyed by a fire after an aborted takeoff at=
 M=C3=A1laga Airport, Spain; 50 of the 294 on board die.</li>
<li>September 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero=
flot_Flight_343" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 343">Aeroflot Flight 343</a></b>,=
 an Ilyushin Il-62, veers off the runway while landing at <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxembourg_Findel_Airport" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Luxembourg Findel Airport">Luxembourg Findel Airport</a>, killing se=
ven of 77 on board.</li>
<li>December 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerono=
r_Flight_304" title=3D"Aeronor Flight 304">Aeronor Flight 304</a></b>, a Fa=
irchild F-27, crashes near La Florida Airport, Chile; all 46 on board are k=
illed.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAAC_=
Flight_2311" title=3D"CAAC Flight 2311">CAAC Flight 2311</a></b>, an Ilyush=
in Il-18, catches fire before landing at Baiyun Airport in Guangzhou, China=
, resulting 25 deaths of 69 on board though it successfully lands on the ru=
nway.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1983">1983</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D69" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1983">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Air_Canada_797_aft_lavatory=
.jpg" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wik=
ipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Air_Canada_797_aft_lavatory.jpg/220px-Air_Canada_=
797_aft_lavatory.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"165" class=
=3D"thumbimage" data-file-width=3D"727" data-file-height=3D"544"></a>  <div=
 class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/File:Air_Canada_797_aft_lavatory.jpg" class=3D"internal" title=
=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>Fire damage in the aft lavatory, the point of origin=
 of the fire on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Canada_Flight_=
797" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 797">Air Canada Flight 797</a>.</div></div>=
</div>
<ul><li>January 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Un=
ited_Airlines_Flight_2885" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 2885">United Air=
lines Flight 2885</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8-54F, crashes shortly after taking=
 off from Detroit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport, Michigan. All three cr=
ew members are killed.</li>
<li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkis=
h_Airlines_Flight_158" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 158">Turkish Airlin=
es Flight 158</a></b>, a Boeing 727, lands about 50 metres (160&nbsp;ft) sh=
ort of the runway at Ankara Esenbo=C4=9Fa Airport, Turkey, in driving snow,=
 breaks up and catches fire; 47 passengers are killed, all seven crew and 1=
3 passengers survive the accident with injuries.</li>
<li>March 11 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
983_Avensa_Douglas_DC-9_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1983 Avensa D=
ouglas DC-9 crash">1983 Avensa Douglas DC-9 crash</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9 c=
rashes at Barquisimeto Airport, Venezuela, killing 22 passengers and one cr=
ew member.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Air=
_Lines_Flight_855" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 855">Eastern Air Lines=
 Flight 855</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1011 Tristar, loses power from all engine=
s 30 minutes after takeoff from Miami International Airport; the pilot is a=
ble to return to Miami after restarting one engine; no casualties are repor=
ted on board.</li>
<li>June 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Canada=
_Flight_797" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 797">Air Canada Flight 797</a></b>,=
 a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, catches fire during flight over Kentucky; 23 of =
46 passengers die from smoke inhalation even after the crew successfully la=
nds the aircraft at the Cincinnati airport in northern Kentucky.</li>
<li>June 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reeve_Aleu=
tian_Airways_Flight_8" title=3D"Reeve Aleutian Airways Flight 8">Reeve Aleu=
tian Airways Flight 8</a></b>,  Lockheed L-188C Electra; one of the propell=
ers broke away from its engine and struck the fuselage, damaging the flight=
 controls.  The pilots were able to make a successful emergency landing.</l=
i>
<li>July 1 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1983_Cho=
sonminhang_Il-62_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1983 Chosonminhang I=
l-62 crash">Chosonminhang Ilyushin Il-62 crashes</a></b> in mountainous ter=
rain near Lab=C3=A9, Guinea, killing all 23 on board.</li>
<li>July 11 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAME_73=
7-200_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"TAME 737-200 crash">TAME Boeing=
 737-200 crashes</a></b> into a hill near Cuenca, Ecuador, killing all 119 =
on board.</li>
<li>July 16 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1983_Br=
itish_Airways_Sikorsky_S-61_crash" title=3D"1983 British Airways Sikorsky S=
-61 crash">British Airways Sikorsky S-61 helicopter crashes</a></b> into th=
e sea off the Isles of Scilly; 20 of 26 people on board die, in the worst h=
elicopter accident in the United Kingdom to date and results in a review of=
 helicopter safety.</li>
<li>July 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_Gli=
der" title=3D"Gimli Glider">Air Canada Flight 143</a></b>, a Boeing 767, ru=
ns out of fuel above Manitoba because of a miscalculation; the crew success=
fully glides the aircraft to a safe landing at a former Air Force base (and=
 current drag strip) at Gimli, Manitoba; the aircraft becomes known as the =
<i>Gimli Glider</i>.</li>
<li>August 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_5463" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 5463">Aeroflot Flight 5463</a></b>,=
 a Tupolev Tu-134A, crashes into a mountain while approaching Alma-Ata Airp=
ort, killing all 90 on board.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korea=
n_Air_Lines_Flight_007" title=3D"Korean Air Lines Flight 007">Korean Air Li=
nes Flight 007</a></b>, a Boeing 747, is shot down by Soviet fighter planes=
 near Sakhalin and Moneron Island after straying into Soviet airspace; all =
269 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>September 14 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/1983_Guilin_Airport_collision" title=3D"1983 Guilin Airport collision">1=
983 Guilin Airport collision</a></b>, a PLAAF <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Harbin_H-5" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Harbin H-5">Harbin H=
-5</a> bomber collides with a CAAC Hawker Siddeley Trident 2E as it taxies =
for takeoff at Guilin Qifengling Airport, China. 11 of the 106 occupants ab=
oard the Trident are killed. It is unknown how many casualties, if any, occ=
urred aboard the Harbin H-5.</li>
<li>September 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gulf=
_Air_Flight_771" title=3D"Gulf Air Flight 771">Gulf Air Flight 771</a></b>,=
 a Boeing 737, crashes near Mina Jebel Ali, United Arab Emirates, after a b=
omb planted by the Abu Nidal Organization detonates on board; all 112 peopl=
e on board die.</li>
<li>October 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Il=
linois_Flight_710" title=3D"Air Illinois Flight 710">Air Illinois Flight 71=
0</a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 748, crashes near Pinckneyville, Illinois, =
due to electrical problems. All 10 passengers and crew on board are killed.=
</li>
<li>November 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1983_T=
AAG_Angola_Airlines_Boeing_737_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1983 T=
AAG Angola Airlines Boeing 737 crash">TAAG Angola Airlines Flight 462</a>,<=
/b> a Boeing 737-200, is shot down just after takeoff from Lubango Airport;=
 all 130 on board die.</li>
<li>November 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_6833" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 6833">Aeroflot Flight 6833</a></b=
>, a Tupolev Tu-134, is hijacked by seven Georgians attempting to defect fr=
om the Soviet Union; the aircraft is stormed by Alpha Group who arrest four=
 hijackers; three are executed while the fourth receives a jail sentence; o=
f the 71 on board (including the hijackers), eight die; the aircraft is wri=
tten off.</li>
<li>November 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avian=
ca_Flight_011" title=3D"Avianca Flight 011">Avianca Flight 011</a></b>, a B=
oeing 747, strikes a hill because of a navigational error while attempting =
to land in Madrid, Spain; of the 192 passengers and crew aboard, 11 survive=
.</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Madrid_runway_disaster" title=3D"Madrid runway disaster">Madrid runway dis=
aster</a></b>, <b>Iberia Flight 350</b>, a Boeing 727, collides with <b>Avi=
aco Flight 134</b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, on a runway at Madrid=E2=80=
=93Barajas Airport; 51 people aboard the Boeing 727 and all 42 people aboar=
d the DC-9 are killed.</li>
<li>December 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malay=
sian_Airline_System_Flight_684" title=3D"Malaysian Airline System Flight 68=
4">Malaysian Airline System Flight 684</a></b>, an Airbus A300 crashes at K=
uala Lumpur Airport in Malaysia. There are no fatalities of the 247 people =
on board.</li>
<li>December 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ozark=
_Air_Lines_Flight_650" title=3D"Ozark Air Lines Flight 650">Ozark Air Lines=
 Flight 650</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, collides with a snow plow in=
 Sioux Falls, South Dakota; all on board survive, however the driver of the=
 snow plow is killed.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_601" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 601">Aeroflot Flight 601</a></b>, =
an Antonov An-24, crashes on approach to Leshukonskoye Airport due to pilot=
 error, killing 44 of 49 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1984">1984</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D70" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1984">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 10 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
1984_Balkan_Bulgarian_Tupolev_Tu-134_crash" title=3D"1984 Balkan Bulgarian =
Tupolev Tu-134 crash">Balkan Bulgarian Tupolev Tu-134</a></b> crashed into =
a forest near Sofia, Bulgaria, during a snowstorm killing all 50 people on =
board.</li>
<li>February 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scand=
inavian_Airlines_System_Flight_901" title=3D"Scandinavian Airlines System F=
light 901">Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 901</a></b>, a McDonnell Dou=
glas DC-10, crashes into a ditch after overshooting the runway at John F. K=
ennedy Airport, New York, due to pilot error; all 177 passengers and crew o=
nboard survive the incident.</li>
<li>March 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_=
Western_Airlines_Flight_501" title=3D"Pacific Western Airlines Flight 501">=
Pacific Western Airlines Flight 501</a></b>, a Boeing 737, suffers an uncon=
tained engine failure during takeoff from Calgary; all passengers and crew =
are safely evacuated, but the plane burns to the ground.</li>
<li>August 5 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1984_B=
iman_Bangladesh_Airlines_Fokker_F27_crash" title=3D"1984 Biman Bangladesh A=
irlines Fokker F27 crash">Biman Bangladesh Airlines Fokker F27-600</a></b> =
crashed into a marsh near Zia International Airport in Dhaka, Bangladesh wh=
ile landing in poor weather. With a total death toll of 49 people, it is th=
e deadliest aviation disaster to occur on Bangladeshi soil.</li>
<li>July 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Air=
lines_Flight_405" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 405">Indian Airlines Flig=
ht 405</a></b>, nine Sikhs belonging to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Khalistan_movement" title=3D"Khalistan movement">Khalistan moveme=
nt</a> forced an Airbus A300 on a domestic flight from Srinagar to the Delh=
i with 254 passengers and 10 crew on board, to be flown to Lahore Airport i=
n Pakistan. The demands (release of prisoners and money) of the hijackers w=
ere not met and they ultimately surrendered to Pakistani authorities on Jul=
y 6.</li></ul>
<ul><li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ind=
ian_Airlines_Flight_421" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 421">Indian Airlin=
es Flight 421</a></b>, seven <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikh"=
 class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sikh">Sikh</a> hijackers demanded an <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Airlines" title=3D"Indian Airline=
s">Indian Airlines</a> jetliner flying from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Delhi" title=3D"Delhi">Delhi</a> to <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Srinagar" title=3D"Srinagar">Srinagar</a> be flown to the Unite=
d Arab Emirates. The plane was taken to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/UAE" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"UAE">UAE</a> where the defense mi=
nister of UAE negotiated the release of the passengers. It was related to t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khalistan_movement" title=3D"Kh=
alistan movement">Sikh secessionist struggle</a> in the Indian state of <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab_(India)" class=3D"mw-redirect"=
 title=3D"Punjab (India)">Punjab</a>.</li></ul>
<ul><li>August 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cam=
eroon_Airlines_Flight_786" title=3D"Cameroon Airlines Flight 786">Cameroon =
Airlines Flight 786</a></b>, a Boeing 737, with 109 passengers and seven cr=
ew on board, suffers an uncontained engine failure during taxi for takeoff =
at the Douala, Cameroon airport, starting a fire; two people die as the pla=
ne burns to the ground.</li>
<li>September 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero=
servicios_Ecuatorianos_Flight_767-103" title=3D"Aeroservicios Ecuatorianos =
Flight 767-103">Aeroservicios Ecuatorianos Flight 767-103</a></b>, a Dougla=
s DC-8-55F crashes after failing to get airborne at Quito's Mariscal Sucre =
International Airport, Ecuador. All four crew, as well as 49 on the ground,=
 are killed.</li>
<li>October 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_3352" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3352">Aeroflot Flight 3352</a></b>=
, a Tupolev Tu-154B, crashes on landing at Tsentralny Airport, Omsk, Russia=
, killing 174 passengers and four people on the ground.</li>
<li>December 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provin=
cetown-Boston_Airlines_Flight_1039" title=3D"Provincetown-Boston Airlines F=
light 1039">Provincetown-Boston Airlines Flight 1039</a></b>, an Embraer 11=
0 Bandeirante with 13 passengers and crew on board, crashes on takeoff at J=
acksonville, Florida, killing all aboard.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_3519" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 3519">Aeroflot Flight 3519</a></b=
>, a Tupolev Tu-154B, crashes at Krasnoyarsk Airport while attempting an em=
ergency landing following an engine fire, killing 110 of 111 on board.</li>=
</ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1985">1985</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D71" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1985">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:BrAirtours_28M_8-1988_B.jpg=
" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikiped=
ia/commons/thumb/c/c1/BrAirtours_28M_8-1988_B.jpg/220px-BrAirtours_28M_8-19=
88_B.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"139" class=3D"thumbima=
ge" data-file-width=3D"1035" data-file-height=3D"656"></a>  <div class=3D"t=
humbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/File:BrAirtours_28M_8-1988_B.jpg" class=3D"internal" title=3D"Enlarge"></=
a></div>Remains of British Airtours Flight&nbsp;28M at Manchester Airport</=
div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eas=
tern_Air_Lines_Flight_980" title=3D"Eastern Air Lines Flight 980">Eastern A=
ir Lines Flight 980</a></b>, a Boeing 727 en route from Paraguay to Florida=
, United States, impacts Mount Illimani in Bolivia while descending for a s=
cheduled stopover at El Alto International Airport, killing all 29 people o=
n board.</li>
<li>January 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galaxy=
_Airlines_Flight_203" title=3D"Galaxy Airlines Flight 203">Galaxy Airlines =
Flight 203</a></b>, a Lockheed L-188 Electra bound for Minneapolis, Minneso=
ta, United States, crashes shortly after takeoff from Cannon International =
Airport in Reno, Nevada, due to an improperly secured air start access door=
; 70 of the 71 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_7841" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 7841">Aeroflot Flight 7841</a></b>=
, a Tupolev Tu-134 operating a domestic flight in the Soviet Union, crashes=
 6.2 miles (10.0&nbsp;km) east of Minsk National Airport after both engines=
 fail due to ice ingestion, killing 58 of the 80 on board.</li>
<li>February 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Airlines_Flight_006" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 006">China Airlines Fl=
ight 006</a></b>, a Boeing 747SP en route from Taoyuan International Airpor=
t, Taiwan, to Los Angeles in the United States, suffers an engine flameout =
off the coast of California and dives 30,000 feet (9,100&nbsp;m) before reg=
aining control; the aircraft lands safely in San Francisco and all 274 occu=
pants survive, with two passengers injured.</li>
<li>February 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iberi=
a_Airlines_Flight_610" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Iberia Airlines Fligh=
t 610">Iberia Flight 610</a></b>, a Boeing 727 operating a domestic flight =
in Spain, crashes into a television broadcast antenna installed on the summ=
it of Monte Oiz while approaching Bilbao Airport, killing all 141 passenger=
s and seven crew on board.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_Fl=
ight_8381" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 8381">Aeroflot Fl=
ight 8381</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-134 operating a domestic flight in the Sovi=
et Union, collides with a Soviet Air Force Antonov An-26; both aircraft cra=
sh near Zolochev, Ukraine, killing all 94 people on board the two aircraft.=
</li>
<li>June 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_847" title=3D"TWA Flight 847">Trans World Airlines Flight 847</a></b>, a =
Boeing 727 operating a multi-leg flight from Cairo, Egypt, to San Diego, Ca=
lifornia, United States, is hijacked by Lebanese militants shortly after ta=
king off from Athens in Greece; one passenger is murdered during the three-=
day ordeal.</li>
<li>June 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braathens=
_SAFE_Flight_139" title=3D"Braathens SAFE Flight 139">Braathens SAFE Flight=
 139</a></b>, a Boeing 737 operating a domestic flight in Norway, is hijack=
ed by a political activist who demands to speak to the Norwegian Prime Mini=
ster K=C3=A5re Willoch; all crew and passengers survive unharmed.</li>
<li>June 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India=
_Flight_182" title=3D"Air India Flight 182">Air India Flight 182</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 747 en route from Montr=C3=A9al=E2=80=93Mirabel International Airpo=
rt to London Heathrow Airport, is destroyed over the Atlantic Ocean off the=
 southwest coast of Ireland by a bomb planted by Sikh extremists; all 329 p=
eople on board lose their lives.</li>
<li>July 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_7425" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 7425">Aeroflot Flight 7425</a></b>, a=
 Tupolev Tu-154B operating a domestic flight in the Soviet Union, stalls wh=
ile cruising at 38,000 feet (11,582&nbsp;m) over Uzbekistan and enters an u=
nrecoverable spin, killing all 200 people on board.</li>
<li>August 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Ai=
r_Lines_Flight_191" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 191">Delta Air Lines Fl=
ight 191</a></b>, a Lockheed L-1011 TriStar flying from Florida to Californ=
ia in the United States, crashes on approach to Dallas/Fort Worth Internati=
onal Airport after experiencing wind shear from a sudden microburst thunder=
storm; 136 of the 163 people on board are killed, as well as a motorist who=
se car is struck by the aircraft.</li>
<li>August 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_A=
irlines_Flight_123" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Japan Airlines Flight 12=
3">Japan Airlines Flight 123</a></b>, a Boeing 747 operating a domestic fli=
ght in Japan, crashes into Mount Takamagahara after suffering a rapid decom=
pression that severs all hydraulic lines and renders the aircraft uncontrol=
lable; with the loss of 520 of the 524 people on board, this is <b>the dead=
liest single-aircraft disaster in history</b> to date.</li>
<li>August 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British=
_Airtours_Flight_28M" title=3D"British Airtours Flight 28M">British Airtour=
s Flight 28M</a></b>, a Boeing 737 bound for Corfu International Airport, G=
reece, aborts its takeoff from Manchester Airport, England, because of an e=
ngine fire; 55 of the 137 on board are killed, mostly due to smoke inhalati=
on.</li>
<li>August 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bar_Har=
bor_Airlines_Flight_1808" title=3D"Bar Harbor Airlines Flight 1808">Bar Har=
bor Airlines Flight 1808</a></b>, a Beech 99 operating a domestic multi-leg=
 flight from Boston, Massachusetts, to Bangor, Maine, crashes on approach t=
o Auburn/Lewiston Municipal Airport, where it is about to make an unschedul=
ed flag stop; all six passengers and two crew lose their lives.</li>
<li>September 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1985_=
Bakhtar_Afghan_Airlines_Antonov_An-26_shootdown" title=3D"1985 Bakhtar Afgh=
an Airlines Antonov An-26 shootdown">A Bakhtar Afghan Airlines Antonov An-2=
6 is shot down</a></b> over Afghanistan by a ground-to-air missile, while o=
perating a domestic flight from Kandahar to Farah; all 52 people on board a=
re killed.</li>
<li>September 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midwe=
st_Express_Airlines_Flight_105" title=3D"Midwest Express Airlines Flight 10=
5">Midwest Express Airlines Flight 105</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9 bo=
und for Atlanta, Georgia, crashes shortly after takeoff from Milwaukee Mitc=
hell International Airport, Wisconsin, due to engine failure and pilot erro=
r, killing all 31 people on board.</li>
<li>September 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hens=
on_Airlines_Flight_1517" title=3D"Henson Airlines Flight 1517">Henson Airli=
nes Flight 1517</a></b>, a Beechcraft Model 99 operating a domestic flight =
from Maryland to Virginia in the United States, crashes on approach to Shen=
andoah Valley Regional Airport, killing all 14 passengers and crew on board=
.</li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt=
Air_Flight_648" title=3D"EgyptAir Flight 648">EgyptAir Flight 648</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737 operating a flight between Greece and Egypt, is hijacked by Pa=
lestinian militants and forced to land on the island of Malta where <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sa%27ka_Forces" class=3D"mw-redirect" tit=
le=3D"Sa'ka Forces">Egyptian Special Forces</a> storm the aircraft; the inc=
ident kills 56 of the 89 passengers, two of the six crew members, and all b=
ut one of the hijackers.</li>
<li>November 25 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1985_Aeroflot=
_Antonov_An-12_shoot-down" title=3D"1985 Aeroflot Antonov An-12 shoot-down"=
>An Aeroflot Antonov An-12 is shot down</a></b> over Angola by a surface-to=
-air missile, while operating a cargo flight from Cuito Cuanavale to Luanda=
, allegedly by South African Special Forces; all 21 people on board are kil=
led.</li>
<li>December 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arrow=
_Air_Flight_1285" title=3D"Arrow Air Flight 1285">Arrow Air Flight 1285</a>=
</b>, a Douglas DC-8 operating a multi-leg charter flight from Cairo, Egypt=
, to Kentucky in the United States, crashes shortly after takeoff from Gand=
er International Airport, Newfoundland, killing all 256 passengers and crew=
 on board, making it the worst air disaster to occur on Canadian soil to da=
te.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_101/435" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 101/435">Aeroflot Flight 101/4=
35</a></b>, an Antonov An-24 operating a multi-leg domestic flight in the S=
oviet Union, is hijacked by the co-pilot and diverted to China; the aircraf=
t lands safely at Qiqihar Airport in northeast China and all 51 on board ar=
e unharmed.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1986">1986</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D72" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1986">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:202px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Aerom%C3%A9xico498.jpg" cla=
ss=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/co=
mmons/thumb/f/fc/Aerom%C3%A9xico498.jpg/200px-Aerom%C3%A9xico498.jpg" decod=
ing=3D"async" width=3D"200" height=3D"145" class=3D"thumbimage" data-file-w=
idth=3D"394" data-file-height=3D"286"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><di=
v class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Aerom%C3%=
A9xico498.jpg" class=3D"internal" title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>Aerom=C3=A9xi=
co Flight 498 falling to the ground immediately after a mid-air collision w=
ith a Piper Cherokee.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 18 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/1986_Aerov%C3%ADas_Guatemala_air_crash" title=3D"1986 Aerov=C3=ADas Gu=
atemala air crash">1986 Aerov=C3=ADas Guatemala air crash</a></b>, a Sud Av=
iation SE-210 Caravelle crashes into a hill on approach into Santa Elena Ai=
rport, Guatemala. All 94 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexicana=
_Flight_940" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mexicana Flight 940">Mexicana d=
e Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 940</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes into high ground =
near Santiago Maravat=C3=ADo, Mexico. All 167 passengers and crew are kille=
d in the worst ever air disaster involving the Boeing 727.</li>
<li>April 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_840_bombing_(1986)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"TWA Flight 840 bombing=
 (1986)">TWA Flight 840</a></b>, a Boeing 727, is bombed by Palestinian mil=
itants, killing four of the 121 people on board, the plane manages to land =
safely in Athens.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Lanka_F=
light_512" title=3D"Air Lanka Flight 512">Air Lanka Flight 512</a></b>, a L=
ockheed L-1011, is bombed by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam, killing =
21 of 148 on board.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Airli=
nes_Flight_334" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 334">China Airlines Flight 3=
34</a></b>, a Boeing 747, is hijacked by the pilot, who subdues the two oth=
er crew members and changes heading to land in Guangzhou. All three on boar=
d survive.</li>
<li>June 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Can=
yon_Airlines_Flight_6" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Grand Canyon Airlines=
 Flight 6">Grand Canyon Airlines Flight 6</a></b>, a De Havilland Canada DH=
C-6 Twin Otter, collides with a Bell 206 helicopter over the Tonto Plateau,=
 killing all 25 on board both aircraft.</li>
<li>July 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_F=
light_2306" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 2306">Aeroflot Flight 2306</a></b>, a =
Tupolev Tu-134, crashes near Syktyvkar, Russia, while attempting an emergen=
cy landing following a fire in the cargo hold, killing 54 of 92 on board.</=
li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LIAT_Fli=
ght_319" title=3D"LIAT Flight 319">LIAT Flight 319</a></b>, a DHC-6 Twin Ot=
ter crashes into the sea en route to E. T. Joshua Airport, St. Vincent and =
the Grenadines. All 13 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerom%C=
3%A9xico_Flight_498" title=3D"Aerom=C3=A9xico Flight 498">Aerom=C3=A9xico F=
light 498</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, collides with a Piper Cherokee=
 over Cerritos, California, killing all 67 people aboard both aircraft and =
15 people on the ground.</li>
<li>September 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_A=
m_Flight_73" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 73">Pan Am Flight 73</a></b>, a Boeing =
747, is hijacked on the ground at Jinnah International Airport in Karachi, =
Pakistan, by Palestinian militants. Twenty people die after a shootout occu=
rs inside the plane.</li>
<li>October 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_6502" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 6502">Aeroflot Flight 6502</a></b>=
, a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes in Kuybyshev (now Samara), Russia, due to pilot=
 error, killing 70 of 94 people on board.</li>
<li>November 6 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1986_British_International_Helicopters_Chinook_crash" title=3D"1986 Britis=
h International Helicopters Chinook crash">1986 British International Helic=
opters Chinook crash</a></b>, a Boeing 234LR Chinook crashes on approach to=
 Sumburgh Airport, Shetland Islands; of 47 people on board, 45 die.</li>
<li>December 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerof=
lot_Flight_892" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 892">Aeroflot Flight 892</a></b>, =
a Tupolev Tu-134A, crashes near Schonefeld Airport, East Berlin after the c=
rew misunderstands instructions from ATC, killing 72 of 82 on board; two in=
itially survive, but die later.</li>
<li>December 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi=
_Airways_Flight_163" title=3D"Iraqi Airways Flight 163">Iraqi Airways Fligh=
t 163</a></b>, a Boeing 737, is hijacked by Hezbollah militants while en ro=
ute to Amman, Jordan. A confrontation with security forces causes the plane=
 to crash, killing 63 of the 106 people on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1987">1987</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D73" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1987">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:NW255_crashsite.jpg" class=

ons/thumb/d/dc/NW255_crashsite.jpg/220px-NW255_crashsite.jpg" decoding=3D"a=
sync" width=3D"220" height=3D"202" class=3D"thumbimage" data-file-width=3D"=
300" data-file-height=3D"275"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=

jpg" class=3D"internal" title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>Debris from Northwest A=
irlines Flight 255 scattered across Middlebelt Road after it crashed on Aug=
ust 16, 1987.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Var=
ig_Flight_797" title=3D"Varig Flight 797">Varig Flight 797</a></b>, a Boein=
g 707, crashes near Abidjan because of engine failure. Out of the 52 passen=
gers and crew on board, there is only one survivor.</li>
<li>January 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skywes=
t_Airlines_Flight_1834" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Skywest Airlines Fli=
ght 1834">Skywest Airlines Flight 1834</a></b>, a Swearingen Metro II, coll=
ides in mid-air with a private Mooney M-20 near Salt Lake City, killing all=
 10 on board both aircraft.</li>
<li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_505" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 505">Aeroflot=
 Flight 505</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40, crashes into the ground at Tashkent=
, Uzbekistan, after encountering a wake vortex from an Ilyushin Il-76 that =
had taken off one and a half minutes earlier, killing all nine on board.</l=
i>
<li>March 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwest=
_Airlink_Flight_2268" title=3D"Northwest Airlink Flight 2268">Northwest Air=
link Flight 2268</a></b>, a CASA 212, crashes while attempting to land at D=
etroit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport in Detroit, Michigan, killing nine=
 of the 19 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garuda_In=
donesia_Flight_035" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 035">Garuda Indonesia =
Flight 035</a></b>, a Douglas DC-9, crashes while on approach to Medan Airp=
ort; 23 of 45 on board die.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Ea=
gle_Flight_5452" title=3D"American Eagle Flight 5452">American Eagle Flight=
 5452</a></b>, a CASA C-212, crashes while landing at Mayag=C3=BCez, Puerto=
 Rico, due to maintenance issues and pilot error. All four passengers survi=
ve, both crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOT_Flight_=
5055" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LOT Flight 5055">LOT Polish Airlines F=
light 5055</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-62M, crashes near Warsaw during landing =
because of engine failure. All 183 passengers and crew members die in the a=
ccident.</li>
<li>June 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_=
Flight_528" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 528">Aeroflot Fl=
ight 528</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40, overruns the runway on landing at Berd=
yansk, Ukraine, killing eight of 29 on board.</li>
<li>June 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippin=
e_Airlines_Flight_206" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 206">Philippine =
Airlines Flight 206</a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 748, crashes on the slope=
s of Mount Ugo, Benguet, as it begins its approach to Loakan Airport in Bag=
uio City; all 50 passengers and crew are killed. Poor visibility is blamed =
for the crash.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
87_Belize_Air_International_C-97_Mexico_City_crash" title=3D"1987 Belize Ai=
r International C-97 Mexico City crash">1987 Belize Air International C-97 =
Mexico City crash</a></b>, a Boeing C-97G Stratofreighter crashes on to a h=
ighway shortly after taking off from Mexico City International Airport, Mex=
ico. Five of the twelve passengers and crew are killed, as well as 44 on th=
e ground.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwe=
st_Airlines_Flight_255" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 255">Northwest A=
irlines Flight 255</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, crashes on takeoff f=
rom Detroit as a result of pilot error. Of 155 on board, four-year-old Cece=
lia Cichan is the only survivor. Two people on the ground in a car also are=
 killed.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_Ai=
rways_Flight_365" title=3D"Thai Airways Flight 365">Thai Airways Flight 365=
</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into the ocean off the coast of Thailand as=
 a result of pilot error. All 83 passengers and crew die.</li>
<li>October 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero_T=
rasporti_Italiani_Flight_460" title=3D"Aero Trasporti Italiani Flight 460">=
Aero Trasporti Italiani Flight 460</a></b>, an ATR 42-312, crashed into a m=
ountain 15 minutes after takeoff due to pilot error. All 37 on board die.</=
li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conti=
nental_Airlines_Flight_1713" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 1713">Con=
tinental Airlines Flight 1713</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes on=
 takeoff during a snowstorm at Denver's Stapleton International Airport, ki=
lling 25 passengers and three crew.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South=
_African_Airways_Flight_295" title=3D"South African Airways Flight 295">Sou=
th African Airways Flight 295</a></b>, a Boeing 747, crashes into the India=
n Ocean after a fire in the cargo hold. All 159 aboard die.</li>
<li>November 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korea=
n_Air_Flight_858" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 858">Korean Air Flight 858</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 707, crashes into the Andaman Sea after a bomb explodes on b=
oard. All 115 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacifi=
c_Southwest_Airlines_Flight_1771" title=3D"Pacific Southwest Airlines Fligh=
t 1771">Pacific Southwest Airlines Flight 1771</a></b>, a BAe 146, is hijac=
ked and deliberately crashes near Cayucos, California, by a disgruntled air=
line employee. All 43 people on board, including the hijacker, are killed.<=
/li>
<li>December 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phili=
ppine_Airlines_Flight_443" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 443">Philipp=
ine Airlines Flight 443</a></b>, a Shorts 360=E2=80=93300, crashes into Mt.=
 Gurain on the island of Mindanao. All 15 passengers and crew on board are =
killed.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1988">1988</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D74" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1988">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pan_Am_Flight_103._Crashed_=
Lockerbie,_Scotland,_21_December_1988.jpg" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" sr=
c=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Pan_Am_Fligh=
t_103._Crashed_Lockerbie%2C_Scotland%2C_21_December_1988.jpg/220px-Pan_Am_F=
light_103._Crashed_Lockerbie%2C_Scotland%2C_21_December_1988.jpg" decoding=

h=3D"3021" data-file-height=3D"2177"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div=
 class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pan_Am_Fli=
