light 103.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>January 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Con=
dor_Flugdienst_Flight_3782" title=3D"Condor Flugdienst Flight 3782">Condor =
Flugdienst Flight 3782</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into a mountain near =
Seferihisar, Turkey, due to a navigation error, killing all 16 on board.</l=
i>
<li>January 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_=
Southwest_Airlines_Flight_4146" title=3D"China Southwest Airlines Flight 41=
46">China Southwest Airlines Flight 4146</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-18, crashe=
s while on approach to Chongqing Airport in China due to loss of control fo=
llowing an in-flight fire; all 108 on board die.</li>
<li>January 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerofl=
ot_Flight_699" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 699">Aeroflot Flight 699</a></b>, a=
 Tupolev Tu-154, lands hard and crashes at Turkmenbashi International Airpo=
rt due to pilot error, killing 11 of 146 on board.</li>
<li>January 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans-=
Colorado_Airlines_Flight_2286" title=3D"Trans-Colorado Airlines Flight 2286=
">Trans-Colorado Airlines Flight 2286</a></b>, a Swearingen SA.227AC Metro =
III, crashes while on approach to Durango-La Plata Airport. Nine of the 17 =
passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%B=
Crnberger_Flugdienst_Flight_108" title=3D"N=C3=BCrnberger Flugdienst Flight=
 108">N=C3=BCrnberger Flugdienst Flight 108</a></b>, a Swearingen Metroline=
r III, crashes while en route to D=C3=BCsseldorf Airport, Germany. The crew=
 become disorientated after the aircraft is struck by lightning, leading to=
 an uncontrollable spin. The aircraft disintegrates mid-air, resulting in t=
he deaths of all 21 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>February 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AVAir=
_Flight_3378" title=3D"AVAir Flight 3378">AVAir Flight 3378</a></b>, a Swea=
ringen Metroliner III, crashes on takeoff from Raleigh-Durham Airport due t=
o pilot error, killing all 12 on board.</li>
<li>March 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAT_Fligh=
t_230" title=3D"TAT Flight 230">TAT Flight 230</a></b>, a Fairchild FH-227,=
 crashes near Fontainebleau, France, killing all 23 on board; an electrical=
 problem is suspected.</li>
<li>March 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avianca_=
Flight_410" title=3D"Avianca Flight 410">Avianca Flight 410</a></b>, a Boei=
ng 727, crashes into terrain near C=C3=BAcuta, Colombia after takeoff as a =
result of pilot error. All 142 people on board die.</li>
<li>April 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuwait_Ai=
rways_Flight_422" title=3D"Kuwait Airways Flight 422">Kuwait Airways Flight=
 422</a></b>, a Boeing 747, is hijacked en route from Bangkok to Kuwait by =
Lebanese guerillas demanding the release of Shi'ite prisoners held by Kuwai=
t, leading to a hostage crisis lasting 16 days and encompassing three conti=
nents. The flight, initially forced to land at Mashhad in northeastern Iran=
, travels 3,200 miles to Larnaca, Cyprus and finally to Algiers. Two passen=
gers are shot dead by the hijackers.  The remainder of the 112 passengers a=
nd crew, including three members of the Kuwaiti royal family, are eventuall=
y released and the hijackers allowed to leave Algeria.</li>
<li>April 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aloha_Ai=
rlines_Flight_243" title=3D"Aloha Airlines Flight 243">Aloha Airlines Fligh=
t 243</a></b>, a Boeing 737, suffers explosive decompression during flight =
but manages to land safely. Of 95 people on board, one flight attendant is =
blown out of the plane and killed, and several passengers are injured.</li>
<li>May 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wider%C3%B8=
e_Flight_710" title=3D"Wider=C3=B8e Flight 710">Wider=C3=B8e Flight 710</a>=
</b>, a Dash 7, crashes in Torghatten, Norway, in thick fog, killing all 36=
 passengers in the worst-ever Dash 7 accident.</li>
<li>May 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TACA_Fligh=
t_110" title=3D"TACA Flight 110">TACA Flight 110</a></b>, a Boeing 737, suf=
fers dual engine failure due to water ingestion; the aircraft lands safely =
at NASA's Michoud Assembly Facility in New Orleans; all on board survive.</=
li>
<li>June 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austral_L=
%C3%ADneas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_46" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Austral L=
=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 46">Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 46=
</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes short of the runway at Libertad=
or General Jose de San Martin Airport, killing all 22 on board.</li>
<li>June 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Franc=
e_Flight_296" title=3D"Air France Flight 296">Air France Flight 296</a></b>=
, an Airbus A320, makes a low pass over Mulhouse-Habsheim Airport in landin=
g configuration during an air show and crashes into trees at the end of the=
 runway. Of 130 passengers aboard, three die.</li>
<li>July 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_Air_F=
light_655" title=3D"Iran Air Flight 655">Iran Air Flight 655</a></b>, an Ai=
rbus A300, is shot down over Iranian waters by the missile cruiser USS <i>V=
incennes</i>; all 290 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 13 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1988_=
British_International_Helicopters_Sikorsky_S-61N_crash" title=3D"1988 Briti=
sh International Helicopters Sikorsky S-61N crash">1988 British Internation=
al Helicopters Sikorsky S-61N crash</a></b>: a Sikorsky S-61 ditches in the=
 North Sea due to an engine fire; all 21 on board survive.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAAC_Fl=
ight_301" title=3D"CAAC Flight 301">CAAC Flight 301</a></b>, a Hawker Sidde=
ley Trident operating a Guangzhou Baiyun Airport to Hong Kong Kai Tak Airpo=
rt flight, runs off the runway. Seven of the 89 passengers and crew on boar=
d are killed.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_A=
ir_Lines_Flight_1141" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 1141">Delta Air Lines=
 Flight 1141</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes on takeoff from Dallas-Fort Wor=
th International Airport as a result of pilot error and poor design Boeing'=
s mechanical failsafe system on the 727; of 108 people on board, 12 passeng=
ers and two crew members are killed.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietn=
am_Airlines_Flight_831" title=3D"Vietnam Airlines Flight 831">Vietnam Airli=
nes Flight 831</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes on approach to Don Mueang=
 International Airport in Bangkok. 76 of the 90 passengers and crew on boar=
d are killed.</li>
<li>September 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethi=
opian_Airlines_Flight_604" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Flight 604">Ethiopia=
n Airlines Flight 604</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes on takeoff after suffe=
ring multiple bird strikes; 35 of 98 passengers die, all six crew survive.<=
/li>
<li>October 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uganda=
_Airlines_Flight_775" title=3D"Uganda Airlines Flight 775">Uganda Airlines =
Flight 775</a></b>, a Boeing 707-338C, crashes while attempting to land at =
Rome's Fiumicino Airport; 33 of the 52 passengers and crew on board are kil=
led.</li>
<li>October 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian=
_Airlines_Flight_113" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 113">Indian Airlines =
Flight 113</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes on approach 2.6&nbsp;km short of =
the runway in poor visibility in Ahmedabad, India, killing 133 of the 135 p=
eople on board.</li>
<li>November 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOT_Po=
lish_Airlines_Flight_703" title=3D"LOT Polish Airlines Flight 703">LOT Poli=
sh Airlines Flight 703</a></b>, an Antonov An-24, crashes on approach to Rz=
esz=C3=B3w-Jasionka Airport, killing one passenger, all others survive.</li=
>
<li>December 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_A=
m_Flight_103" title=3D"Pan Am Flight 103">Pan Am Flight 103</a></b>, a Boei=
ng 747, disintegrates in the air over Lockerbie, Dumfries and Galloway, Sco=
tland, after a terrorist bomb explodes on board. All 259 people on board an=
d 11 on the ground are killed. The incident is also known as the <i>Lockerb=
ie air disaster</i>.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1989">1989</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D75" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1989">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keg=
worth_air_disaster" title=3D"Kegworth air disaster">British Midland Airways=
 Flight 092</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes near Kegworth, Leicestershire, U=
nited Kingdom, after one of its engines loses a fan blade and fails. Of the=
 118 passengers and eight crew, 79 survive. The incident became known as th=
e <i>Kegworth air disaster</i> and is the first loss of a Boeing 737-400.</=
li>
<li>February 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indepe=
ndent_Air_Flight_1851" title=3D"Independent Air Flight 1851">Independent Ai=
r Flight 1851</a></b>, a Boeing 707, crashes into a hill on approach to San=
ta Maria, the Azores. All 144 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flyin=
g_Tiger_Line_Flight_66" title=3D"Flying Tiger Line Flight 66">Flying Tiger =
Line Flight 66</a></b>, a Boeing 747 crashes near Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, o=
n approach to land, killing all four on board. The crash is caused by misco=
mmunication between ATC and the crew.</li></ul>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Flt_811_damage.JPG" class=

light 811 after the cargo door blew open mid-flight; nine passengers were e=
jected through the hole.</div></div></div>
<ul><li>February 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U=
nited_Airlines_Flight_811" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 811">United Airl=
ines Flight 811</a></b>, a Boeing 747, suffers an explosive decompression s=
hortly after takeoff from Honolulu, Hawaii, United States, caused by a carg=
o door that burst open during flight. Of 355 people on board, nine passenge=
rs are blown out of the plane, but the crew manage to land safely at Honolu=
lu.</li>
<li>March 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Onta=
rio_Flight_1363" title=3D"Air Ontario Flight 1363">Air Ontario Flight 1363<=
/a></b>, a Fokker F28, crashes immediately after takeoff from Dryden, Ontar=
io, Canada, because of ice on the wings, killing 24 of 69 people on board.<=
/li>
<li>March 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transbra=
sil_Flight_801" title=3D"Transbrasil Flight 801">Transbrasil Flight 801</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 707, crashes on a high speed approach into <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S%C3%A3o_Paulo_Guarulhos_International_Airport" cla=
ss=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"S=C3=A3o Paulo Guarulhos International Airport"=
>S=C3=A3o Paulo Guarulhos International Airport</a>, the left wing striking=
 a building and crashing into a residential area. All three crewmembers and=
 22 persons on the ground were killed. The 707 involved was used in the 197=
0 movie <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airport_(1970_film)" title=
=3D"Airport (1970 film)">Airport</a> when it was owned by <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flying_Tiger_Line" title=3D"Flying Tiger Line">Flyi=
ng Tigers</a>.</li>
<li>June 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surinam_Ai=
rways_Flight_764" title=3D"Surinam Airways Flight 764">Surinam Airways Flig=
ht 764</a></b>, a Douglas DC-8, crashes while attempting to land in heavy f=
og at Paramaribo, Suriname. The plane hits trees and flips upside down, kil=
ling 176 of 187 people on board.</li>
<li>July 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ai=
rlines_Flight_232" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 232">United Airlines Fli=
ght 232</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, suffers a complete hydraulic sy=
stem failure over Iowa, United States, after the tail-mounted engine disint=
egrates. The crew maintains partial control of the aircraft using different=
ial throttle, bringing it to a crash landing on the runway of the Sioux Cit=
y, Iowa, airport. Of the 296 people on board, 112 die.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_Ai=
r_Flight_803" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 803">Korean Air Flight 803</a></b>=
, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, crashes while attempting to land in heavy fog =
at Tripoli, Libya. 75 of the 199 passengers and crew on board plus four peo=
ple on the ground are killed in the accident.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olympic_=
Aviation_Flight_545" title=3D"Olympic Aviation Flight 545">Olympic Aviation=
 Flight 545</a></b>, a Shorts 330=E2=80=93220, crashes into Mount Kerkis in=
 Greece. All 34 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>August 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakista=
n_International_Airlines_Flight_404" title=3D"Pakistan International Airlin=
es Flight 404">Pakistan International Airlines Flight 404</a></b>, a Fokker=
 F27, disappears on a flight with 54 on board; the wreckage has never been =
found.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuban=
a_de_Aviaci%C3%B3n_Flight_9046" title=3D"Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 904=
6">Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 9046</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-62M, crashes=
 while trying to take off from Jos=C3=A9 Mart=C3=AD International Airport i=
n Havana, Cuba. All 126 people on board the aircraft plus 45 people on the =
ground are killed in the crash.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Varig=
_Flight_254" title=3D"Varig Flight 254">Varig Flight 254</a></b>, a Boeing =
737, runs out of fuel because of incorrect navigation and crashes in the Br=
azilian jungle, killing 13 of the 54 people on board.</li>
<li>September 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partn=
air_Flight_394" title=3D"Partnair Flight 394">Partnair Flight 394</a></b>, =
a Convair 580, crashes into the North Sea after its tail section falls off =
in mid-air. All 55 people on board die. The disaster is blamed on counterfe=
it aircraft parts.</li>
<li>September 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTA_=
Flight_772" title=3D"UTA Flight 772">UTA Flight 772</a></b>, a McDonnell Do=
uglas DC-10, explodes in mid-air over the Sahara desert when a bomb hidden =
in its forward cargo hold detonates. All 170 people on board are killed. Re=
sponsibility for the bombing is later traced back to Abdullah Senussi, the =
brother-in-law of Libyan leader Muammar al-Gaddafi, whose government in 200=
3 agrees to pay compensation to the victims.</li>
<li>September 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USAi=
r_Flight_5050" title=3D"USAir Flight 5050">USAir Flight 5050</a></b>, a Boe=
ing 737, overruns the runway at LaGuardia Airport attempting to abort takeo=
ff after a tire on a nosewheel bursts due to a mistrimmed rudder; two passe=
ngers die.</li>
<li>October 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tan-Sa=
hsa_Flight_414" title=3D"Tan-Sahsa Flight 414">Tan-Sahsa Flight 414</a></b>=
, a Boeing 727, crashes into a mountain known as Cerro de Hula near Tegucig=
alpa, Honduras, due to pilot error; 127 of 146 on board die.</li>
<li>October 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_=
Airlines_Flight_204" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 204">China Airlines Fli=
ght 204</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into the Chiashan mountain range aft=
er takeoff from Hualien Airport due to pilot error; all 54 on board die.</l=
i>
<li>November 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avian=
ca_Flight_203" title=3D"Avianca Flight 203">Avianca Flight 203</a></b>, a B=
oeing 727, explodes in mid-air over Colombia, killing all 107 people on boa=
rd and three people on the ground. The Medell=C3=ADn Cartel claimed respons=
ibility for the attack.</li>
<li>December 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_F=
light_867" title=3D"KLM Flight 867">KLM Flight 867</a></b>, a Boeing 747 fl=
ying from Amsterdam to Anchorage, Alaska, flies through a cloud of volcanic=
 debris, subsequently losing power from all four engines. The crew is able =
to restart the engines and land the plane safely.</li>
<li>December 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Express_Flight_2415" title=3D"United Express Flight 2415">United Express =
Flight 2415</a></b>, a BAe Jetstream 31 operated by North Pacific Airlines =
crashes while attempting to land at Tri-Cities Airport, Washington. All six=
 passengers and crew are killed.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1990s">1990s</span><span class=3D"mw-=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1990">1990</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1990">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nor=
thwest_Airlines_Flight_5_(1990)" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 5 (1990=
)">Northwest Airlines Flight 5</a></b>, a Boeing 727 with 145 on board, los=
es an engine over Madison, Florida, the aircraft makes an emergency landing=
 at Tampa International Airport, all on board survive.</li>
<li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SANSA_=
Flight_32" title=3D"SANSA Flight 32">SANSA Flight 32</a></b>, crashes into =
a mountain just after takeoff from Juan Santamaria International Airport in=
 San Jos=C3=A9, Costa Rica, killing all 20 passengers and three crew on boa=
rd.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Av=
ianca_Flight_52" title=3D"Avianca Flight 52">Avianca Flight 52</a></b>, a B=
oeing 707, runs out of fuel and crashes while attempting to land at John F.=
 Kennedy International Airport in New York; of the 158 people on board, 85 =
survive.</li>
<li>February 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India=
n_Airlines_Flight_605" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 605">Indian Airlines=
 Flight 605</a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes on its final approach to Banga=
lore Airport. 92 out of 146 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_=
Southeast_Airlines_Flight_2254" title=3D"Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight=
 2254">Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight 2254</a></b>, an Embraer EMB 120 =
Brasilia, collides with a Cessna 172, both on the Cessna die. Flight 2254 l=
ands; all seven on board survive.</li>
<li>April 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wider%C3=
%B8e_Flight_839" title=3D"Wider=C3=B8e Flight 839">Wider=C3=B8e Flight 839<=
/a></b>, a DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes into water just after takeoff from V=
=C3=A6r=C3=B8y Airport, killing all five people on board.</li>
<li>May 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippine=
_Airlines_Flight_143" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 143">Philippine A=
irlines Flight 143</a></b>, a Boeing 737, explodes and burns on the ground =
at Ninoy Aquino International Airport, killing eight of 120 on board.</li>
<li>June 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_A=
irways_Flight_5390" title=3D"British Airways Flight 5390">British Airways F=
light 5390</a></b>, a BAC One-Eleven, suffers explosive decompression over =
Didcot, Oxfordshire, England, when one of the front windscreen panes blows =
out. The captain is partially blown out of the cockpit, but a flight attend=
ant manages to keep the unconscious pilot from falling out of the aircraft.=
 The first officer lands the aircraft safely at Southampton Airport. All on=
 board survive.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
1990_Guangzhou_Baiyun_airport_collisions" title=3D"1990 Guangzhou Baiyun ai=
rport collisions">Guangzhou Baiyun airport collisions</a></b>, a hijacked B=
oeing 737 operating <b>Xiamen Airlines Flight 8301</b> clips <b>China South=
west Airlines Flight 2402</b>, a Boeing 707, during landing at Guangzhou Ba=
iyun International Airport, and collides with <b>China Southern Airlines Fl=
ight 2812</b>, a Boeing 757; of the 225 occupants on board the three aircra=
ft, 128 die.</li>
<li>November 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alita=
lia_Flight_404" title=3D"Alitalia Flight 404">Alitalia Flight 404</a></b>, =
a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes on approach to Z=C3=BCrich Airport, Switz=
erland, killing all 46 people on board.</li>
<li>November 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangk=
ok_Airways_Flight_125" title=3D"Bangkok Airways Flight 125">Bangkok Airways=
 Flight 125</a></b>, a De Havilland Canada DHC-8-103, crashes on approach t=
o Koh Samui Airport in Thailand, killing all 33 passengers and five crew on=
 board.</li>
<li>December 3 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1990_Wayne_County_Airport_runway_collision" title=3D"1990 Wayne County Air=
port runway collision">1990 Wayne County Airport runway collision</a></b>, =
<b>Northwest Airlines Flight 1482</b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, collides w=
ith <b>Northwest Airlines Flight 299</b>, a Boeing 727, on a runway at Detr=
oit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport; eight of the 54 people on board the =
DC-9 are killed; all 154 people on board the Boeing 727 survive.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1991">1991</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1991">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

<ul><li>February 1 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Los_Angeles_runway_disaster" title=3D"Los Angeles runway disaster">Los=
 Angeles runway disaster</a></b>, <b>USAir Flight 1493</b>, a Boeing 737 la=
nding at Los Angeles International Airport, strikes <b>SkyWest Airlines Fli=
ght 5569</b>, a Fairchild Metro commuter plane waiting to take off from the=
 same runway. All 12 people aboard the Metro and 23 of the 89 on the Boeing=
 737 are killed.</li>
<li>February 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAN_C=
hile_Flight_1069" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LAN Chile Flight 1069">LAN=
 Chile Flight 1069</a></b>, a BAe 146, overruns the runway while landing at=
 Puerto Williams, Chile, killing 20 of the 72 people on board.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Ai=
rlines_Flight_585" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 585">United Airlines Fli=
ght 585</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes while attempting to land at Colorado=
 Springs Airport, Colorado, killing all 25 people on board. The cause of th=
e crash is not identified until the investigation into the crash of <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USAir_Flight_427" title=3D"USAir Flight 4=
27">USAir Flight 427</a> in 1994; both crashes are eventually attributed to=
 defects in a valve associated with the rudder.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroposta=
l_Alas_de_Venezuela_Flight_108" title=3D"Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela Fligh=
t 108">Aeropostal Alas de Venezuela Flight 108</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas=
 DC-9 crashes into a mountain shortly after taking off from La Chinita Inte=
rnational Airport, Venezuela. All 45 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>March 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singapor=
e_Airlines_Flight_117" title=3D"Singapore Airlines Flight 117">Singapore Ai=
rlines Flight 117</a></b>, an Airbus A310, is hijacked by Pakistani militan=
ts en route to Singapore Changi Airport, where, upon landing, it is stormed=
 by Singapore Special Operations forces. All of the hijackers are killed in=
 the operation, with no fatalities among the passengers and crew.</li>
<li>April 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_=
Southeast_Airlines_Flight_2311" title=3D"Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight=
 2311">Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight 2311</a></b>, an Embraer EMB 120R=
T, rolls sharply and crashes on final approach to Brunswick, Georgia, killi=
ng all 23 people on board.</li>
<li>May 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lauda_Air_=
Flight_004" title=3D"Lauda Air Flight 004">Lauda Air Flight 004</a></b>, a =
Boeing 767, disintegrates in mid-air over Uthai Thani Province and Suphan B=
uri Province, Thailand, killing all 223 people on board. A thrust reverser =
had accidentally deployed in flight, causing the disaster. It is the first =
fatal crash of a Boeing 767.</li>
<li>July 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L%27Expre=
ss_Airlines_Flight_508" title=3D"L'Express Airlines Flight 508">L'Express A=
irlines Flight 508</a></b>, a Beechcraft Model 99, crashes while on approac=
h Birmingham Municipal Airport, Alabama, due to severe thunderstorms, killi=
ng 13 people on board.</li>
<li>July 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigeria_A=
irways_Flight_2120" title=3D"Nigeria Airways Flight 2120">Nigeria Airways F=
light 2120</a></b>, a Nationair McDonnell Douglas DC-8 chartered by Nigeria=
 Airways to transport Nigerian pilgrims to Mecca, crashes shortly after tak=
eoff from King Abdulaziz International Airport, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, becau=
se of a fire caused by tire failure. All 261 on board die, including 14 Can=
adian crew members.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_=
Airlines_Flight_257" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 257">Indian Airlines F=
light 257</a></b>, a Boeing 737, hits high ground during descent about 30&n=
bsp;km from the Imphal airport. All six crew members and 63 passengers are =
killed.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cont=
inental_Express_Flight_2574" title=3D"Continental Express Flight 2574">Cont=
inental Express Flight 2574</a></b>, an Embraer EMB 120RT, crashes on desce=
nt in Eagle Lake, Texas, killing all 14 people on board. Maintenance crews =
traded work shifts during repairs to the horizontal stabilizer, inadvertent=
ly leaving 47 bolts missing. Reformers pointed to this error and called for=
 development of a "safety culture".</li>
<li>December 27 =E2=80=93 Both engines of <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Scandinavian_Airlines_System_Flight_751" title=3D"Scandinavian A=
irlines System Flight 751">Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 751</a></b>,=
 a McDonnell Douglas MD-81, surge shortly after takeoff from Stockholm Arla=
nda Airport. The pilots successfully make an emergency landing in a nearby =
field, injuring 25 passengers but incurring not a single fatality.</li>
<li>December 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Airlines_Flight_358" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 358">China Airlines Fl=
ight 358</a></b>, a Boeing 747 freighter, suffers double engine separation =
and crashes into a hill near Wanli, Taipei, Taiwan, killing all five crew o=
n board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Com=
mutAir_Flight_4281" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"CommutAir Flight 4281">C=
ommutAir Flight 4281</a></b>, a Beechcraft 1900C crashes on approach into A=
dirondack Regional Airport, New York. Two of the four occupants are killed.=
</li>
<li>January 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_In=
ter_Flight_148" title=3D"Air Inter Flight 148">Air Inter Flight 148</a></b>=
, an Airbus A320, crashes in the Vosges Mountains on approach to Strasbourg=
, France, killing 87 of 96 people on board.</li>
<li>March 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USAir_Fl=
ight_405" title=3D"USAir Flight 405">USAir Flight 405</a></b>, a Fokker F-2=
8, crashes on takeoff from New York because of ice buildup. Twenty-seven of=
 the 51 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 31 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans-Air_Servic=
e_Flight_671" title=3D"Trans-Air Service Flight 671">Trans-Air Service Flig=
ht 671</a></b>, a Boeing 707-321C, experiences an in-flight separation of t=
wo engines on the right wing. Despite substantial control difficulties and =
a fire that breaks out on the right wing during approach, the pilots safely=
 land at a military airbase in Istres, France. None of the five occupants a=
re injured.</li>
<li>June 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copa_Airli=
nes_Flight_201" title=3D"Copa Airlines Flight 201">Copa Airlines Flight 201=
</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200 Advanced, crashes near Dari=C3=A9n, Panama, kill=
ing all 47 passengers and crew on board; a faulty attitude indicator is the=
 cause.</li>
<li>June 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_E=
agle_Flight_5456" title=3D"American Eagle Flight 5456">American Eagle Fligh=
t 5456</a></b>, a CASA C-212 Aviocar operated by Executive Airlines crashes=
 on approach into Eugenio Mar=C3=ADa de Hostos Airport, Puerto Rico. All fi=
ve passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>June 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GP_Express=
_Flight_861" title=3D"GP Express Flight 861">GP Express Flight 861</a></b>,=
 a Beechcraft Model 99 crashes on approach into Anniston Metropolitan Airpo=
rt, Alabama. Three of the six passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandala_A=
irlines_Flight_660" title=3D"Mandala Airlines Flight 660">Mandala Airlines =
Flight 660</a></b>, a Vickers Viscount 816, crashes on approach to Pattimur=
a Airport, Ambon, Indonesia, killing all 63 passengers and seven crew on bo=
ard.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_843" title=3D"TWA Flight 843">TWA Flight 843</a></b> aborts takeoff at Jo=
hn F. Kennedy International Airport. The Lockheed L-1011 turns off the runw=
ay onto grass in order to avoid striking a concrete barrier. The plane is d=
estroyed by fire shortly after all 292 passengers and crew evacuate with no=
 loss of life.</li>
<li>July 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_Airw=
ays_International_Flight_311" title=3D"Thai Airways International Flight 31=
1">Thai Airways International Flight 311</a></b>, an Airbus A310, crashes o=
n approach into Kathmandu, Nepal, killing all 14 crew and 99 passengers on =
board.</li>
<li>July 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Gen=
eral_Aviation_Flight_7552" title=3D"China General Aviation Flight 7552">Chi=
na General Aviation Flight 7552</a></b>, a Yakovlev 42D, loses control just=
 after takeoff from Nanjing Airport and crashes into a pond; 108 of 126 on =
board die.</li>
<li>August 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflo=
t_Flight_2808" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 2808">Aeroflot Flight 2808</a></b>,=
 a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes into buildings while attempting to land at Ivano=
vo Yuzhny Airport, killing all 84 on board.</li>
<li>September 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietn=
am_Airlines_Flight_850" title=3D"Vietnam Airlines Flight 850">Vietnam Airli=
nes Flight 850</a></b>, an Airbus A310-200, is hijacked by <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ly_Tong" title=3D"Ly Tong">Ly Tong</a>, a former p=
ilot in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Vietnam_Ai=
r_Force" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Republic of Vietnam Air Force">Repu=
blic of Vietnam Air Force</a>. He then drops anti-communist leaflets over H=
o Chi Minh City before parachuting out. Vietnamese security forces later ar=
rest him on the ground. The aircraft lands safely, and no one on board is i=
njured.</li>
<li>September 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIA_=
Flight_268" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"PIA Flight 268">Pakistan Interna=
tional Airlines Flight 268</a></b>, an Airbus A300, crashes near Kathmandu,=
 Nepal, killing all 12 crew and 155 passengers.</li>
<li>October 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Al_F=
light_1862" title=3D"El Al Flight 1862">El Al Flight 1862</a></b>, a Boeing=
 747, freighter, crashes into high-rise apartment buildings in Amsterdam af=
ter two of its engines detach from the wing. Forty-three people, including =
the plane's crew of three plus an additional passenger, are killed.</li>
<li>October 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merpat=
i_Nusantara_Airlines_Flight_5601" title=3D"Merpati Nusantara Airlines Fligh=
t 5601">Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 5601</a></b>, a CASA/IPTN CN-235,=
 crashes into Mount Papandayan near the town Garut in Indonesia. All 31 pas=
sengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietn=
am_Airlines_Flight_474" title=3D"Vietnam Airlines Flight 474">Vietnam Airli=
nes Flight 474</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40, crashes while on approach to Nha=
 Trang Airport in a tropical storm. Thirty people on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Southern_Airlines_Flight_3943" title=3D"China Southern Airlines Flight 394=
3">China Southern Airlines Flight 3943</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, crashes o=
n descent to Guilin Airport, killing all 141 aboard.</li>
<li>December 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marti=
nair_Flight_495" title=3D"Martinair Flight 495">Martinair Flight 495</a></b=
> crashes in Faro, Portugal, killing 54 people and injuring 106.</li>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya=
n_Arab_Airlines_Flight_1103" title=3D"Libyan Arab Airlines Flight 1103">Lib=
yan Arab Airlines Flight 1103</a></b>, a Boeing 727, collides with a Libyan=
 Air Force MiG-23 near Tripoli International Airport, killing all 159 on bo=
ard both aircraft.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1993">1993</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D80" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1993">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luf=
thansa_CityLine_Flight_5634" title=3D"Lufthansa CityLine Flight 5634">Lufth=
ansa CityLine Flight 5634</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-8, crashes sho=
rt of the runway at Paris=E2=80=93Charles de Gaulle Airport, killing four o=
f 23 on board.</li>
<li>February 8 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1993_Tehran_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1993 Tehran mid-air collision">199=
3 Tehran mid-air collision</a></b>, an Iran Air Tours Tupolev Tu-154 collid=
es in mid-air with an Iranian Air Force Sukhoi Su-24, killing all 133 on bo=
ard both aircraft.</li>
<li>February 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lufth=
ansa_Flight_592" title=3D"Lufthansa Flight 592">Lufthansa Flight 592</a></b=
>, an Airbus A310-300, is hijacked and the pilot is forced to fly to John F=
. Kennedy International Airport. The plane lands safely and the hijacker su=
rrenders. All 104 on board survive.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palair_Ma=
cedonian_Airlines_Flight_301" title=3D"Palair Macedonian Airlines Flight 30=
1">Palair Macedonian Airlines Flight 301</a></b>, a Fokker 100, crashes sho=
rtly after takeoff from Skopje Airport in Macedonia; 83 of the 97 passenger=
s and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Eas=
tern_Airlines_Flight_583" title=3D"China Eastern Airlines Flight 583">China=
 Eastern Airlines Flight 583</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11, makes an e=
mergency landing at Shemya Air Force Base after the slats are accidentally =
deployed in mid-air near the Aleutian Islands; all on board initially survi=
ve, but two die later.</li>
<li>April 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_Ai=
r_System_Flight_451" title=3D"Japan Air System Flight 451">Japan Air System=
 Flight 451</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, encounters windshear and ski=
ds off the runway at Hanamaki Airport; all on board survive.</li>
<li>April 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_A=
irlines_Flight_427" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 427">Indian Airlines Fl=
ight 427</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, is hijacked on a flight between New Del=
hi and Srinagar, India. The plane lands at Amritsar Airport where it is sto=
rmed by commandos; the hijacker is killed and the 140 passengers and crew s=
urvive without injury.</li>
<li>April 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_A=
irlines_Flight_491" title=3D"Indian Airlines Flight 491">Indian Airlines Fl=
ight 491</a></b>, a Boeing 737, strikes a large vehicle on a road just outs=
ide Aurangabad Airport, killing 55 of the 118 people on board.</li>
<li>May 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SAM_Colomb=
ia_Flight_501" title=3D"SAM Colombia Flight 501">SAM Colombia Flight 501</a=
></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes into Mount Paramo Frontino, killing all 132 on=
 board.</li>
<li>July 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merpati_Nu=
santara_Airlines_Flight_724" title=3D"Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 724=
">Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 724</a></b>, a Fokker F27, collides wit=
h a small hill near the sea, breaks up and plunges into the sea shortly aft=
erwards, killing 41 people on board.</li>
<li>July 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Nor=
thwest_Airlines_Flight_2119" title=3D"China Northwest Airlines Flight 2119"=
>China Northwest Airlines Flight 2119</a></b>, a BAe 146, overruns the runw=
ay at Yinchuan Hedong Airport, Ningxia, China after an aborted takeoff; the=
 aircraft crashes into a lake, killing 54 passengers and one crew member.</=
li>
<li>July 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asiana_Ai=
rlines_Flight_733" title=3D"Asiana Airlines Flight 733">Asiana Airlines Fli=
ght 733</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into a mountain in Haenam, South Kor=
ea, after failed landing attempts, killing 78 of the 110 people on board; t=
his crash is the first loss of a Boeing 737-500.</li>
<li>August 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakha_A=
via_Flight_301" title=3D"Sakha Avia Flight 301">Sakha Avia Flight 301</a></=
b>, a Let L-410 Turbolet, crashes on approach to Aldan Airport in Russia, k=
illing all 24 people on board.</li>
<li>August 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1993_Ta=
jik_Air_Yakovlev_Yak-40_incident" title=3D"1993 Tajik Air Yakovlev Yak-40 i=
ncident">A Tajik Air Yakovlev Yak-40 crashes</a></b> after overshooting the=
 runway on takeoff from Khorog Airport, killing 82 of the 86 people on boar=
d; the accident is the deadliest involving the Yak-40 as well as the deadli=
est accident in Tajikistan to date.</li>
<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1993_Ev=
erest_Air_Dornier_228_crash" title=3D"1993 Everest Air Dornier 228 crash">A=
n Everest Air Dornier Do 228 crashes</a></b> near Bharatpur in Nepal, killi=
ng all 19 people on board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>September 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Lufthansa_Flight_2904" title=3D"Lufthansa Flight 2904">Lufthansa Flight 290=
4</a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes after overrunning the runway in Warsaw, =
Poland, killing two and injuring 68 of the 72 people on board.</li>
<li>September 21 =E2=80=93 In the first of the three <b><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transair_Georgia_airliner_shootdowns" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Transair Georgia airliner shootdowns">Transair Georgia airl=
iner shootdowns</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-134A is hit on approach to Sukhumi-Ba=
busheri Airport by a surface-to-air missile; the plane crashes into the Bla=
ck Sea, killing all five crew members and all 22 passengers.</li>
<li>September 22 =E2=80=93 In the second of the three <b><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transair_Georgia_airliner_shootdowns" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Transair Georgia airliner shootdowns">Transair Georgia air=
liner shootdowns</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, carrying soldiers from Tbilisi,=
 is shot down on landing in the Sukhumi-Babusheri Airport; the plane crashe=
s on the runway and catches fire, killing 108 of the 132 people on board.</=
li>
<li>October 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_=
Eastern_Airlines_Flight_5398" title=3D"China Eastern Airlines Flight 5398">=
China Eastern Airlines Flight 5398</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, over=
runs the runway at Fuzhou Changle International Airport in heavy weather, k=
illing two of 80 on board.</li>
<li>October 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wider%=
C3%B8e_Flight_744" title=3D"Wider=C3=B8e Flight 744">Wider=C3=B8e Flight 74=
4</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes in Overhalla, No=
rway, on approach to Namsos Airport, killing both pilots and four passenger=
s; the crash is also known as the <i>Namsos Accident</i>.</li>
<li>November 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_=
Airlines_Flight_605" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 605">China Airlines Fli=
ght 605</a></b>, a Boeing 747-400, overruns Kai Tak Airport's runway 13 on =
landing during a typhoon; the aircraft is unable to stop before crashing in=
to Hong Kong harbor; all 374 on board escape safely; this crash is the firs=
t loss of a Boeing 747-400.</li>
<li>November 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Northern_Airlines_Flight_6901" title=3D"China Northern Airlines Flight 690=
1">China Northern Airlines Flight 6901</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, =
crashes on approach to =C3=9Cr=C3=BCmqi Diwopu International Airport, Xinji=
ang, China; killing 12 of the 102 on board; pilot error is blamed.</li>
<li>November 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avioi=
mpex_Flight_110" title=3D"Avioimpex Flight 110">Avioimpex Flight 110</a></b=
>, a Yakovlev Yak-42, crashes on approach to Ohrid Airport in Macedonia; al=
l 116 passengers and crew die as a result of the crash, though one passenge=
r lived for 11 days before succumbing to his injuries.</li>
<li>December 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northw=
est_Airlink_Flight_5719" title=3D"Northwest Airlink Flight 5719">Northwest =
Airlink Flight 5719</a></b>, a Jetstream 31, crashes into two ridges east o=
f Hibbing, Minnesota, killing all 18 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1994">1994</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

 section: 1994">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:USAir_Flight_427_Impact_cra=

></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https:=

nternal" title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>Crater left by the impact of <a href=

<ul><li>January 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bai=
kal_Airlines_Flight_130" title=3D"Baikal Airlines Flight 130">Baikal Airlin=
es Flight 130</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, loses control and crashes near Irk=
utsk, Russia, after the hydraulic system failed due to an engine fire, kill=
ing all 124 on board and one person on the ground.</li>
<li>January 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_=
Express_Flight_6291" title=3D"United Express Flight 6291">United Express Fl=
ight 6291</a></b>, a BAe Jetstream 41 crashes on approach into <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Port_Columbus_International_Airport" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Port Columbus International Airport">Port Columbus In=
ternational Airport</a>, Ohio. Five of the eight passengers and crew are ki=
lled.</li>
<li>February 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulko=
vo_Aviation_Enterprise_Flight_9045" title=3D"Pulkovo Aviation Enterprise Fl=
ight 9045">Pulkovo Aviation Enterprise Flight 9045</a></b>, an Antonov An-1=
2BP crashes on approach into Nalchik Airport, Russia. All 13 passengers and=
 crew are killed. The aircraft was carrying 12,515&nbsp;kg of coins from th=
e Saint Petersburg Mint.</li>
<li>March 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1994_Saha=
ra_Airlines_Boeing_737_crash" title=3D"1994 Sahara Airlines Boeing 737 cras=
h">A Sahara Airlines Boeing 737 crashes</a></b> during a training flight in=
to an Aeroflot Ilyushin Il-86 at New Delhi, India, killing all 8 on both ai=
rcraft and 1 on the ground.</li>
<li>March 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot=
_Flight_593" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 593">Aeroflot Flight 593</a></b>, an =
Airbus A310, crashes into a wooded hillside in Siberia. All 75 passengers a=
nd crew are killed.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KLM_Cityh=
opper_Flight_433" title=3D"KLM Cityhopper Flight 433">KLM Cityhopper Flight=
 433</a></b>, a Saab 340, crashes while trying to return to Schiphol Airpor=
t, due to pilot error and equipment failure; the pilot and two passengers d=
ie, nine passengers are injured.</li>
<li>April 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_E=
xpress_Flight_705" title=3D"Federal Express Flight 705">Federal Express Fli=
ght 705</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10-30, experiences an attempted hij=
acking by a FedEx employee; the three crew members are severely injured, bu=
t manage to subdue the attacker and land the aircraft safely with no loss o=
f life.</li>
<li>April 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Ai=
rlines_Flight_140" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 140">China Airlines Fligh=
t 140</a></b>, an Airbus A300, crashes while landing at Nagoya, Japan, as a=
 result of pilot error. 264 of the 271 people on board die.</li>
<li>June 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Nort=
hwest_Airlines_Flight_2303" title=3D"China Northwest Airlines Flight 2303">=
China Northwest Airlines Flight 2303</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154M, breaks up =
in mid-air and crashes near Xian, China, killing all 160 on board. The dead=
liest airplane crash ever to occur in China is attributed to a maintenance =
error.</li>
<li>June 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbus_In=
dustrie_Flight_129" title=3D"Airbus Industrie Flight 129">Airbus Industrie =
Flight 129</a></b>, an Airbus A330 on a test flight, crashes at France's To=
ulouse-Blagnac Airport, killing all seven on board.</li>
<li>July 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Maurit=
anie_Flight_625" title=3D"Air Mauritanie Flight 625">Air Mauritanie Flight =
625</a></b>, a Fokker F28 Fellowship crashes on landing at Tidjikja Airport=
, Mauritania in sandstorm conditions. 80 of the 93 passengers and crew are =
killed.</li>
<li>July 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USAir_Flig=
ht_1016" title=3D"USAir Flight 1016">USAir Flight 1016</a></b>, a McDonnell=
 Douglas DC-9, crashes while attempting to land at Charlotte, North Carolin=
a, during a thunderstorm. 37 of the 57 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>July 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alas_Chir=
icanas_Flight_901" title=3D"Alas Chiricanas Flight 901">Alas Chiricanas Fli=
ght 901</a></b>, an Embraer EMB-110, explodes in mid-air over Panama, killi=
ng all 21 people on board. Investigators conclude that a suicide bomber cau=
sed the plane to explode, although motives and affiliation of the bomber re=
main unclear.</li>
<li>August 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_A=
ir_Maroc_Flight_630" title=3D"Royal Air Maroc Flight 630">Royal Air Maroc F=
light 630</a></b>, an ATR-42, is deliberately crashed into the Atlas Mounta=
ins, killing all 44 on board.</li>
<li>September 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USAir=
_Flight_427" title=3D"USAir Flight 427">USAir Flight 427</a></b>, a Boeing =
737, crashes while attempting to land at Pittsburgh International Airport, =
killing all 132 people on board. Investigations showed that a fault in the =
Boeing 737 rudder was to blame for the crash.</li>
<li>September 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1994=
_Vanavara_Air_Disaster" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"1994 Vanavara Air Di=
saster">1994 Vanavara Air Disaster</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40 operated by C=
heremshanka Airlines crashes near Vanavara, Russia after running out of fue=
l in bad weather, killing 28 passengers and crew.</li>
<li>October 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_A=
seman_Airlines_Flight_746" title=3D"Iran Aseman Airlines Flight 746">Iran A=
seman Airlines Flight 746</a></b>, a Fokker F-28, crashes into a mountain n=
ear Natanz, Iran, due to double engine failure, killing all 66 on board.</l=
i>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Eagle_Flight_4184" title=3D"American Eagle Flight 4184">American Eagle F=
light 4184</a></b>, an ATR 72 turboprop, crashes near Roselawn, Indiana, wh=
ile waiting to land at Chicago, because of ice buildup on its wings. All 68=
 people on board die.</li>
<li>November 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scandi=
navian_Airlines_System_Flight_347" title=3D"Scandinavian Airlines System Fl=
ight 347">Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 347</a></b>, a McDonnell Doug=
las MD-82 operating a domestic flight in Norway, is hijacked by a Bosnian N=
ational; after landing at Bod=C3=B8 Airport to release some hostages, the a=
ircraft flies on to Oslo Airport where the hijacker later surrenders.</li>
<li>November 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_F=
light_427" title=3D"TWA Flight 427">TWA Flight 427</a></b>, a McDonnell Dou=
glas MD-82, collides with a Superior Aviation Cessna 441 on the runway at L=
ambert-St. Louis International Airport, killing the pilot and passenger in =
the Cessna; there are no fatalities on board the MD-82.</li>
<li>December 11 =E2=80=93 A bomb explodes on board <b><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippine_Airlines_Flight_434" title=3D"Philippine Air=
lines Flight 434">Philippine Airlines Flight 434</a></b>, a Boeing 747, kil=
ling one passenger, in a prelude to the terrorist <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Bojinka_plot" title=3D"Bojinka plot">Bojinka plot</a>. Desp=
ite subsequent difficulties in controlling the aircraft, the crew succeeds =
in making an emergency landing at Naha, Okinawa.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger=
ia_Airways_Flight_9805" title=3D"Nigeria Airways Flight 9805">Nigeria Airwa=
ys Flight 9805</a></b>, a Boeing 707 operating a cargo flight between Saudi=
 Arabia and Nigeria, suffers an in-flight fire before crashing into marshla=
nd in Nigeria; both passengers and one of the three crew members are killed=
.</li>
<li>December 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_A=
lg%C3%A9rie_Flight_702P" title=3D"Air Alg=C3=A9rie Flight 702P">Air Alg=C3=
=A9rie Flight 702P</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes on approach to Coventry A=
irport, England, killing all five on board.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_F=
rance_Flight_8969" title=3D"Air France Flight 8969">Air France Flight 8969<=
/a></b>, an Airbus A300, is hijacked on the tarmac at Algiers, Algeria, by =
the militant group GIA. After a two-day standoff, the plane is allowed to f=
ly to Marseille, France, where it is stormed by French commandos who kill t=
he hijackers.</li>
<li>December 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turki=
sh_Airlines_Flight_278" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 278">Turkish Airli=
nes Flight 278</a></b>, a Boeing 737-400, crashes on final approach to Van =
Ferit Melen Airport in eastern Turkey in driving snow. Five of the seven cr=
ew and 52 of the 69 passengers are killed.</li></ul>

<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

<ul><li>January 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In=

>, a Douglas DC-9, crashes in a lagoon near Mar=C3=ADa La Baja, Colombia du=
e to an improperly set altimeter, killing 51 of 52 on board.</li>
<li>January 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bristo=
w_Helicopters_Flight_56C" title=3D"Bristow Helicopters Flight 56C">Bristow =
Helicopters Flight 56C</a></b>, a Eurocopter Super Puma, is struck by light=
ning and is forced to make an emergency landing in the North Sea; all 18 on=
 board survive.</li>
<li>March 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAROM_Fl=
ight_371" title=3D"TAROM Flight 371">TAROM Flight 371</a></b>, an Airbus A3=
10, crashes near Balote=C8=99ti, Romania due to mechanical failure and pilo=
t error, killing all 60 on board.</li>
<li>May 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knight_Air=
_Flight_816" title=3D"Knight Air Flight 816">Knight Air Flight 816</a></b>,=
 an Embraer EMB 110 Bandeirante crashes whilst trying to return to Leeds Br=
adford Airport, UK in poor weather. All 12 passengers and crew are killed.<=
/li>
<li>June 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ansett_New=
_Zealand_Flight_703" title=3D"Ansett New Zealand Flight 703">Ansett New Zea=
land Flight 703</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-8, crashes during a land=
ing approach near the Tararua Ranges, New Zealand, killing four of the 21 p=
eople on board.</li>
<li>June 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_Nippo=
n_Airways_Flight_857" title=3D"All Nippon Airways Flight 857">All Nippon Ai=
rways Flight 857</a></b>, a Boeing 747SR, is hijacked on a domestic flight =
between Tokyo and Hakodate in Japan; after landing at its destination, the =
aircraft is later stormed by police and the hijacker is arrested; all 365 p=
eople on board survive the incident.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airstan_=
incident" title=3D"Airstan incident">Airstan</a></b>  by Taliban-controlled=
 fighter aircraft before being forced to divert to Kandahar International A=
irport in Afghanistan; the seven crew are held captive for over a year befo=
re overpowering their captors and fleeing in the aircraft.</li>
<li>August 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aviateca=
_Flight_901" title=3D"Aviateca Flight 901">Aviateca Flight 901</a></b>, a B=
oeing 737, crashes into San Vicente volcano while on approach to Cuscatl=C3=
=A1n International Airport; all 65 on board die.</li>
<li>August 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlanti=
c_Southeast_Airlines_Flight_529" title=3D"Atlantic Southeast Airlines Fligh=
t 529">Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight 529</a></b>, an Embraer EMB 120, =
crashes in a field near Carrollton, Georgia, United States, killing nine of=
 the 29 people on board.</li>
<li>September 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mala=
ysia_Airlines_Flight_2133" title=3D"Malaysia Airlines Flight 2133">Malaysia=
 Airlines Flight 2133</a></b>, a Fokker 50, crashes into a shantytown in Ma=
laysia due to pilot error, killing 34 of 53 on board.</li>
<li>November 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_1572" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 1572">American =
Airlines Flight 1572</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-83, shears off treetop=
s on approach, trees ingested into the engine causing them to flame out and=
 shutdown. The aircraft impacts the runway antenna equipment before rolling=
 to a stop. There is one minor injury of the 78 people on board.</li>
<li>November 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger=
ia_Airways_Flight_357" title=3D"Nigeria Airways Flight 357">Nigeria Airways=
 Flight 357</a></b>, a Boeing 737, overruns the runway while landing at Kad=
una Airport, killing 11 of 138 on board.</li>
<li>December 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camero=
on_Airlines_Flight_3701" title=3D"Cameroon Airlines Flight 3701">Cameroon A=
irlines Flight 3701</a></b>, a Boeing 737, loses control and crashes while =
on approach to Douala International Airport, Cameroon; of the 76 on board, =
five survive.</li>
<li>December 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerba=
ijan_Airlines_Flight_56" title=3D"Azerbaijan Airlines Flight 56">Azerbaijan=
 Airlines Flight 56</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes on climbout from Nak=
hchivan Airport after an engine fails due to improper maintenance, killing =
52 of 82 on board.</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khabar=
ovsk_United_Air_Group_Flight_3949" title=3D"Khabarovsk United Air Group Fli=
ght 3949">Khabarovsk United Air Group Flight 3949</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154=
B crashes after entering a steep downward spiral while at cruising altitude=
. All 98 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/1995_Air_St._Martin_Beech_1900_crash" title=3D"1995 Air St. Martin Beech 1=
900 crash">1995 Air St. Martin Beech 1900 crash</a></b>, a Beechcraft 1900D=
 crashes near Belle-Anse, Haiti, killing all 20 people on board.</li>
<li>December 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banat=
_Air_Flight_166" title=3D"Banat Air Flight 166">Banat Air Flight 166</a></b=
>, a Romavia Antonov An-24, crashes after taking off from Verona Airport, b=
ecause of overloading and ice accumulation on the wings; all 49 people on b=
oard are killed.</li>
<li>December 18 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/1995_Trans_Service_Airlift_Electra_crash" title=3D"1995 Trans Service Air=
lift Electra crash">1995 Trans Service Airlift Electra crash</a></b>, a Loc=
kheed L-188 Electra crashes shortly after takeoff from Jamba, Angola, due t=
o overloading and shifting baggage; of the 144 people on board, only three =
survive.</li>
<li>December 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_965" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 965">American Ai=
rlines Flight 965</a></b>, a Boeing 757, crashes into a mountain while appr=
oaching Alfonso Bonilla Arag=C3=B3n International Airport in Palmira, Colom=
bia, killing 159 of 163 on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1996">1996</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D83" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1996">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:TWA800reconstruction.jpg" c=

<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/199=
6_Air_Africa_crash" title=3D"1996 Air Africa crash">1996 Air Africa crash</=
a></b>, an overloaded Antonov An-32 aborts takeoff and overruns into a mark=
et in Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing 227 people on the=
 ground.</li>
<li>February 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birgen=
air_Flight_301" title=3D"Birgenair Flight 301">Birgenair Flight 301</a></b>=
, a Boeing 757, with 189 people on board, crashes into the ocean off Puerto=
 Plata in the Dominican Republic shortly after taking off. All passengers a=
nd crew are killed.</li>
<li>February 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fauce=
tt_Flight_251" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Faucett Flight 251">Faucett F=
light 251</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes into a hill while attempting to la=
nd at Arequipa, Peru. All 123 people on board die.</li>
<li>May 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ValuJet_Fl=
ight_592" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"ValuJet Flight 592">ValuJet Flight=
 592</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes in the Everglades near Miam=
i, Florida, because of a fire in its cargo hold. All 110 people on board ar=
e killed.</li>
<li>June 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastwind_A=
irlines_Flight_517" title=3D"Eastwind Airlines Flight 517">Eastwind Airline=
s Flight 517</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, loses rudder control while on appro=
ach to Richmond International Airport, Richmond, Virginia, and makes an eme=
rgency landing; no fatalities.</li>
<li>June 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garuda_In=
donesia_Flight_865" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 865">Garuda Indonesia =
Flight 865</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-10, aborts takeoff due to an eng=
ine failure and crashes into a threshold at Fukuoka Airport, Fukuoka, Japan=
, killing three of 275 on board.</li>
<li>July 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Air_=
Lines_Flight_1288" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 1288">Delta Air Lines Fl=
ight 1288</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-88, experiences an uncontained en=
gine failure during takeoff on Runway 17 at Pensacola, Florida. Fragments f=
rom the number one (left) Pratt &amp; Whitney JT8D-219 turbofan engine pene=
trate the fuselage, killing two and seriously injuring two of the 142 peopl=
e on board.</li>
<li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TWA_Fligh=
t_800" title=3D"TWA Flight 800">TWA Flight 800</a></b>, a Boeing 747, explo=
des in mid-air above the ocean off East Moriches, New York, killing all 230=
 people on board; 70% of passengers are sucked out during the explosion.</l=
i>
<li>August 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spair_A=
irlines_Flight_3601" title=3D"Spair Airlines Flight 3601">Spair Airlines Fl=
ight 3601</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-76, crashes near Belgrade, Yugoslavia, wi=
th 11 fatalities.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vnukovo=
_Airlines_Flight_2801" title=3D"Vnukovo Airlines Flight 2801">Vnukovo Airli=
nes Flight 2801</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes into a mountain on Spits=
bergen, an island in the Norwegian archipelago of Svalbard, killing all 141=
 on board.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemus=
_Air_Flight_7081" title=3D"Hemus Air Flight 7081">Hemus Air Flight 7081</a>=
</b>, a Tupolev Tu-154 is hijacked while en route from Beirut, Lebanon to V=
arna, Bulgaria. After landing in Varna, the 150 passengers are traded for f=
uel. The plane then flies on to Oslo Gardermoen Airport, Norway, where the =
hijacker later surrenders.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroper=
%C3%BA_Flight_603" title=3D"Aeroper=C3=BA Flight 603">Aeroper=C3=BA Flight =
603</a></b>, a Boeing 757, crashes into the ocean off Pasamayo, Peru, becau=
se of a maintenance error. All 70 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAM_Tr=
ansportes_A%C3%A9reos_Regionais_Flight_402" title=3D"TAM Transportes A=C3=
=A9reos Regionais Flight 402">TAM Transportes A=C3=A9reos Regionais Flight =
402</a></b>, a Fokker 100, crashes shortly after takeoff from Congonhas-S=
=C3=A3o Paulo Airport, Brazil, striking an apartment building and several h=
ouses. All 90 passengers and six crew members on board die. Three people ar=
e killed on the ground.</li>
<li>November 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ADC_Ai=
rlines_Flight_086" title=3D"ADC Airlines Flight 086">ADC Airlines Flight 08=
6</a></b>, a Boeing 727, crashes when the crew loses control of the aircraf=
t while avoiding a mid-air collision on approach to Lagos, Nigeria. All 144=
 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1996_=
Charkhi_Dadri_mid-air_collision" title=3D"1996 Charkhi Dadri mid-air collis=
ion">1996 Charkhi Dadri mid-air collision</a></b>: Saudi Arabian Airlines F=
light 763, a Boeing 747, collides in mid-air with Kazakhstan Airlines Fligh=
t 1907, an Ilyushin Il-76, near Charkhi Dadri, India. All 312 on board the =
Boeing 747 and all 37 on board the Ilyushin Il-76 are killed. It is the <b>=
deadliest mid-air collision in aviation history</b>.</li>
<li>November 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Express_Flight_5925" title=3D"United Express Flight 5925">United Express =
Flight 5925</a></b>, a Beechcraft 1900, collides with a privately owned Bee=
chcraft King Air at Quincy Regional Airport, Illinois; killing all 14 on bo=
ard both aircraft.</li>
<li>November 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethio=
pian_Airlines_Flight_961" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Flight 961">Ethiopian=
 Airlines Flight 961</a></b>, a Boeing 767, is hijacked over Kenya. The air=
craft runs out of fuel, and the pilot attempts to ditch the aircraft in the=
 ocean off Moroni, Comoros. Of the 175 people on board, 125 are killed (inc=
luding the three hijackers).</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirgan=
tara_Air_Service_Flight_5940" title=3D"Dirgantara Air Service Flight 5940">=
Dirgantara Air Service Flight 5940</a></b>, a CASA C-212 Aviocar crashes in=
to a gas factory shortly after takeoff from Syamsudin Noor International Ai=
rport, Indonesia following an engine failure. 16 of the 17 passengers and c=
rew are killed, as well as two on the ground.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1997">1997</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D84" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1997">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Com=
air_Flight_3272" title=3D"Comair Flight 3272">Comair Flight 3272</a></b>, a=
n Embraer EMB 120 Bras=C3=ADlia, crashes near Ida, Michigan, during a snows=
torm, killing all 29 on board.</li>
<li>March 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stavropo=
lskaya_Aktsionernaya_Avia_Flight_1023" title=3D"Stavropolskaya Aktsionernay=
a Avia Flight 1023">Stavropolskaya Aktsionernaya Avia Flight 1023</a></b>, =
an Antonov An-24, breaks up in flight and crashes near Cherkessk, Russia; a=
ll 50 on board die.</li>
<li>April 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merpati_=
Nusantara_Airlines_Flight_106" title=3D"Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 1=
06">Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 106</a></b>, a BAe ATP crashes during=
 a failed go-around in bad weather at Buluh Tumbang International Airport, =
Indonesia. 15 of the 53 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_South=
ern_Airlines_Flight_3456" title=3D"China Southern Airlines Flight 3456">Chi=
na Southern Airlines Flight 3456</a></b>, a Boeing 737, makes a hard landin=
g in Shenzhen, China, during poor weather and crashes, killing 35 of the 74=
 people on board.</li>
<li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sempati_A=
ir_Flight_304" title=3D"Sempati Air Flight 304">Sempati Air Flight 304</a><=
/b>, a Fokker F27, crashes shortly after takeoff from Husein Sastranegara I=
nternational Airport, killing 28 people on board.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Litto=
ral_Flight_701" title=3D"Air Littoral Flight 701">Air Littoral Flight 701</=
a></b>, an ATR 42 flying from France to Italy, overshoots the runway at Flo=
rence Airport and crashes into a ditch; all 14 passengers and two of the th=
ree crew members survive, but the pilot is killed in the accident.</li>
<li>July 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FedEx_Exp=
ress_Flight_14" title=3D"FedEx Express Flight 14">FedEx Express Flight 14</=
a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11, crashes upon landing at Newark Liberty I=
nternational Airport; the two crew members and three passengers escape unin=
jured.</li>
<li>August 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_A=
ir_Flight_801" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 801">Korean Air Flight 801</a></b=
>, a Boeing 747, crashes while attempting to land in heavy rain at Guam Int=
ernational Airport; of the 254 people on board, 229 die.</li>
<li>August 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fine_Air=
_Flight_101" title=3D"Fine Air Flight 101">Fine Air Flight 101</a></b>, a M=
cDonnell Douglas DC-8-61F, crashes after take-off at Miami International Ai=
rport; all four people on board and one person on the ground are killed.</l=
i>
<li>August 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formosa=
_Airlines_Flight_7601" title=3D"Formosa Airlines Flight 7601">Formosa Airli=
nes Flight 7601</a></b>, a Dornier Do 228, crashes while attempting to land=
 at Beigan, Lienchiang, in the Matsu Islands. All 16 passengers and crew on=
 board are killed.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietn=
am_Airlines_Flight_815" title=3D"Vietnam Airlines Flight 815">Vietnam Airli=
nes Flight 815</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-134, crashes on approach to Phnom Penh=
 International Airport in heavy rain, killing 64 of the 66 people on board.=
</li>
<li>September 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal=
_Brunei_Airlines_Flight_238" title=3D"Royal Brunei Airlines Flight 238">Roy=
al Brunei Airlines Flight 238</a></b>, a Dornier Do 228, crashes into a hil=
lside in Lambir Hills National Park, killing all 10 on board.</li>
<li>September 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garu=
da_Indonesia_Flight_152" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 152">Garuda Indon=
esia Flight 152</a></b>, an Airbus A300, crashes into a mountain near Buah =
Nabar, Indonesia, killing all 234 on board.</li>
<li>October 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austra=
l_L%C3%ADneas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_2553" title=3D"Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9=
reas Flight 2553">Austral L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 2553</a></b>, a Mc=
Donnell Douglas DC-9, crashes near Fray Bentos, Uruguay, traveling from Pos=
adas to Buenos Aires, resulting in the death of all 74 occupants.</li>
<li>December 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tajik=
istan_Airlines_Flight_3183" title=3D"Tajikistan Airlines Flight 3183">Tajik=
istan Airlines Flight 3183</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes into the dese=
rt near Sharjah Airport, of the 86 on board, only the flight engineer survi=
ves.</li>
<li>December 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_C=
anada_Flight_646" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 646">Air Canada Flight 646</a>=
</b>, a Bombardier CRJ100ER operating a domestic flight in Canada, crashes =
on landing at Fredericton, New Brunswick, after a failed go-around attempt;=
 all 42 passengers and crew survive the accident.</li>
<li>December 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeros=
vit_Flight_241" title=3D"Aerosvit Flight 241">Aerosvit Flight 241</a></b>, =
a Yakovlev Yak-42, crashes near Thessaloniki, Greece, killing all 70 people=
 on board.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SilkA=
ir_Flight_185" title=3D"SilkAir Flight 185">SilkAir Flight 185</a></b>, a B=
oeing 737, crashes into the Musi River near Palembang, Indonesia, killing a=
ll 102 people on board.</li>
<li>December 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unite=
d_Airlines_Flight_826_(1997)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"United Airline=
s Flight 826 (1997)">United Airlines Flight 826</a></b>, a Boeing 747, enco=
unters severe turbulence two hours into the flight; the aircraft safely lan=
ds back in Tokyo; all survive the accident, but a passenger dies later; des=
pite having no damage, the aircraft is written off.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1998">1998</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D85" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1998">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Swissair_111_debris.jpg" cl=
