<ul><li>February 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ce=
bu_Pacific_Flight_387" title=3D"Cebu Pacific Flight 387">Cebu Pacific Fligh=
t 387</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes into a mountain near Mount=
 Sumagaya in Misamis Oriental in the Philippines, killing all 104 passenger=
s and crew members on board.</li>
<li>February 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Airlines_Flight_676" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 676">China Airlines Fl=
ight 676</a></b>, an Airbus A300, crashes into a residential area while att=
empting to land in Taipei, Taiwan. All 196 people on board are killed, in a=
ddition to six on the ground.</li>
<li>March 19 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1=
998_Ariana_Afghan_Airlines_crash" title=3D"1998 Ariana Afghan Airlines cras=
h">1998 Ariana Afghan Airlines crash</a></b>, a Boeing 727 crashes into Sha=
rki Baratayi Mountain while on approach to Kabul International Airport, kil=
ling all 45 on board.</li>
<li>March 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippi=
ne_Airlines_Flight_137" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 137">Philippine=
 Airlines Flight 137</a></b>, an Airbus A320, overshoots the end of the run=
way while landing at Bacolod City in the Philippines, plowing through sever=
al houses. None of the passengers was harmed, but three people on the groun=
d are killed and several more injured.</li>
<li>April 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fran=
ce_Flight_422" title=3D"Air France Flight 422">Air France Flight 422</a></b=
>, a Boeing 727 leased from TAME Airlines, crashes into the mountains east =
of Bogot=C3=A1, Colombia, on takeoff from El Dorado International Airport o=
f Bogot=C3=A1 in foggy weather. All 53 passengers and crew die.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998=
_Occidental_Petroleum_Boeing_737_crash" title=3D"1998 Occidental Petroleum =
Boeing 737 crash">1998 Occidental Petroleum Boeing 737 crash</a></b>, a Boe=
ing 737 leased from the Peruvian Air Force crashes while on approach to Alf=
=C3=A9rez FAP Alfredo Vladimir Sara Bauer Airport, killing 75 of 88 on boar=
d.</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIA_Flight=
_544" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"PIA Flight 544">Pakistan International=
 Airlines Flight 544</a></b>, a Fokker F-27, is hijacked shortly after take=
off by three armed men. F-16 fighter jets intercept the plane and force it =
to land. The hijackers are arrested and sentenced to death. All 38 on board=
 survive.</li>
<li>May 26 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998_M=
IAT_Mongolian_Airlines_crash" title=3D"1998 MIAT Mongolian Airlines crash">=
1998 MIAT Mongolian Airlines crash</a></b>: a Harbin Y-12 crashes 13 minute=
s after takeoff from Erdenet Airport, Mongolia, killing all 28 passengers a=
nd crew.</li>
<li>June 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propair_F=
light_420" title=3D"Propair Flight 420">Propair Flight 420</a></b>, a Fairc=
hild Metroliner crashes shortly after takeoff from Dorval Airport (now Mont=
r=C3=A9al=E2=80=93Pierre Elliott Trudeau International Airport), Canada fol=
lowing an inflight fire. All 11 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>July 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proteus_A=
irlines_Flight_706" title=3D"Proteus Airlines Flight 706">Proteus Airlines =
Flight 706</a></b>: a Beechcraft 1900D collides in mid-air with a light air=
craft over Quiberon Bay. Both aircraft crash into the sea, killing 15 peopl=
e.</li>
<li>August 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_A=
ir_Flight_8702" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 8702">Korean Air Flight 8702</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 747-400 flying from Japan to South Korea, rolls off the runw=
ay at Gimpo Airport in Seoul and crashes into a ditch; all 395 passengers a=
nd crew survive the accident.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanma_=
Airways_Flight_635" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Myanma Airways Flight 63=
5">Myanma Airways Flight 635</a></b>, a Fokker F-27 Friendship, crashes whi=
le on approach to Tachilek Airport; all 36 on board die.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cubana_=
de_Aviaci%C3%B3n_Flight_389" title=3D"Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 389">C=
ubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 389</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154M overruns the r=
unway whilst taking off from Quito's Mariscal Sucre International Airport, =
Ecuador, proceeding to crash into a soccer field. 70 of the 91 passengers a=
nd crew are killed, along with 10 on the ground.</li>
<li>September 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swiss=
air_Flight_111" title=3D"Swissair Flight 111">Swissair Flight 111</a></b>, =
a McDonnell Douglas MD-11, crashes into the sea near Halifax, Nova Scotia i=
n Canada, because of an onboard fire. All 229 people on board die.</li>
<li>September 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pauk=
nAir_Flight_4101" title=3D"PauknAir Flight 4101">PauknAir Flight 4101</a></=
b>, a BAe 146, leaves M=C3=A1laga but never reaches its destination in Meli=
lla. All 38 passengers and four crew onboard die.</li>
<li>September 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion=
air_Flight_602" title=3D"Lionair Flight 602">Lionair Flight 602</a></b>, an=
 Antonov An-24, is shot down by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam and cr=
ashes off the coast of Jaffna, Sri Lanka, killing all 55 on board.</li>
<li>October 10 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/19=
98_Lignes_A%C3%A9riennes_Congolaises_crash" title=3D"1998 Lignes A=C3=A9rie=
nnes Congolaises crash">1998 Lignes A=C3=A9riennes Congolaises crash</a></b=
> occurs when rebels using a Strela 2 missile shoot down the Boeing 727, wh=
ich crashes near Kindu, Democratic Republic of Congo, killing all 41 on boa=
rd.</li>
<li>December 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_=
Airways_International_Flight_261" title=3D"Thai Airways International Fligh=
t 261">Thai Airways International Flight 261</a></b>, an Airbus A310, crash=
es during poor weather near Surat Thani, Thailand. Of the 146 people on boa=
rd, 102 are killed.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"1999">1999</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D86" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 1999">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

rew on board.</li>

nier 328, loses control and overruns the runway while landing at Genoa Airp=
ort in Italy; 3 passengers and one crew member are killed.</li>

</b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-83 operating a domestic flight in South Korea,=
 overshoots the runway on landing in Pohang; all 156 people on board surviv=
e the incident but the aircraft is destroyed.</li>

lli, Ceyhan, Turkey; all six crew die.</li>

go Flight 6316</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11F, crashes shortly after t=

ll as five on the ground, are killed.</li>
<li>June 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_A=

oard, skids off the runway on landing and crashes into a steel walkway at L=
ittle Rock, Arkansas during strong winds; 11 are killed, and 86 are injured=
.</li>
<li>July 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_Nippo=

ays Flight 61</a></b>, a Boeing 747, is hijacked by a passenger, Yuji Nishi=

mbraer EMB 110 Bandeirante, crashes into a mountain en route to Nadi Intern=
ational Airport, Fiji. All 17 passengers and crew are killed.</li>

 228, crashes into a mountain whilst returning to S=C3=A3o Pedro Airport, C=

 die.</li>

onnell Douglas MD-90, suffers an explosion and catches fire after landing i=

<li>August 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAPA_Fl=

>, a BAe 748, collides with a telecommunications tower whilst on approach i=

<li>September 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brit=

rt of a golf course. All onboard including 30 injured passengers survive.</=

 Boeing 767 bound for Cairo, Egypt, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean off Nan=
tucket, Massachusetts, killing all 217 passengers and crew; cause is disput=
ed: a deliberate suicide/homicide act by the relief first officer according=
 to the NTSB, vs. a Boeing mechanical flaw according to Egyptian aviation a=
uthorities.</li>

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2000">2000</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=

 section: 2000">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cr=
ossair_Flight_498" title=3D"Crossair Flight 498">Crossair Flight 498</a></b=
>, a Saab 340, crashes two minutes after takeoff in Niederhasli, Switzerlan=
d, killing all 10 people on board.</li>
<li>January 13 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2000=
_Marsa_Brega_Short_360_crash" title=3D"2000 Marsa Brega Short 360 crash">Sh=
ort 360 operated by Avisto ditches</a></b> into the sea near Marsa Brega, L=
ibya, as a result of ice buildup, killing 22 of the 41 passengers and crew =
on board.</li>
<li>January 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya_=
Airways_Flight_431" title=3D"Kenya Airways Flight 431">Kenya Airways Flight=
 431</a></b>, an Airbus A310, carrying 169 passengers and 10 crew members, =
crashes into the Atlantic Ocean off C=C3=B4te d'Ivoire after takeoff from A=
bidjan; only 10 of the 179 people on board survive.</li>
<li>January 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska=
_Airlines_Flight_261" title=3D"Alaska Airlines Flight 261">Alaska Airlines =
Flight 261</a></b>, an MD-83, crashes into the Pacific Ocean off Point Mugu=
, California, after experiencing problems with its horizontal stabilizer; a=
ll 83 passengers and five crew members are killed.</li>
<li>February 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emery=
_Worldwide_Airlines_Flight_17" title=3D"Emery Worldwide Airlines Flight 17"=
>Emery Worldwide Airlines Flight 17</a></b>, a DC-8-71F crashes into a salv=
age yard shortly after takeoff from Sacramento Mather Airport, California, =
killing the three crew members on board.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southwest=
_Airlines_Flight_1455" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 1455">Southwest A=
irlines Flight 1455</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, overshoots the runway in Bur=
bank, California; 44 of the 142 people on board are injured, two seriously.=
</li>
<li>April 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Phil=
ippines_Flight_541" title=3D"Air Philippines Flight 541">Air Philippines Fl=
ight 541</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes in a coconut plantation on Sama=
l Island, Davao del Norte while preparing to approach the Davao Internation=
al Airport, killing all 131 people on board in the worst ever accident invo=
lving the 737-200.</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippine=
_Airlines_Flight_812" title=3D"Philippine Airlines Flight 812">Philippine A=
irlines Flight 812</a></b>, an Airbus A330-301 operating a domestic flight =
in the Philippines, undergoes an attempted hijacking shortly before landing=
 at Ninoy Aquino International Airport in Manila; all 290 passengers and cr=
ew survive the incident, but the hijacker jumps from the aircraft to his de=
ath.</li>
<li>June 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wuhan_Air=
lines_Flight_343" title=3D"Wuhan Airlines Flight 343">Wuhan Airlines Flight=
 343</a></b>, a Xian Y-7, is struck by lightning and crashes in Hanyang Dis=
trict, Wuhan, killing all 42 on board and another seven on the ground in th=
e worst ever accident involving the Y-7.</li>
<li>July 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mal%C3%A9v=
_Hungarian_Airlines_Flight_262" title=3D"Mal=C3=A9v Hungarian Airlines Flig=
ht 262">Mal=C3=A9v Hungarian Airlines Flight 262</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154,=
 lands on its belly at Thessaloniki International Airport in Greece; there =
are no serious injuries or fatalities.</li>
<li>July 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerocaribe=
_Flight_7831" title=3D"Aerocaribe Flight 7831">Aerocaribe Flight 7831</a></=
b>, a British Aerospace Jetstream 32, crashes near Chulum Ju=C3=A1rez, Mexi=
co, killing all 19 on board.</li>
<li>July 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hapag-Llo=
yd_Flight_3378" title=3D"Hapag-Lloyd Flight 3378">Hapag-Lloyd Flight 3378</=
a></b>, an Airbus A310, crash lands 650 metres (2,130&nbsp;ft) short of the=
 runway in Vienna after running out of fuel in flight; there are no serious=
 injuries or fatalities.</li>
<li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alliance_=
Air_Flight_7412" title=3D"Alliance Air Flight 7412">Alliance Air Flight 741=
2</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes into government housing in Patna, Indi=
a, as it approaches the airport, killing 55 of the 58 on board and five peo=
ple on the ground.</li>
<li>July 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Franc=
e_Flight_4590" title=3D"Air France Flight 4590">Air France Flight 4590</a><=
/b>, a Concorde crashes during takeoff from Paris, France, after striking d=
ebris on the runway, killing all 100 passengers and nine crew aboard as wel=
l as four people on the ground; the entire Concorde fleet is grounded for o=
ne year.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2000_Royal_N=
epal_Airlines_Twin_Otter_crash" title=3D"2000 Royal Nepal Airlines Twin Ott=
er crash"><b>A Royal Nepal Airlines de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter cr=
ashes</b></a> into Jarayakhali Hill in western Nepal, while operating a dom=
estic passenger flight from Bajhang Airport to Dhangadhi Airport, killing a=
ll 25 people on board.</li>
<li>August 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gulf_Ai=
r_Flight_072" title=3D"Gulf Air Flight 072">Gulf Air Flight 072</a></b>, an=
 Airbus A320, crashes into the Persian Gulf off Manama, Bahrain, while atte=
mpting to land; all 135 passengers and eight crew members are killed.</li>
<li>October 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lao_Av=
iation_Flight_703" title=3D"Lao Aviation Flight 703">Lao Aviation Flight 70=
3</a></b>, a Harbin Y-12 flying a domestic passenger flight in Laos, crashe=
s into a mountain 12&nbsp;km from Nathong Airport, killing eight of the 17 =
people on board.</li>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singap=
ore_Airlines_Flight_006" title=3D"Singapore Airlines Flight 006">Singapore =
Airlines Flight 006</a></b>, a Boeing 747-400, strikes construction equipme=
nt after using a closed runway for takeoff at Chiang Kai-shek International=
 Airport, Taiwan, killing 83 out of 179 people on board.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20=
00_ASA_Pesada_Antonov_An-24_crash" title=3D"2000 ASA Pesada Antonov An-24 c=
rash">ASA Pesada Antonov An-24RV crashes</a></b> shortly after takeoff from=
 Luanda's Quatro de Fevereiro International Airport, Angola, after sufferin=
g a catastrophic engine failure; all 57 passengers and crew are killed.</li=
>
<li>November 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirga=
ntara_Air_Service_Flight_3130" title=3D"Dirgantara Air Service Flight 3130"=
>Dirgantara Air Service Flight 3130</a></b>, a Britten Norman BN-2 Islander=
 operating a domestic flight in Indonesia, crashes into a forest on takeoff=
 from Datah Dawai Airport in East Kalimantan due to overloading and pilot e=
rror; all 18 occupants survive the incident but 11 are seriously injured.</=
li>
<li>December 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Briti=
sh_Airways_Flight_2069" title=3D"British Airways Flight 2069">British Airwa=
ys Flight 2069</a></b>, a Boeing 747-436 en route from Gatwick Airport, Eng=
land, to Nairobi in Kenya, experiences an attempted hijacking by a mentally=
 ill passenger who storms the cockpit at 35,000 feet (11&nbsp;km) and sends=
 the aircraft into a nosedive; the flight crew rescue the situation and non=
e of the 398 people on board is seriously injured.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ye=
menia_Flight_448" title=3D"Yemenia Flight 448">Yemenia Flight 448</a></b>, =
a Boeing 727, is hijacked 15 minutes after takeoff from Sana'a Internationa=
l Airport, Yemen; the crew makes an emergency landing at Djibouti; the hija=
cker is subdued with no casualties to the 91 passengers or 10 crew members =
on board.</li>
<li>January 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RUTACA=
_Airlines_Flight_225" title=3D"RUTACA Airlines Flight 225">RUTACA Airlines =
Flight 225</a></b>, a Douglas DC-3, crashes shortly after takeoff from Tom=
=C3=A1s de Heres Airport, Venezuela, as a result of an engine failure; all =
24 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>January 31 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/2001_Japan_Airlines_mid-air_incident" title=3D"2001 Japan Airlines mid-air=
 incident">2001 Japan Airlines mid-air incident</a></b>, Japan Airlines Fli=
ght 907, a Douglas DC-10, and Japan Airlines Flight 958, a Boeing 747, narr=
owly avoid colliding by a margin of 36 feet (11 meters) near <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yaizu,_Shizuoka" title=3D"Yaizu, Shizuoka">Yaizu=
</a>, Japan.</li>
<li>February 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logan=
air_Flight_670A" title=3D"Loganair Flight 670A">Loganair Flight 670A</a></b=
>, a Short 360 operating a postal flight, crashes shortly after takeoff fro=
m Edinburgh Airport, Scotland, as a result of a double engine failure; both=
 crew members are killed.</li>
<li>March 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_Airw=
ays_International_Flight_114" title=3D"Thai Airways International Flight 11=
4">Thai Airways International Flight 114</a></b>, a Boeing 737-400, is dest=
royed by an explosion while on the tarmac at Don Mueang Airport, Thailand, =
prior to boarding; one flight attendant is killed in the explosion.</li>
<li>March 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Cara=
%C3%AFbes_Flight_1501" title=3D"Air Cara=C3=AFbes Flight 1501">Air Cara=C3=
=AFbes Flight 1501</a></b>, a DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes into a house whilst=
 on approach into Saint Barth=C3=A9lemy Airport, Guadeloupe; all 19 passeng=
ers and crew, as well as one person on the ground, are killed.</li>
<li>March 29 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2=
001_Avjet_Aspen_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2001 Avjet Aspen cras=
h">2001 Avjet Aspen crash</a></b>, an Avjet charter flight, a Gulfstream II=
I jet with 15 passengers and three crew, crashes on approach into Aspen, Co=
lorado, killing all on board.</li>
<li>May 17 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
1_Faraz_Qeshm_Airlines_Yak-40_crash" title=3D"2001 Faraz Qeshm Airlines Yak=
-40 crash">2001 Faraz Qeshm Airlines Yak-40 crash</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-4=
0 crashes into mountains en route to Gorgan Airport, Iran amid poor weather=
 conditions; all 30 passengers and crew are killed, including Iran's Minist=
er of Roads and Transportation, Rahman Dadman.</li>
<li>July 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vladivosto=
k_Air_Flight_352" title=3D"Vladivostok Air Flight 352">Vladivostok Air Flig=
ht 352</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, enters a flat spin on approach to Irkutsk=
 Airport in Irkutsk, Russia, crashes down onto its belly and bursts into fl=
ames in a wooded area, killing all 145 aboard.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Tra=
nsat_Flight_236" title=3D"Air Transat Flight 236">Air Transat Flight 236</a=
></b>, an Airbus A330, makes an emergency landing in the Azores after runni=
ng out of fuel over the Atlantic Ocean; some tires blow out upon landing, c=
ausing a fire that is extinguished by emergency personnel on the ground; no=
ne of the 293 passengers or 13 crew on board the aircraft is seriously inju=
red.</li>
<li>August 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binter_=
Mediterr%C3%A1neo_Flight_8261" title=3D"Binter Mediterr=C3=A1neo Flight 826=
1">Binter Mediterr=C3=A1neo Flight 8261</a></b>, a CASA CN-235, suffers por=
t engine failure and crashes onto the N-340 road while attempting to make a=
n emergency landing at Ruiz Picasso International Airport, killing four of =
43 on board; the pilot initially survives, but dies several hours later.</l=
i>
<li><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/September_11_attacks" title=
=3D"September 11 attacks">September 11 attacks</a></b>:
<ul><li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
American_Airlines_Flight_11" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 11">American=
 Airlines Flight 11</a></b>, a Boeing 767-200ER with 92 people on board, is=
 hijacked after taking off from Boston, and is flown into the north tower o=
f the World Trade Center in New York City; all on board are killed as well =
as around 1600 people on the ground and in the building; the collapse of bo=
th towers brings the total death toll from the two crashes to at least 2,76=
3, the deadliest disaster involving commercial aircraft.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit=
ed_Airlines_Flight_175" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 175">United Airline=
s Flight 175</a></b>, a Boeing 767-200 with 65 people on board, is hijacked=
 after taking off from Boston and is flown into the south tower of the Worl=
d Trade Center in New York City; all on board are killed as well as around =
900 people on the ground and in the building; the collapse of both towers b=
rings the total death toll from the two crashes to at least 2,763, the dead=
liest disaster involving commercial aircraft.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amer=
ican_Airlines_Flight_77" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 77">American Air=
lines Flight 77</a></b>, a Boeing 757-200 with 64 people on board, is hijac=
ked after taking off from Dulles International Airport and is flown into th=
e Pentagon; all on board are killed as well as 125 people in the building a=
nd on the ground.</li>
<li>September 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit=
ed_Airlines_Flight_93" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 93">United Airlines =
Flight 93</a></b>, a Boeing 757-200 with 44 people on board, is hijacked af=
ter taking off from Newark, New Jersey; passengers struggle with the hijack=
ers, and the aircraft crashes in a field near Shanksville, Pennsylvania, ki=
lling all on board.</li></ul></li>
<li>September 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAM_=
Flight_9755" title=3D"TAM Flight 9755">TAM Airlines Flight 9755</a></b>, a =
Fokker 100 operating a domestic flight in Brazil, suffers an uncontained en=
gine failure near Belo Horizonte; debris shatters three windows causing dec=
ompression of the aircraft; one passenger is partially blown out of the cab=
in and later dies, but the other 87 passengers and crew survive.</li>
<li>October 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siberia=
_Airlines_Flight_1812" title=3D"Siberia Airlines Flight 1812">Siberia Airli=
nes Flight 1812</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, is shot down by the Ukrainian mi=
litary over the Black Sea; all 66 passengers and 12 crew members are killed=
.</li>
<li>October 8 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Linate_Airport_disaster" title=3D"Linate Airport disaster">Linate Airport d=
isaster</a></b>, Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 686, an MD-87, crashes=
 into a Cessna business jet on takeoff from Milan, Italy, then swerves into=
 a baggage handling building and catches fire; all 110 people on board the =
MD-87 and all four in the Cessna are killed, as well as four people on the =
ground.</li>
<li>November 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_587" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 587">American Ai=
rlines Flight 587</a></b>, an Airbus A300, crashes into a Queens neighborho=
od in New York City when the plane's vertical tail fin snaps off just after=
 takeoff due to overuse of the rudder by the first officer during a wake tu=
rbulence encounter; all 251 passengers and nine crew members on board are k=
illed as well as five people on the ground.</li>
<li>November 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross=
air_Flight_3597" title=3D"Crossair Flight 3597">Crossair Flight 3597</a></b=
>, an Avro RJ100, crashes near Bassersdorf, Switzerland, while attempting t=
o land in Z=C3=BCrich; 24 of the 33 people on board lose their lives.</li>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 On board <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/2001_shoe_bomb_attempt" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2001 shoe bomb a=
ttempt">American Airlines Flight 63</a></b>, a Boeing 767, a passenger, <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Reid" title=3D"Richard Reid">=
Richard Reid</a>, attempts to detonate explosives hidden in his shoes, but =
fails and is subdued by two flight attendants and passengers; the aircraft =
lands safely in Boston.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2002">2002</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D90" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 2002">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li=
on_Air_Flight_386" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Lion Air Flight 386">Lion=
 Air Flight 386</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes while attempting to take=
 off from Riau, Indonesia; all 103 on board survive.</li>
<li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garuda=
_Indonesia_Flight_421" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 421">Garuda Indones=
ia Flight 421</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, experiences a dual flameout after =
entering a thunderstorm, and crashes into the Bengawan Solo River in Indone=
sia; a flight attendant is killed but the other 59 people on board survive =
the accident.</li>
<li>January 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAME_F=
light_120" title=3D"TAME Flight 120">TAME Flight 120</a></b>, a Boeing 727,=
 crashes into a volcano on approach to Tulc=C3=A1n, Ecuador, in low-visibil=
ity conditions; all 94 on board are killed.</li>
<li>February 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_=
Air_Tours_Flight_956" title=3D"Iran Air Tours Flight 956">Iran Air Tours Fl=
ight 956</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes into the Sefid Kooh mountains d=
uring heavy rain, snow, and dense fog, while descending for Khorramabad Air=
port; all twelve crew members and 107 passengers are killed.</li>
<li>April 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Chin=
a_Flight_129" title=3D"Air China Flight 129">Air China Flight 129</a></b>, =
a Boeing 767-200ER, crashes into a hill during a landing attempt at Busan, =
South Korea, in misty conditions; of the 155 passengers and 11 crew, 37 sur=
vive.</li>
<li>May 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EAS_Airline=
s_Flight_4226" title=3D"EAS Airlines Flight 4226">EAS Airlines Flight 4226<=
/a></b>, a BAC 1-11 500 series, crashes into the Gwammaja neighborhood at K=
ano, Nigeria, shortly after takeoff; the ensuing crash results in the death=
s of 73 on board and at least 30 civilians on the ground.</li>
<li>May 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EgyptAir_Fl=
ight_843" title=3D"EgyptAir Flight 843">EgyptAir Flight 843</a></b>, a Boei=
ng 737-566, crashes near Tunis, Tunisia, while landing in rough weather; of=
 the 62 people on board, 14 die.</li>
<li>May 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_North=
ern_Airlines_Flight_6136" title=3D"China Northern Airlines Flight 6136">Chi=
na Northern Airlines Flight 6136</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, crashe=
s near Dalian, China, after a passenger sets fire to the cabin with gasolin=
e; all 103 passengers and nine crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Airl=
ines_Flight_611" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 611">China Airlines Flight =
611</a></b>, a Boeing 747-200B, disintegrates above the Taiwan Strait in mi=
d-flight due to maintenance error, killing all 225 people on board.</li>
<li>July 1 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3=
%9Cberlingen_mid-air_collision" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=C3=9Cberlin=
gen mid-air collision">=C3=9Cberlingen mid-air collision</a></b>, Bashkiria=
n Airlines Flight 2937, a Tupolev Tu-154 with 60 passengers and nine crew m=
embers on board, collides with DHL Flight 611, a Boeing 757 freighter with =
two pilots on board near Lake Constance, Germany; all people on both planes=
 die.</li>
<li>July 4 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
2_Prestige_Airlines_Boeing_707_crash" title=3D"2002 Prestige Airlines Boein=
g 707 crash">2002 Prestige Airlines Boeing 707 crash</a></b>, a Boeing 707 =
crashes at Bangui Airport while attempting an emergency landing, killing 28=
 of 30 on board.</li>
<li>July 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swiss_Int=
ernational_Air_Lines_Flight_850" title=3D"Swiss International Air Lines Fli=
ght 850">Swiss International Air Lines Flight 850</a></b>, a Saab 2000, str=
ikes an earth bank after landing at Werneuchen Airfield after multiple dive=
rsions due to a storm system; all 20 on board survive the accident but the =
aircraft is written off.</li>
<li>August 22 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
2002_Shangri-La_Air_Twin_Otter_Crash" title=3D"2002 Shangri-La Air Twin Ott=
er Crash">2002 Shangri-La Air Twin Otter Crash</a></b>, a DHC-6 Twin Otter =
crashes in thick cloud whilst on approach into Pokhara Airport, Nepal, kill=
ing all 18 passengers and crew.</li>
<li>August 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rico_Li=
nhas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_4823" title=3D"Rico Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 4823"=
>Rico Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 4823</a></b>, an Embraer EMB 120 Bras=C3=AD=
lia, crashes on approach to Rio Branco International Airport, Brazil, in a =
rainstorm; the aircraft breaks up into three pieces and catches fire; 23 of=
 31 on board die.</li>
<li>October 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwe=
st_Airlines_Flight_85" title=3D"Northwest Airlines Flight 85">Northwest Air=
lines Flight 85</a></b>, a Boeing 747, experiences a rudder hardover; the c=
rew make an emergency landing at Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airpor=
t and all 404 people on board are unharmed.</li>
<li>November 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxair=
_Flight_9642" title=3D"Luxair Flight 9642">Luxair Flight 9642</a></b>, a Fo=
kker F50, crashes short of the runway on approach to Luxembourg Findel Airp=
ort in foggy weather conditions; of the 19 passengers and three crew on boa=
rd, only two survive.</li>
<li>November 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laoag=
_International_Airlines_Flight_585" title=3D"Laoag International Airlines F=
light 585">Laoag International Airlines Flight 585</a></b>, a Fokker F-27 F=
riendship, crashes into Manila Bay shortly after takeoff from Ninoy Aquino =
International Airport; of the 34 people on board, 19 are killed.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerom=
ist-Kharkiv_Flight_2137" title=3D"Aeromist-Kharkiv Flight 2137">Aeromist-Kh=
arkiv Flight 2137</a></b>, an Antonov An-140, crashes near Ardestan in Iran=
 whilst descending into Isfahan International Airport, claiming the lives o=
f all 44 on board; the accident is found to have been caused by insufficien=
t crew training.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air=
_Midwest_Flight_5481" title=3D"Air Midwest Flight 5481">Air Midwest Flight =
5481</a></b>, a Beechcraft 1900, crashes on takeoff from Charlotte, North C=
arolina, United States; all 19 passengers and two pilots are killed.</li>
<li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish=
_Airlines_Flight_634" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 634">Turkish Airline=
s Flight 634</a></b>, an Avro RJ100, crashes during its final approach to l=
and at Diyarbak=C4=B1r Airport, Turkey, in extensive fog. All of the five c=
rew and 70 of the 75 passengers are killed, five passengers survive with se=
rious injuries.</li>
<li>January 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TANS_Pe=
r%C3%BA_Flight_222" title=3D"TANS Per=C3=BA Flight 222">TANS Per=C3=BA Flig=
ht 222</a></b>, a Fokker F28, crashes while on approach to Chachapoyas Airp=
ort; all 46 on board die.</li>
<li>March 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Alg%C=
3%A9rie_Flight_6289" title=3D"Air Alg=C3=A9rie Flight 6289">Air Alg=C3=A9ri=
e Flight 6289</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, veers off the runway on takeoff in=
 Tamanrasset, Algeria; 96 of the 97 passengers and all six crew members die=
.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2003=
_Congo_air_disaster" title=3D"2003 Congo air disaster">2003 Congo air disas=
ter</a></b>, a Ukrainian Cargo Airways Ilyushin Il-76 suffers a rapid decom=
pression after a cargo door opens mid-flight. The aircraft manages to retur=
n to Kinshasa, but not before between 17 and 200 civilians are sucked out t=
o their deaths (casualty numbers vary depending on source).</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2003_Angol=
a_727_disappearance" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2003 Angola 727 disappe=
arance">A Boeing 727-200 is stolen</a></b> from Quatro de Fevereiro Airport=
 in Angola, possibly by two men known to the authorities, and disappears ov=
er the Atlantic Ocean; despite an extensive search effort, the aircraft has=
 never been found.</li>
<li>May 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UM_Airline=
s_Flight_4230" title=3D"UM Airlines Flight 4230">UM Airlines Flight 4230</a=
></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-42 crashes into the side of a mountain near the town =
of Ma=C3=A7ka, Turkey. All 75 people are killed.</li>
<li>May 29 =E2=80=93 A man attempts to hijack <b><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Qantas_Flight_1737" title=3D"Qantas Flight 1737">Qantas Flig=
ht 1737</a></b>, a Boeing 717, in Melbourne, Australia, intending to crash =
the plane in Tasmania. He is overpowered by the flight crew and passengers,=
 but injures three people.</li>
<li>June 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Franc=
e_Flight_5672" title=3D"Air France Flight 5672">Air France Flight 5672</a><=
/b>, a Bombardier CRJ100ER operating a domestic flight from Nantes to Brest=
 in France, crashes on approach to Brest-Guipavas Airport due to pilot erro=
r, killing one of the 24 people on board.</li>
<li>July 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan_Airw=
ays_Flight_139" title=3D"Sudan Airways Flight 139">Sudan Airways Flight 139=
</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes shortly after taking off from Port Suda=
n, Sudan. 116 of the 117 people on board the plane die; a two year old boy =
is the sole survivor.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropica=
l_Airways_Flight_1301" title=3D"Tropical Airways Flight 1301">Tropical Airw=
ays Flight 1301</a></b>, a Let L-410 Turbolet operating a domestic flight i=
n Haiti, crashes into a field shortly after taking off from Cap-Ha=C3=AFtie=
n International Airport, due to a cargo door failure; all 21 people on boar=
d are killed.</li>
<li>August 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colgan_=
Air_Flight_9446" title=3D"Colgan Air Flight 9446">Colgan Air Flight 9446</a=
></b>, a Beech 1900D crashes into the sea just after taking off from Barnst=
able Municipal Airport, Massachusetts. Both pilots are killed.</li>
<li>November 22 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
3_Baghdad_DHL_attempted_shootdown_incident" title=3D"2003 Baghdad DHL attem=
pted shootdown incident">DHL Airbus A300 is struck by a missile</a></b> nea=
r Baghdad, Iraq and loses hydraulic system function, but manages to land sa=
fely with only engine controls without any fatalities. This is the first no=
n-fatal landing of an airliner without control surfaces.</li>
<li>December 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FedEx=
_Express_Flight_647" title=3D"FedEx Express Flight 647">FedEx Express Fligh=
t 647</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-10-10, veers off the runway upon land=
ing after a landing gear collapse and catches fire at Memphis International=
 Airport; two crew members and five passengers escape with only minor injur=
ies.</li>
<li>December 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTA_F=
light_141" title=3D"UTA Flight 141">UTA Flight 141</a></b>, a Boeing 727, r=
uns off the end of the runway upon takeoff at Cotonou, Benin, and crashes o=
nto the beach on the Bight of Benin, killing 151 of the 163 occupants.</li>=
</ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2004">2004</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 2004">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=

<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Fokker_50_AN0790320.jpg" cl=

<ul><li>January 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fla=
sh_Airlines_Flight_604" title=3D"Flash Airlines Flight 604">Flash Airlines =
Flight 604</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, crashes into the Red Sea, killing all=
 135 passengers and 13 crew members in the worst ever accident involving th=
e 737-300.</li>
<li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uzbeki=
stan_Airways_Flight_1154" title=3D"Uzbekistan Airways Flight 1154">Uzbekist=
an Airways Flight 1154</a></b>, a Yakovlev Yak-40 collides with a radar sta=
tion on approach into Tashkent International Airport, Uzbekistan in poor we=
ather. All 37 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>February 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kish_=
Air_Flight_7170" title=3D"Kish Air Flight 7170">Kish Air Flight 7170</a></b=
>, a Fokker 50, crashes at Sharjah International Airport, killing 43 people=
. Three survive with serious injuries.</li>
<li>May 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rico_Linha=
s_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_4815" title=3D"Rico Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 4815">Ri=
co Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 4815</a></b>, an Embraer 120ER, crashes while =
on approach to Eduardo Gomes International Airport, killing all 33 passenge=
rs and crew on board; the cause is never determined.</li>
<li>June 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabon_Expr=
ess_Flight_221" title=3D"Gabon Express Flight 221">Gabon Express Flight 221=
</a></b>, a Hawker Siddeley HS 748 crashes into the sea after attempting an=
 emergency landing at Libreville International Airport, Gabon after an engi=
ne failure. 19 of the 30 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>August 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Tah=
oma_Flight_185" title=3D"Air Tahoma Flight 185">Air Tahoma Flight 185</a></=
b>, a Convair 580, crashes near Covington, Kentucky, while descending to la=
nd, killing the first officer.</li>
<li><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2004_Russian_aircraft_bombi=
ngs" title=3D"2004 Russian aircraft bombings">2004 Russian aircraft bombing=
s</a></b>:
<ul><li>August 24 =E2=80=93 Siberia Airlines Flight 1047, a Tupolev Tu-154,=
 explodes in mid-air while flying over Rostov Oblast, Russia, killing all 3=
8 passengers and eight crew members on board.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 Volga-AviaExpress Flight 1303, a Tupolev Tu-134, ex=
plodes in mid-air while flying over Tula Oblast, Russia, killing all 34 pas=
sengers and nine crew members on board.</li></ul></li>
<li>October 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MK_Air=
lines_Flight_1602" title=3D"MK Airlines Flight 1602">MK Airlines Flight 160=
2</a></b>, a Boeing 747-200F, crashes on takeoff from Halifax Stanfield Int=
ernational Airport, killing all seven on board.</li>
<li>October 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinnac=
le_Airlines_Flight_3701" title=3D"Pinnacle Airlines Flight 3701">Pinnacle A=
irlines Flight 3701</a></b>, a CRJ-200 repositioning flight with no passeng=
ers, crashes near Jefferson City, MO, killing both pilots.</li>
<li>October 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corpor=
ate_Airlines_Flight_5966" title=3D"Corporate Airlines Flight 5966">Corporat=
e Airlines Flight 5966</a></b>, a British Aerospace Jetstream, crashes near=
 Kirksville, Missouri, United States; 13 of the 15 people on board die.</li=
>
<li>November 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China=
_Eastern_Airlines_Flight_5210" title=3D"China Eastern Airlines Flight 5210"=
>China Eastern Airlines Flight 5210</a></b>, a Bombardier CRJ200, stalls an=
d crashes near Baotou, China, shortly after takeoff because of frost contam=
ination; all 53 on board and two people on the ground are killed.</li>
<li>November 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_=
Air_Flight_583" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Lion Air Flight 583">Lion Ai=
r Flight 583</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, crash-lands in Solo City, =
Indonesia, killing 25 of the 154 people on board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>February 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ka=
m_Air_Flight_904" title=3D"Kam Air Flight 904">Kam Air Flight 904</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737-200, crashes in a snowstorm in Afghanistan. All 96 passengers =
and eight crew members die.</li>
<li>February 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Briti=
sh_Airways_Flight_268" title=3D"British Airways Flight 268">British Airways=
 Flight 268</a></b>, a Boeing 747-400, taking off from Los Angeles to Londo=
n suffers fire in engine 2. The plane flies on three engines to Manchester,=
 where it performs an emergency landing. None of the 369 people on board ar=
e harmed.</li>
<li>March 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Trans=
at_Flight_961" title=3D"Air Transat Flight 961">Air Transat Flight 961</a><=
/b>, an Airbus A310, suffers rudder failure after takeoff from Varadero, Cu=
ba; the aircraft returns to Cuba with no casualties.</li>
<li>March 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regional=
_Airlines_Flight_9288" title=3D"Regional Airlines Flight 9288">Regional Air=
lines Flight 9288</a></b>, an Antonov An-24RV, stalls and crashes into a sm=
all hill near Varandey Airport, Russia, due to a possible instrument failur=
e, killing 28 of 52 on board.</li>
<li>March 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Car=
ibbean_Airways_Flight_9955" title=3D"West Caribbean Airways Flight 9955">We=
st Caribbean Airways Flight 9955</a></b>, a Let L-410 Turbolet operating a =
domestic flight in Colombia, South America, stalls due to engine failure an=
d crashes into a forest shortly after departing from El Embrujo Airport on =
Providencia Island, killing nine of the 14 people on board.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airwork_Fli=
ght_23" title=3D"Airwork Flight 23">Airwork Flight 23</a></b>, a Fairchild =
SA227-AC Metro III operating a cargo flight between the north and south isl=
ands of New Zealand, breaks up in mid-air and crashes in Stratford, North I=
sland, due to pilot error, killing the two crew members on board.</li>
<li>May 7 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lock=
hart_River_air_disaster" title=3D"Lockhart River air disaster">Lockhart Riv=
er air disaster</a></b>, an Aero-Tropics Air Services <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fairchild_Swearingen_Metroliner" title=3D"Fairchild Swe=
aringen Metroliner">Fairchild Swearingen Metroliner</a> operating on behalf=
 of Transair strikes terrain on approach into Lockhart River Airport, Austr=
alia. All 15 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>June 9 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
5_Logan_Airport_runway_incursion" title=3D"2005 Logan Airport runway incurs=
ion">2005 Logan Airport runway incursion</a></b>, US Airways Flight 1170, a=
 Boeing 737, and Aer Lingus Flight 132, an Airbus A330, almost collide on a=
 runway at Logan International Airport in Boston, Massachusetts. None of th=
e 381 people on either plane is harmed.</li>
<li>July 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2005_Equa=
torial_Express_Airlines_An-24_crash" title=3D"2005 Equatorial Express Airli=
nes An-24 crash">An Equatorial Express Antonov An-24 crashes</a></b> into a=
 mountainside near Baney in Equatorial Guinea, killing all 60 people on boa=
rd.</li>
<li>August 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Fran=
ce_Flight_358" title=3D"Air France Flight 358">Air France Flight 358</a></b=
>, an Airbus A340-300, skids off a runway at Toronto Pearson International =
Airport, Ontario, while landing and catches fire; all 309 on board escape w=
ithout fatalities, 43 people are injured, the aircraft is completely destro=
yed by the fire.</li>
<li>August 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuninter=
_Flight_1153" title=3D"Tuninter Flight 1153">Tuninter Flight 1153</a></b>, =
an ATR 72, ditches into the Mediterranean Sea near Palermo, Sicily, with 35=
 passengers and four crew members on board; 14 passengers and two crew memb=
ers die.</li>
<li>August 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copterl=
ine_Flight_103" title=3D"Copterline Flight 103">Copterline Flight 103</a></=
b>, a Sikorsky S-76 helicopter crashes off Tallinn, Estonia, killing all 14=
 on board.</li>
<li>August 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helios_=
Airways_Flight_522" title=3D"Helios Airways Flight 522">Helios Airways Flig=
ht 522</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, crashes near Kalamos, Greece, with 115 pa=
ssengers and six crew members on board; there are no survivors.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Ca=
ribbean_Airways_Flight_708" title=3D"West Caribbean Airways Flight 708">Wes=
t Caribbean Airways Flight 708</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, crashes =
in western Venezuela. All on board, 152 passengers and eight crew members, =
die.</li>
<li>August 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TANS_Pe=
r%C3%BA_Flight_204" title=3D"TANS Per=C3=BA Flight 204">TANS Per=C3=BA Flig=
ht 204</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes on approach to Captain Rolden Int=
ernational Airport, Pucallpa, Peru. Thirty-five of the 91 passengers on boa=
rd, as well as five of the seven crew members, die.</li>
<li>September 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manda=
la_Airlines_Flight_091" title=3D"Mandala Airlines Flight 091">Mandala Airli=
nes Flight 091</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes in Medan, Indonesia, kill=
ing 103 of the 111 passengers and all five crew members on board the aircra=
ft and an additional 47 people on the ground.</li>
<li>September 5 =E2=80=93 A Kavatshi Airlines <b><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/2005_Kavatshi_Airlines_Antonov_An-26B_crash" title=3D"2005 K=
avatshi Airlines Antonov An-26B crash">Antonov An-26B crashes</a></b> at Is=
iro Airport in Matari, Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing all 11 peo=
ple on board.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 An Air Kasai <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/2005_Air_Kasai_Antonov_An-26B_crash" title=3D"2005 Air Kasai Antono=
v An-26B crash">Antonov An-26B crashes</a></b> in the Republic of the Congo=
 north of Brazzaville, killing all 13 people on board.</li>
<li>September 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JetB=
lue_Flight_292" title=3D"JetBlue Flight 292">JetBlue Flight 292</a></b>, an=
 Airbus A320, makes an emergency landing at Los Angeles International Airpo=
rt because of landing gear steering failure. There are no injuries to the 1=
39 passengers and six crew members.</li>
<li>October 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bellvi=
ew_Airlines_Flight_210" title=3D"Bellview Airlines Flight 210">Bellview Air=
lines Flight 210</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes shortly after takeoff f=
rom Murtala Muhammed International Airport in Lagos, Nigeria, killing all 1=
17 people on board.</li>
<li>December 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southw=
est_Airlines_Flight_1248" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 1248">Southwes=
t Airlines Flight 1248</a></b>, a Boeing 737-700, slides off the runway dur=
ing landing at Chicago Midway International Airport in Chicago in heavy sno=
w. None of the people on board are injured, but the plane hits two automobi=
les on the ground, killing a passenger.</li>
<li>December 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sosol=
iso_Airlines_Flight_1145" title=3D"Sosoliso Airlines Flight 1145">Sosoliso =
Airlines Flight 1145</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9 with 110 people on b=
oard, crashes during landing in Port Harcourt, Nigeria. Of the 110 people o=
n board; only two survive.</li>
<li>December 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chalk=
%27s_Ocean_Airways_Flight_101" title=3D"Chalk's Ocean Airways Flight 101">C=
halk's Ocean Airways Flight 101</a></b>, a Grumman Mallard, crashes off the=
 coast of Miami Beach, Florida, killing all 20 on board.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerb=
aijan_Airlines_Flight_217" title=3D"Azerbaijan Airlines Flight 217">Azerbai=
jan Airlines Flight 217</a></b>, an Antonov An-140, crashes shortly after t=
akeoff from Baku Airport due to instrument failure, killing all 23 on board=
.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2006">2006</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 2006">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wreckage_of_flight_GLO_1907=

iv class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=

<ul><li>March 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TEAM=
_Linhas_A%C3%A9reas_Flight_6865" title=3D"TEAM Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 68=
65">TEAM Linhas A=C3=A9reas Flight 6865</a></b>, a Let L-410 Turbolet crash=
es whilst conducting a VFR approach to Maca=C3=A9 Airport, Brazil. All 19 p=
assengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armavia_Fli=
ght_967" title=3D"Armavia Flight 967">Armavia Flight 967</a></b>, an Airbus=
 A320, crashes into the Black Sea near the Russian city of Sochi, killing a=
ll 113 on board.</li>
<li>June 21 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20=
06_Yeti_Airlines_Twin_Otter_Crash" title=3D"2006 Yeti Airlines Twin Otter C=
rash">2006 Yeti Airlines Twin Otter Crash</a></b>, a DHC-6 Twin Otter crash=
es during a go-around at Jumla Airport, Nepal. All nine passengers and crew=
 are killed.</li>
<li>July 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S7_Airline=
s_Flight_778" title=3D"S7 Airlines Flight 778">S7 Airlines Flight 778</a></=
b>, an Airbus A310, crashes into a concrete barricade at Irkutsk Internatio=
nal Airport, Russia, upon landing and catches fire. Of the 203 people on bo=
ard, 128 are killed.</li>
<li>July 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIA_Fligh=
t_688" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"PIA Flight 688">Pakistan Internationa=
l Airlines Flight 688</a></b>, a Fokker F27, crashes into a wheat field nea=
r Multan, Pakistan, ten minutes after taking off, killing all 41 passengers=
 and four crew members on board.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FedEx_Exp=
ress_Flight_630" title=3D"FedEx Express Flight 630">FedEx Flight 630</a></b=
>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-10, crashes on landing at Memphis International A=
irport, Tennessee, after the left main landing gear collapses shortly after=
 touchdown, all three crew members are seriously injured.</li>
<li>August 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Alg=
%C3%A9rie_Flight_2208" title=3D"Air Alg=C3=A9rie Flight 2208">Air Alg=C3=A9=
rie Flight 2208</a></b>, a Lockheed L=E2=80=91100 Hercules in Northern Ital=
y crashes as a result of an autopilot malfunction. All three on board are k=
illed.</li>
<li>August 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulkovo=
_Aviation_Enterprise_Flight_612" title=3D"Pulkovo Aviation Enterprise Fligh=
t 612">Pulkovo Aviation Enterprise Flight 612</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, cr=
ashes near Donetsk, Ukraine, killing all 170 people on board.</li>
<li>August 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comair_=
Flight_5191" title=3D"Comair Flight 5191">Comair Flight 5191</a></b>, a Bom=
bardier Canadair CRJ-100, crashes on takeoff at Blue Grass Airport, Kentuck=
y, due to runway confusion; of the 50 people on board, only the first offic=
er survives.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_=
Air_Tours_Flight_945" title=3D"Iran Air Tours Flight 945">Iran Air Tours Fl=
ight 945</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154, crashes while attempting to land in Mas=
had, Iran, killing 28 of 154 on board.</li>
<li>September 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gol_=
Transportes_A%C3%A9reos_Flight_1907" title=3D"Gol Transportes A=C3=A9reos F=
light 1907">Gol Transportes A=C3=A9reos Flight 1907</a></b>, a Boeing 737-8=
00, collides with an Embraer Legacy business jet and crashes in Mato Grosso=
, Brazil; the Embraer Legacy, with seven on board, lands safely with no rep=
orted injuries while all 154 people on board the Boeing 737 die; this crash=
 marks the first loss of a Boeing 737-800.</li>
<li>October 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish=
_Airlines_Flight_1476" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 1476">Turkish Airli=
nes Flight 1476</a></b>, a Boeing 737, is hijacked in Greek airspace. Plane=
 lands at Brindisi Airport, Italy. Hijacker is arrested. All 113 people on =
board survive.</li></ul>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Atlantic_Airways_Flight_670=
_wreckage.png" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedi=

><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Atlantic_Airways_Flight_670_=

f Atlantic Airways Flight 670</div></div></div>
<ul><li>October 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/At=
lantic_Airways_Flight_670" title=3D"Atlantic Airways Flight 670">Atlantic A=
irways Flight 670</a></b>, a BAe 146, slides off the runway at Stord Airpor=
t, Norway, due to hydroplaning and brake failure, killing four of the 16 pe=
ople on board.</li>
<li>October 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contin=
ental_Airlines_Flight_1883" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 1883">Cont=
inental Airlines Flight 1883</a></b>, a Boeing 757, accidentally lands on a=
 taxiway at Newark Liberty International Airport, New Jersey, none of the 1=
54 people onboard are injured.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ADC_Ai=
rlines_Flight_053" title=3D"ADC Airlines Flight 053">ADC Airlines Flight 05=
3</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200, crashes near Abuja, Nigeria, after encounterin=
g wind shear, killing 96 of the 105 people on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2007">2007</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D95" title=3D"Edit=
 section: 2007">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<ul><li>January 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ada=
m_Air_Flight_574" title=3D"Adam Air Flight 574">Adam Air Flight 574</a></b>=
, a Boeing 737-400 with 102 people on board, crashes into the ocean off the=
 island of Sulawesi in Indonesia, killing all on board in the worst ever cr=
ash involving the 737-400.</li>
<li>January 9 =E2=80=93 An <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007=
_Balad_aircraft_crash" title=3D"2007 Balad aircraft crash">AerianTur-M Anto=
nov An-26 crashes</a></b> near Balad, Iraq, killing 34 of the 35 people on =
board. The official cause of the crash is poor weather conditions, but othe=
r sources claim that the plane was shot down by a missile.</li>
<li>January 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_We=
st_Flight_612" title=3D"Air West Flight 612">Air West Flight 612</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 737, is hijacked shortly after takeoff. The plane landed safely at =
N'Djamena International Airport, where the hijacker surrenders. All 103 peo=
ple on board survive.</li>
<li>February 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam_=
Air_Flight_172" title=3D"Adam Air Flight 172">Adam Air Flight 172</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737-300, suffers structural damage while landing near Surabaya, In=
donesia; none of the 149 people on board is seriously injured.</li>
<li>March 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garuda_In=
donesia_Flight_200" title=3D"Garuda Indonesia Flight 200">Garuda Indonesia =
Flight 200</a></b>, a Boeing 737-400, overshoots the runway and crashes whi=
le landing at Yogyakarta, Indonesia, killing 21 of the 140 people on board.=
</li>
<li>March 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTair_Fl=
ight_471" title=3D"UTair Flight 471">UTair Flight 471</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu=
-134, suffers severe structural damage while landing in Samara, Russia, kil=
ling six of the 63 people on board.</li>
<li>March 23 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007=
_Mogadishu_TransAVIAexport_Airlines_Il-76_crash" title=3D"2007 Mogadishu Tr=
ansAVIAexport Airlines Il-76 crash">2007 Mogadishu TransAVIAexport Airlines=
 Il-76 crash</a></b> of an Ilyushin Il-76 near Mogadishu, Somalia, after be=
ing hit by a surface-to-air missile, kills all 11 on board; one passenger i=
nitially survives, but dies hours later.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya_Airwa=
ys_Flight_507" title=3D"Kenya Airways Flight 507">Kenya Airways Flight 507<=
/a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 with 114 people on board, crashes near Douala, Ca=
meroon, killing all on board.</li>
<li>June 3 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
7_Paramount_Airlines_Mil_Mi-8_crash" title=3D"2007 Paramount Airlines Mil M=
i-8 crash">2007 Paramount Airlines Mil Mi-8 crash</a></b>, a Mil Mi-8 helic=
opter crashes in Lungi, Sierra Leone, killing all 22 people on board.</li>
<li>June 21 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007_=
Free_Airlines_L-410_crash" title=3D"2007 Free Airlines L-410 crash">2007 Fr=
ee Airlines L-410 crash</a></b> shortly after takeoff from Kamina Town, Dem=
ocratic Republic of Congo because of severe overloading, kills one and inju=
res four of the 21 people on board.</li>
<li>June 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PMTair_Fl=
ight_241" title=3D"PMTair Flight 241">PMTair Flight 241</a></b>, an Antonov=
 An-24, crashes in southwestern Cambodia, killing all 22 on board.</li></ul=
>

<ul><li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAM_A=
irlines_Flight_3054" title=3D"TAM Airlines Flight 3054">TAM Airlines Flight=
 3054</a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes at Congonhas-S=C3=A3o Paulo Airport,=
 Brazil, killing all 187 people on board and 12 on the ground.</li>
<li>August 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Moor=
ea_Flight_1121" title=3D"Air Moorea Flight 1121">Air Moorea Flight 1121</a>=
</b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6, crashes into the lagoon of the island of=
 Moorea in French Polynesia just 11 seconds after takeoff, killing all 20 o=
n board.</li>
<li>August 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_A=
irlines_Flight_120" title=3D"China Airlines Flight 120">China Airlines Flig=
ht 120</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800, bursts into flames after landing at Naha,=
 Japan; none of the 165 passengers on board is seriously injured.</li>
<li>August 26 =E2=80=93 A Great Lakes Business Company <b><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007_Kongolo_Antonov_An-32B_crash" title=3D"2007 Ko=
ngolo Antonov An-32B crash">Antonov An-32B crashes</a></b> short of the run=
way after experiencing engine failure and attempting to return to Kongolo A=
irport in Kongolo, Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing 14 of the 15 p=
eople on board.</li>
<li>Scandinavian Airlines System <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Dash_8_landing_gear_incidents" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Dash 8 land=
ing gear incidents">Dash 8 landing gear incidents</a></b>:
<ul><li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b>Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 1209</=
b>, a de Havilland Canada Dash 8, experiences a landing gear failure in Aal=
borg, Denmark; none of the 73 people on board is seriously injured, but thr=
ee days later, after a similar incident, the airline grounds the aircraft t=
ype.</li>
<li>September 12 =E2=80=93 <b>Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 2748</b>,=
 a de Havilland Canada Dash 8, experiences a landing gear failure in Vilniu=
s, Lithuania; none of the 52 people on board is injured, but because of a s=
imilar incident three days earlier, all their Dash 8s are grounded.</li>
<li>October 27 =E2=80=93 <b>Scandinavian Airlines System Flight 2867</b>, a=
 de Havilland Canada Dash 8, experiences a landing gear failure in Copenhag=
en, Denmark; none of the 44 people on board is injured, but because of simi=
lar incidents in September, the airline "permanently" removes its Dash 8s f=
rom service; cause is eventually ascribed to maintenance error.</li></ul></=
li>
<li>September 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One-=
Two-GO_Airlines_Flight_269" title=3D"One-Two-GO Airlines Flight 269">One-Tw=
o-GO Airlines Flight 269</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82 carrying 130 pe=
ople, crashes and bursts into flames after attempting to land in Phuket, Th=
ailand, during poor weather conditions, killing 90 people.</li>
<li>October 4 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/200=
7_Africa_One_Antonov_An-26_crash" title=3D"2007 Africa One Antonov An-26 cr=
ash">2007 Africa One Antonov An-26 crash</a></b> into a residential area in=
 Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo, shortly after taking off, kill=
s at least 50 people, most of whom are on the ground.</li>
<li>November 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlas=
jet_Flight_4203" title=3D"Atlasjet Flight 4203">Atlasjet Flight 4203</a></b=
>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-83, crashes into a mountain near Isparta, Turkey,=
 killing all 57 on board.</li>
<li>December 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TAROM=
_Flight_3107" title=3D"TAROM Flight 3107">TAROM Flight 3107</a></b>, a Boei=
ng 737-300, is written-off after hitting a maintenance car on the runway an=
d veering off the runway during takeoff run at Henri Coand=C4=83 Internatio=
nal Airport, Otopeni, Romania; none of the 123 on board is injured.</li></u=
l>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2008">2008</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

 section: 2008">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:BA38_Crash.jpg" class=3D"im=

al" title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Br=
itish_Airways_Flight_38" title=3D"British Airways Flight 38">British Airway=

<ul><li>January 4 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/2008_Los_Roques_archipelago_Transaven_Let_L-410_crash" title=3D"2008 Los R=
oques archipelago Transaven Let L-410 crash">2008 Los Roques archipelago Tr=
ansaven Let L-410 crash</a></b> kills all 14 on board.</li>
<li>January 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Britis=
h_Airways_Flight_38" title=3D"British Airways Flight 38">British Airways Fl=
ight 38</a></b>, a Boeing 777-200ER, lands short of the runway at London He=
athrow Airport due to a fuel system problem; all 152 on board survive. This=
 is the first loss of a Boeing 777-200ER, and the first loss of any 777 due=
 to operational incident.</li>
<li>February 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_=
Airways_Flight_2279" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Eagle Airways Flight 22=
79">Eagle Airways Flight 2279</a></b>, a BAe Jetstream 32, is hijacked 10 m=
inutes after taking off from Blenheim, New Zealand by a passenger who attac=
ks both pilots. The hijacker is eventually restrained by the co-pilot and t=
he flight lands safely at Christchurch. All nine on board survive the incid=
ent.</li>
<li>February 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belav=
ia_Flight_1834" title=3D"Belavia Flight 1834">Belavia Flight 1834</a></b>, =
a Bombardier CRJ100, hits its left wing on the runway while taking off from=
 Yerevan, Armenia. All 21 on board escape the aircraft before it erupts int=
o flames.</li>
<li>February 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa=
_B%C3%A1rbara_Airlines_Flight_518" title=3D"Santa B=C3=A1rbara Airlines Fli=
ght 518">Santa B=C3=A1rbara Airlines Flight 518</a></b>, an ATR 42-300, cra=
shes shortly after taking off from M=C3=A9rida, Venezuela, killing all 46 o=
n board.</li>
<li>April 3 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20=
08_Blue_Wing_Airlines_An-28_crash" title=3D"2008 Blue Wing Airlines An-28 c=
rash">2008 Blue Wing Airlines An-28 crash</a></b>, an Antonov An-28 operate=
d by Blue Wing Airlines crashes near Benzdorp in Suriname. All 19 on board =
are killed.</li>
<li>April 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kata_Air=
_Transport_Flight_007" title=3D"Kata Air Transport Flight 007">Kata Air Tra=
nsport Flight 007</a></b>, a Sudanese airline Antonov An-32 crashes when re=
turning shortly after taking off from Chi=C5=9Fin=C4=83u International Airp=
ort, Moldova, for Turkey. All eight on board are killed.</li>
<li>April 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hewa_Bor=
a_Airways_Flight_122" title=3D"Hewa Bora Airways Flight 122">Hewa Bora Airw=
ays Flight 122</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas DC-9, crashes into a market nea=
r Goma, Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing 40 people, including thre=
e passengers.</li>
<li>May 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalitta_Ai=
r_Flight_207" title=3D"Kalitta Air Flight 207">Kalitta Air Flight 207</a></=
b>, a Boeing 747-200, overruns the runway at Brussels, Belgium. No one is i=
njured but the aircraft is written off.</li>
<li>May 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moskovia_A=
irlines_Flight_9675" title=3D"Moskovia Airlines Flight 9675">Moskovia Airli=
nes Flight 9675</a></b>, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moskovi=
a_Airlines" title=3D"Moskovia Airlines">Moskovia Airlines</a> Antonov An-12=
 crashes shortly after takeoff from Chelyabinsk Airport, Russia due to an o=
nboard fire. All nine crew members are killed.</li>
<li>May 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TACA_Fligh=
t_390" title=3D"TACA Flight 390">TACA Flight 390</a></b>, an Airbus A320, o=
verruns the runway at Toncont=C3=ADn International Airport in Tegucigalpa, =
Honduras, killing five (including two on ground).</li>
<li>June 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan_Air=
ways_Flight_109" title=3D"Sudan Airways Flight 109">Sudan Airways Flight 10=
9</a></b>, an Airbus A310, crashes at Khartoum International Airport and br=
eaks apart, catching fire. 30 deaths are confirmed, six passengers are list=
ed as missing.</li>
<li>July 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centurion_=
Air_Cargo_Flight_164" title=3D"Centurion Air Cargo Flight 164">Centurion Ai=
r Cargo Flight 164</a></b>, a Boeing 747-200BSF operated by <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalitta_Air" title=3D"Kalitta Air">Kalitta Air</a=
>, crashes shortly after taking off from Bogota's El Dorado International A=
irport, Colombia due to an engine failure. All eight crew survive, but two =
on the ground are killed.</li>
<li>July 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qantas_Fl=
ight_30" title=3D"Qantas Flight 30">Qantas Flight 30</a></b>, a Boeing 747-=
400 en route from Hong Kong to Melbourne, performs an emergency descent and=
 lands in Manila after a hull penetration results in rapid decompression; a=
ll aboard survive.</li>
<li>August 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spanair=
_Flight_5022" title=3D"Spanair Flight 5022">Spanair Flight 5022</a></b>, a =
McDonnell Douglas MD-82, crashes on takeoff at Barajas Airport in Madrid, S=
pain. Of the 172 people on board, 154 are killed.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
2008_A%C3%A9reo_Ruta_Maya_crash" title=3D"2008 A=C3=A9reo Ruta Maya crash">=
2008 A=C3=A9reo Ruta Maya crash</a></b>, a Cessna 208 Caravan, crashes 45 m=
inutes after takeoff from La Aurora International Airport, Guatemala en rou=
te to El Estor, Guatemala. 11 of the 14 passengers and crew are killed.</li=
>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_As=
eman_Airlines_Flight_6895" title=3D"Iran Aseman Airlines Flight 6895">Iran =
Aseman Airlines Flight 6895</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes just after takeo=
ff from Manas Airport in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan. 68 of the 90 passengers and c=
rew on board are killed.</li>
<li>August 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sriwija=
ya_Air_Flight_062" title=3D"Sriwijaya Air Flight 062">Sriwijaya Air Flight =
062</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200 overruns the runway at Sultan Thaha Airport, =
Indonesia during a landing attempt, resulting in 26 injuries (14 of them se=
rious). One person on the ground later dies from their injuries.</li>
<li>August 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
2008_Conviasa_Boeing_737_crash" title=3D"2008 Conviasa Boeing 737 crash">20=
08 Conviasa Boeing 737 crash</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200 crashes into <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illiniza" title=3D"Illiniza">Illiniza</a>=
, Ecuador whilst en route to Cotopaxi International Airport, Ecuador. All t=
hree on board are killed.</li>
<li>September 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero=
flot_Flight_821" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 821">Aeroflot Flight 821</a></b>,=
 a Boeing 737, crashes on approach to Perm Airport from Moscow due to pilot=
 error, killing all 88 people on board in the worst ever accident involving=
 the Boeing 737-500.</li>
<li>October 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qantas_=
Flight_72" title=3D"Qantas Flight 72">Qantas Flight 72</a></b>, an Airbus A=
330-300, makes an emergency landing in Exmouth, Australia, following a rapi=
d descent that leaves over 70 people injured, 14 of them seriously.</li>
<li>October 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yeti_Ai=
rlines_Flight_103" title=3D"Yeti Airlines Flight 103">Yeti Airlines Flight =
103</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes 60 nautical mi=
les (110&nbsp;km) from Mt Everest, Nepal, killing 18 of 19 people on board.=
</li>
<li>November 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryana=
ir_Flight_4102" title=3D"Ryanair Flight 4102">Ryanair Flight 4102</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737, suffers up to 90 bird strikes on its final approach to Rome C=
iampino Airport, damaging landing gear and both engines. The aircraft lands=
 safely; 10 of the 172 on board are treated for minor injuries.</li>
<li>November 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XL_Ai=
rways_Germany_Flight_888T" title=3D"XL Airways Germany Flight 888T">XL Airw=
ays Germany Flight 888T</a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes into the Mediterra=
nean Sea on approach into Perpignan-Rivesaltes Airport, France. All seven o=
n board are killed.</li>
<li>December 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conti=
nental_Airlines_Flight_1404" title=3D"Continental Airlines Flight 1404">Con=
tinental Airlines Flight 1404</a></b>, a Boeing 737-500 with 115 people on =
board, veers off the runway upon takeoff from Denver International Airport,=
 comes to rest in a ravine near the runway and catches fire; 38 people are =
injured.</li></ul>

<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.=
