v></div></div>
<ul><li>January 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/US=
_Airways_Flight_1549" title=3D"US Airways Flight 1549">US Airways Flight 15=
49</a></b>, an Airbus A320 bound for Charlotte, North Carolina, ditches in =
the Hudson River shortly after taking off from LaGuardia Airport, New York =
City, due to total engine failure caused by multiple bird strikes; all 155 =
people on board survive the accident.</li>
<li>January 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empire=
_Airlines_Flight_8284" title=3D"Empire Airlines Flight 8284">Empire Airline=
s Flight 8284</a></b>, an ATR 42-300 operating a FedEx cargo flight in Texa=
s, United States, crashes on approach to Lubbock Preston Smith Internationa=
l Airport due to pilot error; the two pilots on board survive the accident =
but the aircraft is destroyed.</li>
<li>February 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2009_M=
anaus_Aerot%C3%A1xi_crash" title=3D"2009 Manaus Aerot=C3=A1xi crash">A Mana=
us Aerot=C3=A1xi Embraer EMB 110 crashes</a></b> in the Amazon basin near S=
anto Ant=C3=B3nio, Brazil, due to overloading, killing 24 of the 28 people =
on board.</li>
<li>February 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colga=
n_Air_Flight_3407" title=3D"Colgan Air Flight 3407">Colgan Air Flight 3407<=
/a></b>, a Bombardier Dash 8 Q400 flying from Newark, New Jersey, to Buffal=
o, New York, United States, crashes into a house in Clarence Center, New Yo=
rk state, killing all 49 on board the aircraft and one person on the ground=
.</li>
<li>February 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turki=
sh_Airlines_Flight_1951" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 1951">Turkish Air=
lines Flight 1951</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 flying from Istanbul, Turkey, t=
o Amsterdam, Netherlands, stalls and crashes into a field during final appr=
oach to Schiphol Airport, killing nine of the 135 people on board.</li>
<li>March 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cougar_H=
elicopters_Flight_91" title=3D"Cougar Helicopters Flight 91">Cougar Helicop=
ters Flight 91</a></b>, a Sikorsky S-92 transporting workers to oil platfor=
ms off Canada's Newfoundland coast, ditches in the Atlantic Ocean 34 miles =
(55&nbsp;km) east-southeast of Newfoundland due to a main gearbox failure; =
17 of the 18 on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emirates=
_Flight_407" title=3D"Emirates Flight 407">Emirates Flight 407</a></b>, an =
Airbus A340-500 en route from Auckland, New Zealand, to Dubai, United Arab =
Emirates, suffers a tailstrike when attempting to take off from its interme=
diate stopover at Melbourne's Tullamarine Airport; the aircraft returns to =
the airport with no casualties.</li>
<li>March 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FedEx_Ex=
press_Flight_80" title=3D"FedEx Express Flight 80">FedEx Express Flight 80<=
/a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11 operating a cargo flight from Guangzhou,=
 China, to Narita, Japan, crashes while attempting to land at Tokyo Narita =
International Airport, killing the two crew members on board the flight.</l=
i>
<li>April 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bond_Offs=
hore_Helicopters_Flight_85N" title=3D"Bond Offshore Helicopters Flight 85N"=
>Bond Offshore Helicopters Flight 85N</a></b>, a Eurocopter AS332 Super Pum=
a returning from the Miller oilfield off the Aberdeenshire coast, Scotland,=
 crashes 11 nautical miles (20&nbsp;km) northeast of Peterhead due to a cat=
astrophic failure of the main rotor gearbox; all 16 on board are killed.</l=
i>
<li>April 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2009_Avia=
star_British_Aerospace_146_crash" title=3D"2009 Aviastar British Aerospace =
146 crash">An Aviastar BAe 146-300 crashes</a></b> into Pikei Hill during a=
 domestic cargo flight from Jayapura to Wamena, Indonesia, killing all 6 cr=
ew members on board.</li>
<li>April 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mimika_A=
ir_Flight_514" title=3D"Mimika Air Flight 514">Mimika Air Flight 514</a></b=
>, a Pilatus PC-6 operating a domestic flight in Western New Guinea, Indone=
sia, crashes into Mount Gergaji due to pilot error, killing all 11 people o=
n board.</li>
<li>April 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CanJet_F=
light_918" title=3D"CanJet Flight 918">CanJet Flight 918</a></b>, a Boeing =
737 operating a flight from Montego Bay, Jamaica, bound for Halifax, Canada=
, is seized on the ground before takeoff by a lone gunman; all 174 passenge=
rs are quickly released, but six crew members are taken hostage for several=
 hours before being freed unharmed.</li>
<li>June 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_France=
_Flight_447" title=3D"Air France Flight 447">Air France Flight 447</a></b>,=
 an Airbus A330 flying from Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, to Paris, France, crash=
es in the Atlantic Ocean, killing all 228 people on board; bodies and aircr=
aft debris are recovered within days but the main fuselage and the black bo=
xes are not found until 2011; this remains the deadliest accident involving=
 the A330.</li>
<li>June 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemenia_F=
light_626" title=3D"Yemenia Flight 626">Yemenia Flight 626</a></b>, an Airb=
us A310 flying from Sanaa, Yemen, to Moroni, Comoros, crashes into the Indi=
an Ocean on approach to Prince Said Ibrahim International Airport due to pi=
lot error; all but one of the 153 occupants are killed, the sole survivor b=
eing a 12-year-old girl who is found clinging to the wreckage.</li>
<li>July 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southwest=
_Airlines_Flight_2294" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 2294">Southwest A=
irlines Flight 2294</a></b>, a Boeing 737 en route from Nashville, Tennesse=
e, to Baltimore, Maryland, United States, makes an emergency landing in Cha=
rleston, West Virginia, after a large hole opens in the skin of the fuselag=
e at 34,000 feet (10,000&nbsp;m) causing a loss of cabin pressure; the airc=
raft lands safely and no-one is injured.</li>
<li>July 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caspian_A=
irlines_Flight_7908" title=3D"Caspian Airlines Flight 7908">Caspian Airline=
s Flight 7908</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154 flying from Tehran, Iran, to Yereva=
n, Armenia, crashes 16 minutes after takeoff due to uncontained engine fail=
ure, killing all 168 people on board.</li>
<li>July 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aria_Air_=
Flight_1525" title=3D"Aria Air Flight 1525">Aria Air Flight 1525</a></b>, a=
n Ilyushin Il-62 operating a domestic flight in Iran, overshoots the runway=
 while attempting to land at Mashhad International Airport, killing 16 of t=
he 173 on board.</li>
<li>August 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merpati_=
Nusantara_Airlines_Flight_9760" title=3D"Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight =
9760">Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 9760</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada=
 DHC-6 Twin Otter operating a domestic flight in the Indonesian province of=
 Papua, crashes into a mountain on approach to Oksibil Airport in good weat=
her, due to pilot error; all 15 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>August 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangkok_=
Airways_Flight_266" title=3D"Bangkok Airways Flight 266">Bangkok Airways Fl=
ight 266</a></b>, an ATR 72-200 operating a domestic flight in Thailand, cr=
ashes while attempting to land at Samui Airport on Ko Samui island, resulti=
ng in at least one confirmed death and 37 injuries amongst the 72 people on=
 board.</li>
<li>August 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airline=
s_PNG_Flight_4684" title=3D"Airlines PNG Flight 4684">Airlines PNG Flight 4=
684</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter operating a domestic fl=
ight in southeastern Papua New Guinea, crashes into mountainous terrain whi=
le on approach to Kokoda Airport due to poor visibility; all 13 people on b=
oard die in the accident.</li>
<li>August 26 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2009_A%=
C3%A9ro-Fr%C3%AAt_An-12_crash" title=3D"2009 A=C3=A9ro-Fr=C3=AAt An-12 cras=
h">An A=C3=A9ro-Fr=C3=AAt Antonov An-12 crashes</a></b> whilst en route to =
Maya-Maya Airport, Brazzaville, Republic of the Congo, after breaking up in=
 mid-air as a result of an inflight fire; all six occupants of the aircraft=
 are killed.</li>
<li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerom=
%C3%A9xico_Flight_576" title=3D"Aerom=C3=A9xico Flight 576">Aerom=C3=A9xico=
 Flight 576</a></b>, a Boeing 737 flying from Canc=C3=BAn to Mexico City, M=
exico, is hijacked by a Bolivian man carrying a fake explosive device; afte=
r landing in Mexico City, the aircraft is stormed by officials and all 107 =
passengers and crew are released unharmed.</li>
<li>September 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airl=
ink_Flight_8911" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Airlink Flight 8911">Airlin=
k Flight 8911</a></b>, a BAe Jetstream 41 operating a domestic flight in So=
uth Africa, crashes into a school shortly after taking off from Durban Inte=
rnational Airport; the pilot dies two weeks later from injuries sustained i=
n the crash.</li>
<li>October 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azza_T=
ransport_Flight_2241" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Azza Transport Flight =
2241">Azza Transport Flight 2241</a></b>, a Boeing 707 bound for Khartoum, =
Sudan, crashes on takeoff from Sharjah International Airport, United Arab E=
mirates, due to pilot error; all six on board the aircraft are killed.</li>
<li>November 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rwand=
Air_Flight_205" title=3D"RwandAir Flight 205">RwandAir Flight 205</a></b>, =
a Bombardier CRJ-100 bound for Entebbe, Uganda, crashes into a terminal bui=
lding at Kigali International Airport in Rwanda shortly after returning for=
 an emergency landing due to difficulties with the flight controls; one of =
the 10 passengers is killed.</li>
<li>November 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2009_=
Pel-Air_Westwind_ditching" title=3D"2009 Pel-Air Westwind ditching">An IAI =
1124 Westwind ditches</a></b> in the Pacific Ocean 3.2 nautical miles (6&nb=
sp;km) west of Norfolk Island after failing to land at the island's airport=
, en route from Samoa to Melbourne, Australia; all six people on board surv=
ive the incident.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avien=
t_Aviation_Flight_324" title=3D"Avient Aviation Flight 324">Avient Aviation=
 Flight 324</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11F bound for Manas Internation=

dong International Airport, China, killing three of the seven crew members =
on board.</li>
<li>December 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_Airlines_Flight_331" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 331">American Ai=
rlines Flight 331</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 operating a flight from the Uni=
ted States to Kingston, Jamaica, overshoots the runway on landing at Norman=
 Manley International Airport due to pilot error; there are multiple injuri=
es amongst the 154 people on board.</li>
<li>December 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North=
west_Airlines_Flight_253" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Northwest Airlines=
 Flight 253">Northwest Airlines Flight 253</a></b>, an Airbus A330-300 flyi=
ng from Amsterdam Airport Schiphol, Netherlands, to Detroit Metropolitan Ai=
rport, Michigan, United States, is attacked by a man using a small explosiv=
e device, causing a small onboard fire; the perpetrator is subdued by passe=
ngers and crew, and the fire quickly extinguished.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 21 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ca=

</b>, a Boeing 747-4R7F operating a multi-leg cargo flight from Hong Kong t=
o Luxembourg, collides with a ground vehicle on landing at Luxembourg Finde=
l Airport due to ATC error; the driver of the ground vehicle is injured in =
the accident.</li>
<li>January 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taban_=
Air_Flight_6437" title=3D"Taban Air Flight 6437">Taban Air Flight 6437</a><=
/b>, a Tupolev Tu-154M operating a domestic flight in Iran, crashes while m=
aking an emergency landing at Mashhad International Airport; all 157 passen=
gers and 13 crew survive the accident with 47 receiving minor injuries.</li=
>
<li>January 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiop=
ian_Airlines_Flight_409" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Flight 409">Ethiopian =
Airlines Flight 409</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 bound for the Ethiopian capit=
al, Addis Ababa, crashes into the Mediterranean Sea shortly after takeoff f=
rom Beirut Rafic Hariri International Airport; all 90 people on board die.<=
/li>
<li>March 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aviastar=
-TU_Flight_1906" title=3D"Aviastar-TU Flight 1906">Aviastar-TU Flight 1906<=
/a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-204 flying from Hurghada, Egypt, to Moscow, Russia, c=
rashes on landing at Domodedovo International Airport in foggy weather; all=
 eight crew on board survive, but the aircraft is written off; this is the =
first loss of the Tu-204.</li>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AeroUnio=
n_Flight_302" title=3D"AeroUnion Flight 302">AeroUnion Flight 302</a></b>, =
an Airbus A300B4F operating a cargo flight from Mexico City, crashes on a m=
issed approach to Monterrey International Airport, Mexico; all five crew me=
mbers are killed, as well as two people on the ground.</li>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merpati_=
Nusantara_Airlines_Flight_836" title=3D"Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 8=
36">Merpati Nusantara Airlines Flight 836</a></b>, a Boeing 737 operating a=
 domestic flight in Indonesia, overshoots the runway at Rendani Airport; al=
l 103 people on board survive, but three are seriously injured.</li>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cathay_P=
acific_Flight_780" title=3D"Cathay Pacific Flight 780">Cathay Pacific Fligh=
t 780</a></b>, an Airbus A330 flying from Juanda International Airport, Ind=
onesia, to Hong Kong, lands safely after the engine thrust controls malfunc=
tion due to contaminated fuel; 57 of the 309 passengers are injured in the =
evacuation; the two pilots receive the IFALPA <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Polaris_Award" title=3D"Polaris Award">Polaris Award</a> for th=
eir heroism and airmanship.</li>
<li>May 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afriqiyah_=
Airways_Flight_771" title=3D"Afriqiyah Airways Flight 771">Afriqiyah Airway=
s Flight 771</a></b>, an Airbus A330 that has flown from Johannesburg, Sout=
h Africa, crashes on landing at Tripoli International Airport, Libya, killi=
ng all but one of the 104 people on board; the sole survivor is a child fro=
m the Netherlands.</li>
<li>May 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pamir_Airw=
ays_Flight_112" title=3D"Pamir Airways Flight 112">Pamir Airways Flight 112=
</a></b>, an Antonov An-24 operating a domestic flight in Afghanistan, cras=
hes shortly after taking off from Kunduz Airport; all 39 passengers and fiv=
e crew lose their lives.</li>
<li>May 22 =E2=80=93<b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India_E=
xpress_Flight_812" title=3D"Air India Express Flight 812">Air India Express=
 Flight 812</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 flying from Dubai, United Arab Emirat=
es, to Mangalore, India, crashes after overshooting the runway at Mangalore=
 International Airport; 158 of the 166 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>June 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Came=
roon_A%C3%A9ro_Service_C-212_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2010 Cam=
eroon A=C3=A9ro Service C-212 crash">A CASA C-212 Aviocar crashes</a></b> n=
ear Djoum, Cameroon, while operating a charter flight to Yangadou, Republic=
 of the Congo; all 11 occupants are killed, including the entire board of S=
undance Resources, an Australian mining conglomerate.</li>
<li>June 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Air_=
Service_Berlin_Douglas_C-47_crash" title=3D"2010 Air Service Berlin Douglas=
 C-47 crash">An Air Service Berlin Douglas C-47 Skytrain crashes</a></b> du=
e to engine failure shortly after taking off from Berlin Sch=C3=B6nefeld Ai=
rport, Germany, for a sightseeing flight over Berlin; 7 of the 28 on board =
are injured in the accident.</li>
<li>July 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lufthansa=
_Cargo_Flight_8460" title=3D"Lufthansa Cargo Flight 8460">Lufthansa Cargo F=
light 8460</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-11 operating a multi-leg flight =
from Frankfurt, Germany, to Hong Kong in southern China, crashes on landing=
 at King Khalid International Airport in Saudi Arabia; both occupants of th=
e aircraft survive the incident.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airblue_F=
light_202" title=3D"Airblue Flight 202">Airblue Flight 202</a></b>, an Airb=
us A321 operating a domestic flight in Pakistan, crashes in the Margalla Hi=
lls northeast of Islamabad, resulting in the deaths of 146 passengers and s=
ix crew members; it is the first fatal accident involving an Airbus A321 an=
d Pakistan's worst air disaster.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katekavi=
a_Flight_9357" title=3D"Katekavia Flight 9357">Katekavia Flight 9357</a></b=
>, an Antonov An-24 operating a domestic flight in Russia, crashes on appro=
ach to Igarka Airport in Krasnoyarsk Krai, killing 12 of the 15 people on b=
oard.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AIRES_F=

 737 operating a domestic flight in Colombia, splits apart after a hard lan=
ding at Gustavo Rojas Pinilla Airport in San Andr=C3=A9s; of the 125 passen=
gers and six crew members on board, two passengers are killed and another 1=
13 injured.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agni_Ai=

Dornier Do 228 operating a domestic flight in Nepal, crashes near Shikharpu=
r in heavy rain, shortly after departing from Kathmandu, killing all 14 peo=
ple on board.</li>
<li>August 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henan_A=
irlines_Flight_8387" title=3D"Henan Airlines Flight 8387">Henan Airlines Fl=
ight 8387</a></b>, an Embraer E-190 operating a domestic flight in China, o=
vershoots the runway and crashes at Yichun, Heilongjiang, killing 44 of the=
 91 passengers and five crew members; this is the first hull loss of an Emb=
raer E-Jet.</li>
<li>August 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Fi=
lair_Let_L-410_crash" title=3D"2010 Filair Let L-410 crash">A Filair Let L-=
410 Turbolet crashes</a></b> on approach to Bandundu Airport, Democratic Re=
public of the Congo, killing all but one of the 21 on board.</li>
<li>September 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UPS_A=
irlines_Flight_6" title=3D"UPS Airlines Flight 6">UPS Airlines Flight 6</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 747-400 flying from Dubai, United Arab Emirates, to Cologne,=
 Germany, crashes at a military base shortly after takeoff, killing both cr=
ew members.</li>
<li>September 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alros=
a_Flight_514" title=3D"Alrosa Flight 514">Alrosa Flight 514</a></b>, a Tupo=
lev Tu-154M operating a domestic flight in Russia, makes a successful emerg=
ency landing at Izhma Airport after suffering in-flight electrical failure;=
 the aircraft overshoots the runway after landing but all 81 passengers and=
 crew survive the incident.</li>
<li>September 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conv=
iasa_Flight_2350" title=3D"Conviasa Flight 2350">Conviasa Flight 2350</a></=
b>, an ATR-42 operating a domestic flight in Venezuela, crashes shortly bef=
ore landing at Guayana International Airport, killing 15 of the 51 people o=
n board.</li>
<li>November 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aero_C=
aribbean_Flight_883" title=3D"Aero Caribbean Flight 883">Aero Caribbean Fli=
ght 883</a></b>, an ATR-72 bound from Haiti to Cuba, crashes in the central=
 Cuban province of Sancti Sp=C3=ADritus, killing all 68 on board in one of =
the worst-ever accidents involving the ATR 72.</li>
<li>November 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qantas=
_Flight_32" title=3D"Qantas Flight 32">Qantas Flight 32</a></b>, an Airbus =
A380 flying from London's Heathrow Airport to Sydney, Australia, suffers an=
 uncontained engine failure after taking off from Singapore's Changi Airpor=
t; upon turning back, the flight lands safely and all 469 people on board a=
re unharmed.</li>
<li>November 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JS_Air=
_Flight_201" title=3D"JS Air Flight 201">JS Air Flight 201</a></b>, a Beech=
craft 1900 operating a domestic charter flight in Pakistan, crashes immedia=
tely after takeoff from Jinnah International Airport, Karachi, due to an en=
gine malfunction; all 21 people on board are killed.</li>
<li>November 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_=
Tarco_Airlines_Antonov_An-24_crash" title=3D"2010 Tarco Airlines Antonov An=
-24 crash">A Tarco Airlines Antonov An-24 crashes</a></b> on landing at Zal=
ingei Airport, Sudan, killing six of the 44 on board.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sun_W=
ay_Flight_4412" title=3D"Sun Way Flight 4412">Sun Way Flight 4412</a></b>, =
an Ilyushin Il-76TD flying from Karachi, Pakistan, to Khartoum, Sudan, suff=
ers an engine fire and crashes near Jinnah International Airport, killing a=
ll eight crew on board and another four on the ground.</li>
<li>December 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dagest=
an_Airlines_Flight_372" title=3D"Dagestan Airlines Flight 372">Dagestan Air=
lines Flight 372</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-154 operating a domestic flight in R=
ussia, skids off the runway during an emergency landing at Domodedovo Inter=
national Airport, killing two of the 160 passengers on board and injuring 8=
7.</li>
<li>December 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_=
Okhaldhunga_Twin_Otter_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2010 Okhaldhun=
ga Twin Otter crash">A Tara Air DHC-6 Twin Otter crashes</a></b> in the Bil=
andu Forest near Shreechaur, Okhaldhunga District, Nepal, killing all 22 pa=
ssengers and crew on board.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kol=

 Tupolev Tu-154, erupts in flames while taxiing at Surgut International Air=

of 105 people on board.</li>

4 on board.</li>

 An-12 crash">2011 Trans Air Congo Antonov An-12 crash</a></b>: an Antonov =
An-12 crashes on approach to Pointe Noire Airport, Republic of the Congo, k=
illing all four crew on board and another 19 on the ground.</li>

_Airlines_Flight_812" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 812">Southwest Air=
lines Flight 812</a></b>, a Boeing 737, ruptures a hole in the fuselage at =
36,000 feet, causing the cabin to lose pressure shortly after takeoff from =
Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport. The plane lands safely at Yuma In=
ternational Airport, Arizona, with 116 people aboard, two passengers with m=
inor injuries.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Na=

 834</a></b>, a Georgian Airways plane operated by the United Nations Missi=

5428">Sol L=C3=ADneas A=C3=A9reas Flight 5428</a></b>, a Saab 340, crashes =
off Prahuaniyeu, R=C3=ADo Negro, Argentina, while en route to General Enriq=
ue Mosconi International Airport, Comodoro Rivadavia due to ice formation o=
n the wings, propellers and under the fuselage, killing all 22 passengers a=

<li>June 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RusAir_Fl=

ev Tu-134, crashes onto the Russian highway A133 near the village of Besove=

<li>July 4 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mis=

 Airways Cessna 208 crash">Missinippi Airways Cessna 208 crash</a></b>, a C=

<li>July 6 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2011_S=

></b>, a Beechcraft 1900D, crashes in dense fog while attempting to land at=

 Airlines Flight 16</a></b>, a Boeing 767, performs a belly landing at Wars=

<ul><li>April 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTair=

, crashes shortly after takeoff from Roshchino International Airport, Tyume=
n, Russia, killing 31 of the 43 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>April 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhoja_Ai=
r_Flight_213" title=3D"Bhoja Air Flight 213">Bhoja Air Flight 213</a></b>, =
a Boeing 737, crashes near Chaklala airbase, Rawalpindi, Pakistan, in bad w=
eather, killing all 127 people on board.</li>
<li>May 9 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moun=
t_Salak_Sukhoi_Superjet_100_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mount Sal=
ak Sukhoi Superjet 100 crash">Mount Salak Sukhoi Superjet 100 crash</a></b>=
, a Sukhoi Superjet 100 crashes into Mount Salak, Indonesia, on an exhibiti=
on flight, killing all 45 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>May 14 =E2=80=93 In the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_A=

2 Agni Air Dornier 228 crash</b></a>, a Dornier Do-228 crashes near Jomsom =
Airport, Nepal, during a go-around; of the 21 on board, six survive.</li>
<li>June 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Air=
_Flight_111" title=3D"Allied Air Flight 111">Allied Air Flight 111</a></b>,=
 a Boeing 727, overruns the runway on landing at Kotoka International Airpo=
rt, Accra, Ghana, and crashes through a fence; the aircraft then hits a bus=
 on a nearby road; all four crew survive but 12 are killed on the ground.</=
li>
<li>June 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dana_Air_F=
light_992" title=3D"Dana Air Flight 992">Dana Air Flight 992</a></b>, a McD=
onnell Douglas MD-83 carrying 147 passengers and six crew members crashes i=
n a suburb of Lagos, Nigeria, on approach to Murtala Muhammed International=
 Airport, killing all on board and 10 more people on the ground.</li>
<li>June 29 =E2=80=93 Six people attempt to hijack <b><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tianjin_Airlines_Flight_7554" title=3D"Tianjin Airlines=
 Flight 7554">Tianjin Airlines Flight 7554</a></b>, an Embraer E-190, 10 mi=
nutes after takeoff; passengers and crew are able to restrain the hijackers=
 until the aircraft makes an emergency landing; of the 101 on board, two hi=
jackers die and 11 passengers and crew are injured; this is China's first s=
erious hijacking attempt since 1990.</li>
<li>August 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012_Su=
dan_Antonov_An-26_crash" title=3D"2012 Sudan Antonov An-26 crash">An Alfa A=
irlines Antonov An-24-100 crashes</a></b> in the Nuba mountain range near T=
alodi, Sudan, on approach to Talodi Airstrip, killing all 32 people on boar=
d.</li>
<li>September 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petr=
opavlovsk-Kamchatsky_Air_Flight_251_(2012)" title=3D"Petropavlovsk-Kamchats=
ky Air Flight 251 (2012)">Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky Air Flight 251</a></b>, =
an Antonov An-28, crashes in Kamchatka Peninsula, Russia, killing 10 of the=
 14 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>September 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sita=
_Air_Flight_601" title=3D"Sita Air Flight 601">Sita Air Flight 601</a></b>,=
 a Dornier Do 228, crashes on the bank of the Manohara River, Kathmandu, Ne=
pal, after a bird strike, killing all 19 on board.</li>
<li>November 30 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/2012_A%C3%A9ro-Service_Ilyushin_Il-76T_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=

yushin Il-76T crash</a></b>, an Ilyushin Il-76T freighter crashes short of =
runway threshold on approach to Maya=E2=80=93Maya Airport, Brazzaville, Rep=
ublic of Congo, in bad weather, killing all six aboard, 26 on the ground, a=
nd injuring 14.</li>
<li>December 17 =E2=80=93 The <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2=
012_Amazon_Sky_An-26_crash" title=3D"2012 Amazon Sky An-26 crash">2012 Amaz=
on Sky An-26 crash</a></b> kills a crew of four, when the aircraft hits the=
 ground while crossing the Andes.</li>
<li>December 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_B=
agan_Flight_011" title=3D"Air Bagan Flight 011">Air Bagan Flight 011</a></b=
>, a Fokker 100, crash-lands on a road near Heho Airport, Myanmar, killing =
one on board, one on the ground and injuring 11.</li>
<li>December 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_W=
ings_Airlines_Flight_9268" title=3D"Red Wings Airlines Flight 9268">Red Win=
gs Airlines Flight 9268</a></b>, a Tupolev Tu-204 on a re-positioning fligh=
t, overruns the runway on landing at Moscow's Vnukovo International Airport=
, then breaks apart and catches fire; five of the eight crew on board are k=
illed in the first fatal accident involving the Tu-204.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2013">2013</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D102" title=3D"Edi=
t section: 2013">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></h3>
<ul><li>January 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SC=
AT_Airlines_Flight_760" title=3D"SCAT Airlines Flight 760">SCAT Airlines Fl=
ight 760</a></b>, a Bombardier CRJ200, crashes in thick fog on approach to =
Almaty International Airport, Kazakhstan, killing all 16 passengers and fiv=
e crew on board.</li>
<li>February 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South=
_Airlines_Flight_8971" title=3D"South Airlines Flight 8971">South Airlines =
Flight 8971</a></b>, an Antonov An-24, crash-lands in dense fog at Donetsk =
International Airport, Ukraine, killing five of 52 people on board.</li>
<li>March 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013_Comp=
agnie_Africaine_d%27Aviation_Fokker_50_crash" title=3D"2013 Compagnie Afric=
aine d'Aviation Fokker 50 crash">A CAA Fokker 50 crashes</a></b> in poor we=
ather conditions on approach to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go=
ma_International_Airport" title=3D"Goma International Airport">Goma Interna=
tional Airport</a>, Democratic Republic of the Congo, killing all five crew=
 and one of the four passengers.</li>
<li>March 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ACE_Air_C=
argo_Flight_51" title=3D"ACE Air Cargo Flight 51">ACE Air Cargo Flight 51</=
a></b>, a Beechcraft 1900C-1 crashes into a mountain whilst on approach int=
o Dillingham Municipal Airport, Alaska. Both crew members were killed.</li>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_Air=
_Flight_904" title=3D"Lion Air Flight 904">Lion Air Flight 904</a></b>, a B=
oeing 737 carrying 101 passengers and seven crew members, crashes into the =
ocean while attempting to land at Ngurah Rai International Airport on the I=
ndonesian island of Bali, injuring 46 people.</li>
<li>April 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National=
_Airlines_Flight_102" title=3D"National Airlines Flight 102">National Airli=
nes Flight 102</a></b>, a Boeing 747 freighter, stalls and crashes shortly =
after takeoff from Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan, due to load shifting, kill=
ing all seven crew members on board.</li>
<li>May 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepal_Airl=
ines_Flight_555" title=3D"Nepal Airlines Flight 555">Nepal Airlines Flight =
555</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6, overruns the runway on landing at=
 Jomsom Airport, Nepal, injuring seven people.</li></ul>

<ul><li>July 6 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asiana=

</li>

 Airlines Flight 345</a></b>, a Boeing 737, suffers a landing gear collapse=

f from Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos, killing 16 people on =

<li>October 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lao_Ai=
rlines_Flight_301" title=3D"Lao Airlines Flight 301">Lao Airlines Flight 30=
1</a></b>, an ATR-72, crashes shortly before landing at Pakse International=
 Airport under adverse weather conditions, killing all 44 passengers and fi=
ve crew on board.</li>
<li>November 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tatar=
stan_Airlines_Flight_363" title=3D"Tatarstan Airlines Flight 363">Tatarstan=
 Airlines Flight 363</a></b>, a Boeing 737, crashes at Kazan International =
Airport, Russia, during a go-around, killing all 50 people on board.</li>
<li>November 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAM_M=
ozambique_Airlines_Flight_470" title=3D"LAM Mozambique Airlines Flight 470"=
>LAM Mozambique Airlines Flight 470</a></b>, an Embraer 190, en route from =
Maputo International Airport, Mozambique, to Quatro de Fevereiro Airport, A=
ngola is deliberately crashed by the captain into Bwabwata National Park in=
 northern Namibia, killing all 33 people on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2014">2014</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

pan></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Crest_Onyx_with_the_tail_of=

ata-file-height=3D"3456"></a>  <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"ma=

ry 10,</span> 2015</div></div></div>
<ul><li>February 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N=
epal_Airlines_Flight_183" title=3D"Nepal Airlines Flight 183">Nepal Airline=
s Flight 183</a></b>, a de Havilland Canada DHC-6, crashes near Khidim abou=
t 74 kilometres southwest of Pokhara, Nepal, killing all 18 people on board=
.</li>
<li>February 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethio=
pian_Airlines_Flight_702" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Flight 702">Ethiopian=
 Airlines Flight 702</a></b>, a Boeing 767, is hijacked by the co-pilot whi=
le en route from Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, to Rome, Italy, but lands safely at=
 Geneva, Switzerland. All 202 passengers and crew aboard are unharmed.</li>
<li>March 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia_=
Airlines_Flight_370" title=3D"Malaysia Airlines Flight 370">Malaysia Airlin=
es Flight 370</a></b>, a Boeing 777 en route from Kuala Lumpur to Beijing w=
ith 227 passengers and 12 crew on board, disappears from radar over the Gul=
f of Thailand. A wing part was later found in <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/R%C3%A9union" title=3D"R=C3=A9union">R=C3=A9union</a>.</li>
<li>July 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia_=
Airlines_Flight_17" title=3D"Malaysia Airlines Flight 17">Malaysia Airlines=
 Flight 17</a></b>, a Boeing 777 en route from Amsterdam to Kuala Lumpur, i=
s shot down over eastern Ukraine, killing all 283 passengers and 15 crew on=
 board in the deadliest civilian airliner shootdown incident.</li>
<li>July 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TransAsia=
_Airways_Flight_222" title=3D"TransAsia Airways Flight 222">TransAsia Airwa=
ys Flight 222</a></b>, an ATR-72 en route from Kaohsiung to Penghu, Taiwan,=
 crashes during go-around, killing 48 of the 58 people on board.</li>
<li>July 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Alg%C=
3%A9rie_Flight_5017" title=3D"Air Alg=C3=A9rie Flight 5017">Air Alg=C3=A9ri=
e Flight 5017</a></b>, a chartered Swiftair McDonnell Douglas MD-83 operati=
ng for Air Alg=C3=A9rie en route from Burkina Faso to Algiers, crashes in t=
he northern Mali desert after disappearing from radar approximately 50 minu=
tes after takeoff, killing all 110 passengers and six crew members on board=
.</li>
<li>August 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepahan=
_Airlines_Flight_5915" title=3D"Sepahan Airlines Flight 5915">Sepahan Airli=
nes Flight 5915</a></b>, a HESA IrAn-140 (an Antonov An-140 built under lic=
ense) crashes shortly after takeoff from Mehrabad International Airport, Ir=
an, killing 39 of the 48 people on board.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skyway=
_Enterprises_Flight_7101" title=3D"Skyway Enterprises Flight 7101">Skyway E=
nterprises Flight 7101</a></b>, a Short 360 operating a charter flight for =
FedEx crashes into Maho Bay shortly after takeoff from Princess Juliana Int=
ernational Airport, Saint Martin. Both crew members are killed.</li>
<li>December 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logan=
air_Flight_6780" title=3D"Loganair Flight 6780">Loganair Flight 6780</a></b=
>, a Saab 2000, nosedives after a lightning strike. The crew makes a safe e=
mergency landing back at Aberdeen. All 33 passengers and crew are unharmed.=
</li>
<li>December 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indon=
esia_AirAsia_Flight_8501" title=3D"Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501">Indonesia=
 AirAsia Flight 8501</a></b>, an Airbus A320 en route from Surabaya, Indone=
sia to Singapore, crashes into waters off Borneo, killing all 155 passenger=
s and seven crew on board.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2015">2015</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D104" title=3D"Edi=
t section: 2015">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:TransAsia_Airways_Flight_23=
5.JPG" class=3D"image"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wi=

_Airways_Flight_235.JPG" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"165" cl=
ass=3D"thumbimage" data-file-width=3D"2292" data-file-height=3D"1718"></a> =
 <div class=3D"thumbcaption"><div class=3D"magnify"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/File:TransAsia_Airways_Flight_235.JPG" class=3D"internal"=
 title=3D"Enlarge"></a></div>TransAsia Airways Flight 235.</div></div></div=
>
<ul><li>February 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tr=
ansAsia_Airways_Flight_235" title=3D"TransAsia Airways Flight 235">TransAsi=
a Airways Flight 235</a></b>, an ATR-72, stalls on takeoff and crashes into=
 the Keelung River in Taiwan after striking the Huandong Viaduct and a pass=
ing taxi. 43 of the 58 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li>
<li>March 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Air=
_Lines_Flight_1086" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 1086">Delta Air Lines F=
light 1086</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-88 skids off the runway at LaGua=
rdia Airport and crashes into a fence, coming inches from Flushing Bay. Sev=
eral people are injured, but there are no fatalities.</li>
<li>March 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germanwi=
ngs_Flight_9525" title=3D"Germanwings Flight 9525">Germanwings Flight 9525<=
/a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes in southern France en route from Barcelona=
, Spain to D=C3=BCsseldorf, Germany as a result of a deliberate act by the =
first officer. All 144 passengers and six crew on board the aircraft die in=
 the crash.</li>
<li>March 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Cana=
da_Flight_624" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 624">Air Canada Flight 624</a></b=
>, an Airbus A320, crashes short of the runway and hits power lines while l=
anding at Stanfield International Airport, en route from Toronto. All 138 p=
assengers and crew on board survive, with 23 treated for minor injuries.</l=
i>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carson_A=
ir_Flight_66" title=3D"Carson Air Flight 66">Carson Air Flight 66</a></b>, =
a Swearingen Metro II crashes into a mountain en route to Prince George Air=
port, British Columbia. Both crew members are killed.</li>
<li>April 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asiana_A=
irlines_Flight_162" title=3D"Asiana Airlines Flight 162">Asiana Airlines Fl=
ight 162</a></b>, an Airbus A320, crashes short of the runway and hits a lo=
calizer while landing at Hiroshima Airport, en route from Seoul. All 82 pas=
sengers and crew on board survive, but 27 are injured.</li>
<li>April 25 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_=
Airlines_Flight_1878" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 1878">Turkish Airlin=
es Flight 1878</a></b>, an Airbus A320, is severely damaged in a landing ac=
cident at Atat=C3=BCrk International Airport. All 102 passengers and crew o=
n board are evacuated without injury.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trigana=
_Air_Service_Flight_267" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Trigana Air Service=
 Flight 267">Trigana Air Service Flight 267</a></b>, an ATR-42, crashes whi=
le en route from Sentani Airport, to Oskibil Airport in the eastern Indones=
ian province of Papua. All 49 passengers and five crew members are killed i=
n the crash in the worst aviation accident ever involving the ATR-42.</li>
<li>September 5 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/2015_Senegal_mid-air_collision" title=3D"2015 Senegal mid-air collision">=
2015 Senegal mid-air collision</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800, collides in a mid=
-air with a BAe 125 air ambulance operated by Senegalair over eastern Seneg=
al. The BAe 125 crashes in the Atlantic killing all seven on board, while t=
he 737 lands safely without any injuries to those on board.</li>
<li>September 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Briti=
sh_Airways_Flight_2276" title=3D"British Airways Flight 2276">British Airwa=
ys Flight 2276</a></b>, a Boeing 777-200, aborts takeoff at McCarran Intern=
ational Airport, Las Vegas, NV following an engine fire. All 189 passengers=
 and crew are evacuated safely.</li>
<li>October 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aviasta=
r_Flight_7503" title=3D"Aviastar Flight 7503">Aviastar Flight 7503</a></b>,=
 a DHC-6 Twin Otter, crashes on a mountain 11 minutes after take-off over P=
alopo, Indonesia, killing all 10 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynami=
c_Airways_Flight_405" title=3D"Dynamic Airways Flight 405">Dynamic Airways =
Flight 405</a></b>, a Boeing 767-200, erupts in flames while preparing for =
take-off at Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport. All 101 passen=
gers and crew on board survive, but 21 people are injured.</li>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metroj=
et_Flight_9268" title=3D"Metrojet Flight 9268">Metrojet Flight 9268</a></b>=
, an Airbus A321, explodes in mid-air over the Sinai Peninsula due to a ter=
rorist bomb, 23 minutes after takeoff from Sharm-El-Sheikh, killing all 224=
 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>November 4 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/2015_Juba_An-12_crash" title=3D"2015 Juba An-12 crash">2015 Juba An-12 cra=
sh</a></b>, an Allied Services, Ltd. Antonov An-12 crashes near the White N=
ile shortly after takeoff from Juba International Airport, killing 37 of 39=
 on board.</li>
<li>November 22 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avia_=
Traffic_Company_Flight_768" title=3D"Avia Traffic Company Flight 768">Avia =
Traffic Company Flight 768</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, touches down hard at =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osh_Airport" title=3D"Osh Airport"=
>Osh Airport</a> injuring 8, and causing all landing gears to be ripped off=
. The aircraft skids off the runway and the left engine is ripped off.</li>
<li>December 24 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/2015_Services_Air_Airbus_A310-300_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2=
015 Services Air Airbus A310-300 crash">2015 Services Air Airbus A310-300 c=
rash</a></b>, an Airbus A310-300F overshoots the runway at Mbuji-Mayi Airpo=
rt, Democratic Republic of the Congo due to a brake failure. The five crew =
survive but eight on the ground are killed.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2016">2016</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=
lving_commercial_aircraft&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D105" title=3D"Edi=
t section: 2016">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></h3>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:%D0%90%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B0%D0=

<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wes=
t_Air_Sweden_Flight_294" title=3D"West Air Sweden Flight 294">West Air Swed=
en Flight 294</a></b>, a Bombardier CRJ200 cargo freighter, crashes while i=
n cruise near Akkajaure in Sweden; both crew members on board are killed.</=
li>
<li>February 2 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daallo=
_Airlines_Flight_159" title=3D"Daallo Airlines Flight 159">Daallo Airlines =
Flight 159</a></b>, an Airbus A321, suffers an explosion shortly after taki=
ng off from Aden Adde International Airport, Somalia; two people are injure=
d and one, the suspected suicide bomber, is killed after falling from the a=
ircraft.</li>
<li>February 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tara_=
Air_Flight_193" title=3D"Tara Air Flight 193">Tara Air Flight 193</a></b>, =
a Viking Air-built DHC-6 Twin Otter, flies into a storm and crashes into a =
mountainside at Dana, Myagdi district, Nepal, killing all 23 on board.</li>
<li>February 26 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/2016_Air_Kasthamandap_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2016 Air Kast=
hamandap crash">2016 Air Kasthamandap crash</a></b>, an Air Kasthamandap PA=
C 750XL crash-lands in Nepal, killing the two crew members and injuring nin=
e passengers.</li>
<li>March 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/True_Avia=
tion_Flight_21" title=3D"True Aviation Flight 21">True Aviation Flight 21</=
a></b>, an Antonov An-26 crashes into the sea whilst trying to return to Co=
x's Bazar Airport, Bangladesh after an engine failure, killing three of the=
 four crew on board.</li>
<li>March 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flydubai=
_Flight_981" title=3D"Flydubai Flight 981">Flydubai Flight 981</a></b>, a B=
oeing 737-800, crashes while landing at Rostov-on-Don, Russia, in poor weat=
her, killing all 62 people on board.</li>
<li>March 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EgyptAir=
_Flight_181" title=3D"EgyptAir Flight 181">EgyptAir Flight 181</a></b>, an =
Airbus A320, is hijacked and forcibly diverted to Larnaca International Air=
port, Cyprus; all passengers and crew are released unharmed.</li>
<li>April 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batik_Air=
_Flight_7703" title=3D"Batik Air Flight 7703">Batik Air Flight 7703</a></b>=
, a Boeing 737-800, collides with an ATR 42 on the runway at Halim Perdanak=
usma Airport in Jakarta; both aircraft are substantially damaged, but all 6=
0 occupants of the two aircraft survive.</li>
<li>April 13 =E2=80=93 A <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_S=
unbird_Aviation_crash" title=3D"2016 Sunbird Aviation crash">Sunbird Aviati=
on Britten-Norman Islander crashes</a></b> on approach to Kiunga Airport in=
 the Western Province of Papua New Guinea, while operating a non-scheduled =
domestic charter flight, killing all 12 on board.</li>
<li>April 29 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2=
016_Tur%C3%B8y_helicopter_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2016 Tur=C3=
=B8y helicopter crash">2016 Tur=C3=B8y helicopter crash</a></b>, a Eurocopt=
er EC225L Super Puma helicopter crashes near Tur=C3=B8y, an island off the =
coast of Norway; all 13 passengers and crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 18 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/201=
6_Silk_Way_Airlines_Antonov_An-12_crash" title=3D"2016 Silk Way Airlines An=
tonov An-12 crash">2016 Silk Way Airlines Antonov An-12 crash</a></b>,  a S=
ilk Way Airlines Antonov An-12 cargo plane crashes after an engine failure,=
 killing seven and injuring two.</li>
<li>May 19 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EgyptAir_F=
light_804" title=3D"EgyptAir Flight 804">EgyptAir Flight 804</a></b>, an Ai=
rbus A320, crashes into the eastern Mediterranean Sea after a series of sha=
rp descending turns; all 56 passengers and 10 crew are killed.</li>
<li>May 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_Air=
_Flight_2708" title=3D"Korean Air Flight 2708">Korean Air Flight 2708</a></=
b>, a Boeing 777-300, suffers an engine failure and resulting fire while ta=
xiing for takeoff at Haneda Airport; all 319 passengers and crew are evacua=
ted although 12 are injured.</li>
<li>August 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emirates=
_Flight_521" title=3D"Emirates Flight 521">Emirates Flight 521</a></b>, a B=
oeing 777-300, lands wheels-up at Dubai International Airport and bursts in=
to flames shortly after landing; all 300 passengers and crew escape from th=
e aircraft unharmed, but one firefighter is killed by an explosion.</li>
<li>August 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASL_Airl=
ines_Hungary_Flight_7332" title=3D"ASL Airlines Hungary Flight 7332">ASL Ai=
rlines Hungary Flight 7332</a></b>, a Boeing 737, overruns a runway on land=
ing at Orio al Serio International Airport; both pilots survive.</li>
<li>August 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southwe=
st_Airlines_Flight_3472" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 3472">Southwest=
 Airlines Flight 3472</a></b>, a Boeing 737, suffers an uncontained engine =
failure over the Gulf of Mexico, causing substantial damage to the aircraft=
 and loss of cabin pressure; the aircraft lands safely at Pensacola Interna=
tional Airport, with no injuries among the 104 on board.</li>
<li>October 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americ=
an_Airlines_Flight_383_(2016)" title=3D"American Airlines Flight 383 (2016)=
">American Airlines Flight 383</a></b>, a Boeing 767-300ER, suffers an unco=
ntained engine failure and fire at Chicago O'Hare Airport; 20 of the 170 pe=
ople on board suffer injuries.</li>
<li>October 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FedEx_=
Express_Flight_910" title=3D"FedEx Express Flight 910">FedEx Express Flight=
 910</a></b>, a McDonnell Douglas MD-10-10F, skids off the runway after the=
 landing gear collapses on landing at Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood Internation=
al Airport; the left wing is severely damaged in a post-crash fire but both=
 pilots survive.</li>
<li>October 31 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/2016_Alfa_Indonesia_DHC-4_crash" title=3D"2016 Alfa Indonesia DHC-4 crash"=
>2016 Alfa Indonesia DHC-4 crash</a></b>, a DHC-4T Turbo Caribou operating =
a cargo flight to Ilaga Airport, Indonesia, crashes in the Ilaga Pass; all =
four crew members are killed.</li>
<li>November 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LaMia=
_Flight_2933" title=3D"LaMia Flight 2933">LaMia Flight 2933</a></b>, an Avr=
o RJ85, crashes at Cerro Gordo en route to Medell=C3=ADn, Colombia, whilst =
carrying the Brazilian football team Chapecoense; all but six of the 77 pas=
sengers and crew die.</li>
<li>December 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakist=
an_International_Airlines_Flight_661" title=3D"Pakistan International Airli=
nes Flight 661">Pakistan International Airlines Flight 661</a></b>, an ATR-=
42-500, crashes at Havelian while en route from Chitral to Islamabad; all 4=
2 passengers and five crew members are killed in the accident.</li>
<li>December 20 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeros=
ucre_Flight_157" title=3D"Aerosucre Flight 157">Aerosucre Flight 157</a></b=
>, a Boeing 727-200, crashes while failing to take off from Puerto Carre=C3=
=B1o en route to Bogota, Colombia; there is only one survivor among the six=
 crew members on board.</li>
<li>December 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afriq=
iyah_Airways_Flight_209" title=3D"Afriqiyah Airways Flight 209">Afriqiyah A=
irways Flight 209</a></b>, an Airbus A320-214, is hijacked by two Gaddafi s=
upporters and forced to land at Malta Airport; after several hours, all pas=
sengers and crew are released and the hijackers surrender.</li></ul>

<ul><li>January 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tu=
rkish_Airlines_Flight_6491" title=3D"Turkish Airlines Flight 6491">Turkish =
Airlines Flight 6491</a></b>, a Boeing 747-400F, crashes into a residential=
 area upon attempting landing in thick fog in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan. The four=
 crew members and 35 people on the ground are killed.</li>
<li>March 8 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameristar_Charter=
s_Flight_9363" title=3D"Ameristar Charters Flight 9363">Ameristar Charters =
Flight 9363</a></b>, a MD-83 chartered to fly the Michigan Wolverines men's=
 basketball team to the 2017 Big Ten Men's Basketball Tournament in Washing=
ton, D.C., overruns the runway on takeoff at Willow Run Airport, Ypsilanti,=
 Michigan after suffering a jammed elevator. The aircraft is damaged but al=
l 116 onboard survive.</li>
<li>March 20 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2=
017_South_Supreme_Airlines_Antonov_An-26_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"2017 South Supreme Airlines Antonov An-26 crash">2017 South Supreme Air=
lines Antonov An-26 crash</a></b>, an Antonov An-26 crashes on landing at W=
au Airport, South Sudan. All 40 passengers and five crew members survive.</=
li>
<li>March 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peruvian=
_Airlines_Flight_112" title=3D"Peruvian Airlines Flight 112">Peruvian Airli=
nes Flight 112</a></b>, a Boeing 737-300, is burnt out following the collap=
se of the landing gear at Francisco Carle Airport, Jauja. All 150 people on=
 board survive.</li>
<li>April 29 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2=
017_Aerogaviota_Antonov_An-26_crash" title=3D"2017 Aerogaviota Antonov An-2=
6 crash">2017 Aerogaviota Antonov An-26 crash</a></b>, an Antonov An-26 cra=
shes into a mountain whilst on a military charter flight from Gustavo Rizo =
Airport, Cuba. All eight on board are killed.</li>
<li>May 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summit_Air=
_Flight_409" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Summit Air Flight 409">Summit A=
ir Flight 409</a></b>, a Let L-410 operating a cargo flight crashes short o=
f Lukla Airport, Nepal in poor visibility. Two of the three crew members ar=
e killed, one of whom dies later in hospital.</li>
<li>July 7 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Canada=
_Flight_759" title=3D"Air Canada Flight 759">Air Canada Flight 759</a></b>,=
 an Airbus A320 on approach to runway 28R at San Francisco International Ai=
rport, nearly lands on a taxiway occupied by four loaded passenger jets. No=
 one is killed or injured.</li>
<li>September 30 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_=
France_Flight_66" title=3D"Air France Flight 66">Air France Flight 66</a></=
b>, an Airbus A380, suffers an uncontained engine failure and makes an emer=
gency landing at Goose Bay Airport, Newfoundland &amp; Labrador, Canada. No=
 one is killed or injured.</li>
<li>October 14 =E2=80=93 In the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/2017_Valan_International_Antonov_An-26_crash" title=3D"2017 Valan Internat=
ional Antonov An-26 crash">2017 Valan International Antonov An-26 crash</a>=
</b>, an Antonov An-26 crashes into the sea just short of Abidjan's F=C3=A9=
lix Houphou=C3=ABt Boigny International Airport, Ivory Coast. Four of the t=
en occupants are killed.</li>
<li>November 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khaba=
rovsk_Airlines_Flight_463" title=3D"Khabarovsk Airlines Flight 463">Khabaro=
vsk Airlines Flight 463</a></b>, a Let L-410 Turbolet, crashes short of the=
 runway at Nelkan Airport in Russia, killing four of the five passengers an=
d both crew members.</li>
<li>December 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_=
Wind_Aviation_Flight_282" title=3D"West Wind Aviation Flight 282">West Wind=
 Aviation Flight 282</a></b>, an ATR 42-300, crashes shortly after takeoff =
from Fond-du-Lac Airport, Saskatchewan, Canada. Of the 25 passengers and cr=
ew on board, all initially survive, but one passenger dies of his injuries =
in the hospital 12 days later.</li>
<li>December 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natur=
e_Air_Flight_9916" title=3D"Nature Air Flight 9916">Nature Air Flight 9916<=
/a></b>, a Cessna 208 Caravan crashes shortly after takeoff from Punta Isli=
ta Airport, Costa Rica. All 12 passengers and crew on board are killed.</li=
></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2018">2018</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

pan></h3>
<ul><li>January 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pe=
gasus_Airlines_Flight_8622" title=3D"Pegasus Airlines Flight 8622">Pegasus =
Airlines Flight 8622</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800, skids off the end of the ru=
nway at Trabzon Airport, Turkey and comes to rest on a cliff. All 168 passe=
ngers and crew survive without injury. The aircraft is written off.</li>
<li>February 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarat=
ov_Airlines_Flight_703" title=3D"Saratov Airlines Flight 703">Saratov Airli=
nes Flight 703</a></b>, an Antonov An-148, crashes shortly after taking off=
 from Domodedovo International Airport, Russia. All 71 passengers and crew =
are killed.</li>
<li>February 13 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Airlin=
es_Flight_1175" title=3D"United Airlines Flight 1175">United Airlines Fligh=
t 1175</a> </b>, a Boeing 777-200 operating a domestic flight between San F=
rancisco International Airport and Honolulu International Airport, suffers =
a contained engine failure over the Pacific Ocean. An emergency landing is =
successfully performed at Honolulu and all 373 passengers and crew survive =
unharmed.</li>
<li>February 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran_=
Aseman_Airlines_Flight_3704" title=3D"Iran Aseman Airlines Flight 3704">Ira=
n Aseman Airlines Flight 3704</a></b>, an ATR 72=E2=80=93200 on a domestic =
flight in Iran, crashes into the Zagros Mountains killing all 60 passengers=
 and six crew members on board.</li>
<li>March 11 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Ira=
n_Bombardier_Challenger_crash" title=3D"2018 Iran Bombardier Challenger cra=
sh">A Bombardier Challenger 604 private jet crashes</a></b> in the Zagros M=
ountains, Iran, killing all 11 people on board.</li>
<li>March 12 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/US-Bangl=
a_Airlines_Flight_211" title=3D"US-Bangla Airlines Flight 211">US-Bangla Ai=
rlines Flight 211</a></b>, a Bombardier Q400 on an international flight fro=
m Dhaka to Nepal, crashes at Tribhuvan International Airport; 52 of the 71 =
people on board are killed.</li></ul>

</div></div></div>
<ul><li>April 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sout=
hwest_Airlines_Flight_1380" title=3D"Southwest Airlines Flight 1380">Southw=
est Airlines Flight 1380</a></b>, a Boeing 737-700 en route over Bernville,=
 Pennsylvania, suffers an engine failure at cruise altitude. Some debris en=
ters the fuselage, causing substantial damage to the aircraft and loss of c=
abin pressure. The crew safely diverts to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Philadelphia_International_Airport" title=3D"Philadelphia Internati=
onal Airport">Philadelphia International Airport</a>. One passenger is kill=
ed; another seven are injured.</li>
<li>May 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sichuan_Ai=
rlines_Flight_8633" title=3D"Sichuan Airlines Flight 8633">Sichuan Airlines=
 Flight 8633</a></b>, an Airbus A319-100, makes an emergency landing at Chi=
na's Chengdu Shuangliu Airport after part of the cockpit windshield fails; =
all 128 passengers and crew survive the incident.</li>
<li>May 18 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cubana_de_=
Aviaci%C3%B3n_Flight_972" title=3D"Cubana de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 972">Cuba=
na de Aviaci=C3=B3n Flight 972</a></b>, a Boeing 737-200/Adv, crashes short=
ly after takeoff from Jos=C3=A9 Mart=C3=AD International Airport in Havana,=
 Cuba. 112 of the 113 passengers and crew are killed; the sole survivor is =
seriously injured.</li>
<li>June 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_UY_A=
viation_King_Air_C90_crash" title=3D"2018 UY Aviation King Air C90 crash">A=
 Beechcraft King Air C90 crashes</a></b> at Jagruti Nagar, India, killing a=
ll four people on the aircraft and one person on the ground.</li>
<li>July 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Vanua=
tu_Flight_241" title=3D"Air Vanuatu Flight 241">Air Vanuatu Flight 241</a><=
/b>, an ATR 72-500, skids off the runway after a flight from Tanna to Port =
Villa, Vanuatu. 13 of the 43 people on board suffer minor injuries.</li>
<li>July 31 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerom%C3%=
A9xico_Connect_Flight_2431" title=3D"Aerom=C3=A9xico Connect Flight 2431">A=
erom=C3=A9xico Connect Flight 2431</a></b>, an Embraer ERJ-190AR, crashes i=
nto wooded terrain in Durango shortly after take-off from Durango Internati=
onal Airport. The aircraft is destroyed, but all 99 passengers and four cre=
w survive.</li>
<li>August 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Ju-=
Air_Junkers_Ju_52_crash" title=3D"2018 Ju-Air Junkers Ju 52 crash">A Ju-Air=
 Junkers Ju 52 crashes</a></b> near Piz Segnas, Switzerland, killing all 20=
 on board.</li>
<li>August 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Ho=
rizon_Air_Q400_incident" title=3D"2018 Horizon Air Q400 incident">2018 Hori=
zon Air Q400 incident</a></b>, a Horizon Air Bombardier Dash 8 Q400 aircraf=
t registered N449QX, is stolen from Seattle=E2=80=93Tacoma International Ai=
rport with no passengers on board and later crashes on Ketron Island, killi=
ng the sole occupant.</li>
<li>August 16 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xiamen_=
Airlines_Flight_8667" title=3D"Xiamen Airlines Flight 8667">Xiamen Airlines=
 Flight 8667</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800,  crash-lands at Ninoy Aquino Intern=
ational Airport amidst heavy monsoon rains while landing runway 06/24. The =
aircraft skids off the end of the runway. All 157 passengers and eight crew=
 are unharmed.</li>
<li>September 1 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTair=
_Flight_579" title=3D"UTair Flight 579">UTair Flight 579</a></b>, a Boeing =
737-800, overshoots the runway and catches fire while landing in Sochi Inte=
rnational Airport, injuring 18 people. One airport employee dies of a heart=
 attack.</li></ul>

<ul><li>September 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Y=

g 20 of the 23 passengers and crew on board.</li>
<li>September 28 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_=

></b>, a Boeing 737-800, lands short of the runway and comes to rest in a l=

 one passenger dies whilst 34 passengers and 12 crew escape without serious=
 injuries.</li>
<li>October 11 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_India_Expr=
ess_Flight_611" title=3D"Air India Express Flight 611">Air India Express Fl=
ight 611</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 operating an international flight from T=
iruchirappalli, India to Dubai, United Arab Emirates, suffers a tail strike=
 and crashes into Airport equipment and a perimeter wall on takeoff. The ai=
rcraft continues to fly for hours before diverting to Mumbai. All 136 peopl=
e onboard survive.</li>
<li>October 29 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_A=
ir_Flight_610" title=3D"Lion Air Flight 610">Lion Air Flight 610</a></b>, a=
 Boeing 737 MAX 8, crashes into the Java Sea shortly after takeoff from Soe=
karno=E2=80=93Hatta International Airport in Jakarta en route to Depati Ami=
r Airport in Pangkal Pinang, Indonesia. All 181 passengers and eight crew a=
re killed.</li>
<li>November 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fly_Ja=
maica_Airways_Flight_256" title=3D"Fly Jamaica Airways Flight 256">Fly Jama=
ica Airways Flight 256</a></b>, a Boeing 757-200, crash lands after returni=
ng to Cheddi Jagan International Airport, Guyana, after suffering a hydraul=
ic failure 45 minutes after takeoff en route to Toronto. All on board initi=
ally survive, but one passenger dies a week later due to injuries sustained=
 in the crash.</li>
<li>November 11 - <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_Astana_Fl=
ight_1388" title=3D"Air Astana Flight 1388">Air Astana Flight 1388</a></b>,=
 an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embraer_ERJ-190" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Embraer ERJ-190">Embraer ERJ-190</a>, suffers severe cont=
rol issues shortly after takeoff. It lands safely 90 minutes later at <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beja_Airbase" title=3D"Beja Airbase">Be=
ja Airbase</a>. The aircraft is written off.</li></ul>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2019">2019</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=

<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=

<ul><li>January 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20=
19_Saha_Airlines_Boeing_707_crash" title=3D"2019 Saha Airlines Boeing 707 c=
rash">A Saha Airlines Boeing 707 crashes</a></b> after overshooting the run=
way at Fath Air Base in Iran, when the crew attempts to land at the wrong a=
irport; 15 of the 16 people on board lose their lives.</li>
<li>February 23 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlas=
_Air_Flight_3591" title=3D"Atlas Air Flight 3591">Atlas Air Flight 3591</a>=
</b>, a Boeing 767 en route from Miami, Florida, to Houston, Texas, United =
States, crashes into Trinity Bay on approach to Houston's George Bush Inter=
continental Airport, killing both crew members and the single passenger on =
board.</li>
<li>February 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biman=
_Bangladesh_Airlines_Flight_147" title=3D"Biman Bangladesh Airlines Flight =
147">Biman Bangladesh Airlines Flight 147</a></b>, a Boeing 737-800 flying =
from Bangladesh to Dubai, undergoes an attempted hijacking and makes an eme=
rgency landing at Shah Amanat International Airport in Chittagong; all pass=
engers are safely evacuated and the perpetrator is shot dead by Bangladeshi=
 special forces.</li>
<li>March 9 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Colo=
mbia_DC-3_crash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2019 Colombia DC-3 crash">A=
 Laser A=C3=A9reo Douglas DC-3 crashes</a></b> while attempting to land at =
La Vanguardia Airport, Villavicencio, Colombia, killing all 11 passengers a=
nd three crew members on board the aircraft.</li>
<li>March 10 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia=
n_Airlines_Flight_302" title=3D"Ethiopian Airlines Flight 302">Ethiopian Ai=
rlines Flight 302</a></b>, a Boeing 737 MAX 8 bound for Nairobi, Kenya, cra=
shes near Bishoftu, Ethiopia, shortly after taking off from Addis Ababa's B=
ole International Airport, due to a design flaw in the flight control syste=
m; all 157 people on board died.</li>
<li>May 3 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami_Air_I=
nternational_Flight_293" title=3D"Miami Air International Flight 293">Miami=
 Air International Flight 293</a></b>, a Boeing 737-81Q operating a flight =
from Guant=C3=A1namo Bay, Cuba, to Florida, United States, overshoots the r=
unway on landing at Naval Air Station Jacksonville during a thunderstorm; a=
ll 143 passengers and crew survived the accident.</li>
<li>May 5 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aeroflot_Fl=
ight_1492" title=3D"Aeroflot Flight 1492">Aeroflot Flight 1492</a></b>, a S=
ukhoi Superjet 100 operating a domestic flight in Russia, suffers an inflig=
ht electrical failure shortly after departing from Sheremetyevo Internation=
al Airport, Moscow, and returns to the airport where it catches fire after =
landing; 41 of the 78 people on board died.</li>
<li>May 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biman_Bangl=
adesh_Airlines_Flight_060" title=3D"Biman Bangladesh Airlines Flight 060">B=
iman Bangladesh Airlines Flight 060</a></b>, a Bombardier Q400 inbound from=
 Shahjalal International Airport in Bangladesh, overshoots the runway in ba=
d weather at Yangon International Airport, Myanmar; all 33 people on board =
survived but 18 were injured.</li>
<li>May 13 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Alask=
a_mid-air_collision" title=3D"2019 Alaska mid-air collision">A Taquan Air d=
e Havilland Canada DHC-3 Turbine Otter floatplane collides</a></b> in mid-a=
ir with a Mountain Air Service de Havilland Canada DHC-2 Beaver floatplane,=
 while both are operating sightseeing flights over George Inlet, Alaska, Un=
ited States; the DHC-2 pilot and all four passengers are killed; the DHC-3 =
makes an emergency water landing with the loss of one of its 10 passengers.=
</li>
<li>June 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angara_Ai=
rlines_Flight_200" title=3D"Angara Airlines Flight 200">Angara Airlines Fli=
ght 200</a></b>, an Antonov An-24 operating a domestic flight in Russia, su=
ffers an in-flight engine failure and lands at Nizhneangarsk Airport where =
it overshoots the runway and crashes into a building; all 43 passengers sur=
vive but two of the four crew members are killed.</li>
<li>August 15 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ural_Ai=
rlines_Flight_178" title=3D"Ural Airlines Flight 178">Ural Airlines Flight =
178</a></b>, an Airbus A321 bound for Simferopol, Crimea, suffers a double =
bird strike immediately after takeoff from Zhukovsky International Airport =
in Moscow, Russia, and performs an emergency belly landing in a cornfield; =
74 of the 233 people on board are injured.</li>
<li>October 4 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine=
_Air_Alliance_Flight_4050" title=3D"Ukraine Air Alliance Flight 4050">Ukrai=
ne Air Alliance Flight 4050</a></b>, an Antonov An-12 en route from Spain t=
o Turkey, crashes on approach to its intermediate stopover at Lviv Internat=
ional Airport in Ukraine, due to fuel exhaustion; five of the eight occupan=
ts are killed and the three survivors are seriously injured.</li>
<li>October 17 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PenAir=
_Flight_3296" title=3D"PenAir Flight 3296">PenAir Flight 3296</a></b>, a Sa=
ab 2000 flying from Anchorage, Alaska, United States, to Amaknak Island off=
 the Alaskan coast, overshoots the runway after landing in erratic wind con=
ditions, critically injuring two of the 42 people on board, one of whom die=
s the next day.</li>
<li>November 24 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_=
Busy_Bee_Congo_crash" title=3D"2019 Busy Bee Congo crash">A Busy Bee Dornie=
r Do 228 crashes</a></b> into a densely populated area shortly after takeof=
f from Goma International Airport in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, =
killing all 19 occupants of the aircraft and 10 people on the ground.</li>
<li>December 27 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bek_A=
ir_Flight_2100" title=3D"Bek Air Flight 2100">Bek Air Flight 2100</a></b>, =
a Fokker 100 operating a domestic flight in Kazakhstan, crashes on takeoff =
from Almaty International Airport, killing 13 of the 98 people on board and=
 injuring 66.</li></ul>
<h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2020s">2020s</span><span class=3D"mw-=

<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"2020">2020</span><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DList_of_accidents_and_incidents_invo=

pan></h3>
<ul><li>January 8 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukr=
aine_International_Airlines_Flight_752" title=3D"Ukraine International Airl=
ines Flight 752">Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752</a></b>, a Boein=
g 737-800 bound for Kyiv, Ukraine, crashes shortly after taking off from Im=
am Khomeini International Airport in Tehran, Iran, after being hit by two s=
urface-to-air missiles launched by Iranian military forces; all 176 crew an=
d passengers on board are killed.</li>
<li>January 14 =E2=80=93 <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_=
Air_Lines_Flight_89" title=3D"Delta Air Lines Flight 89">Delta Air Lines Fl=
ight 89</a></b>, a Boeing 777-200, dumps fuel over several schools and neig=
hborhoods while returning to Los Angeles International Airport due to a com=
pressor stall, injuring 56.</li></ul>
<div class=3D"thumb tright"><div class=3D"thumbinner" style=3D"width:222px;=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Caspian_Airlines_Airplane_2=
